name: Advanced Women's Healthcare Specialists, S.C.
bio: Dr. Ranae Yockey has a passion for empowering women to make the best decisions about their own healthcare. As a mother of two, she understands the need for honest and compassionate care during the changing stages of a womans lifecycle. She is dedicated to providing a highly-educated team of providers who can blend compassionate treatment with advanced technologies to provide a warm and inviting healthcare facility.As Director of Robotic Surgical Services at Alexian Brothers Medical Center, she leads excellence in minimally-invasive surgery. She also serves as Director of the Perinatal Subcommittee, and formerly was the Director of Women and Infant Services at Alexian Brothers, as well as serving on the Quality Assurance Committee. Dr. Yockey is also a teaching physician, and an active community patient advocate through various educational speaking events. Her life is dedicated to caring for women and educating them about new and improved choices in female care. Areas of focus for Dr. Yockey are minimally-invasive surgery, high risk OB care, infertility, pelvic pain, and incontinence and weight loss.In addition to providing womens healthcare, shes passionate about helping women look and feel their best through her Revive MedSpa. Revive offers full lines of skin care, facials, Microderm abrasion and skin rejuvenation services to help her patients both look and feel amazing. After more than 19 years in healthcare, Dr. Yockey remains energetic and grateful for the opportunity to serve her patients.

name: Advanced Women's Healthcare Specialists, S.C.
bio: Allison Corro, PA-C, M.S., is a certified Physician Assistant who provides comprehensive preventive, gynecological and obstetrical care to women of all ages. Allison performs in-office colposcopies, endometrial biopsies, Intrauterine device placement and removal, as well as ultrasound imaging.Allison completed her undergraduate studies at Loyola University of Chicago, graduating Magna Cum Laude. She attended Rosalind Franklin University of Medicine and Science for her Masters of Science and Physician Assistant studies. She is certified by the National Commission for Certification of Physician Assistants, and is a member of the Illinois Academy of Physician Assistants. After graduation Allison worked in Family Practice, and participated in the National Health Service Corps, providing care to the medically underserved community.Allison is married and has two children. She enjoys watching all of the Chicago teams, trying new food, and Salsa dance.The greatest wealth is health.  Virgil

name: Advanced Women's Healthcare Specialists, S.C.
bio: Marian Catalano, APN, FNP, M.S., is a board-certified Family Nurse Practitioner who provides comprehensive preventive, gynecological and obstetrical care to women of all ages. Marian performs in-office endometrial biopsies, Intrauterine device placement and removal, she is certified in BioTE pellets hormone replacement therapy, and certified in pain management.Marian completed her undergraduate studies at Elmhurst College. She attended Saint Xavier University of Chicago graduating with a Master of Science in Nursing and Family Nurse Practitioner studies. She is certified by the American Nurses Credentialing Center and a member of the American Association of Nurse Practitioners. Marian worked in Labor and Delivery at Alexian Brothers for 20 years and served as a departmental charge nurse.  She was awarded the Alexian Brothers Nurse Scholarship and completed her graduate degree.  After graduation she served as a Family Nurse Practitioner as a Pediatric Gastrointestinal NP. She later went on to work with anesthesiologists and pain specialists and joined the Pain Management Team. She then went on the serve in the Family\/Internal Medicine area and worked with men and women of all age groups with an emphasis on primary care and prevention. Marian now returns to the area of specialty which utilizes her womens health care experience.Marian is married and has two daughters and two step-daughters. She has plenty of life knowledge of womens health within her own home.  She enjoys watching the Chicago Cubs, Bears (not lately) and Blackhawks, enjoys cooking, and has a love of music.

name: Advanced Women's Healthcare Specialists, S.C.
bio: Madison Monk, PA-C, M.S., is a certified Physician Assistant who has a passion for providing preventative, well-rounded, gynecological and obstetrical care to women of all ages.Madison grew up in Sterling, IL and completed her undergraduate studies at North Central College in Naperville, IL.  She attended Rosalind Franklin University of Medicine and Science in North Chicago, IL.  There she received her Master's of Science and Physician Assistant Studies degree.  She is certified by the National Commission for Certified Physician Assistants.  After graduation Madison got married and moved to Columbia, MO with her husband where she practiced as a hospitalist PA in Family Medicine while her husband finished up his schooling at the University of Missouri.  She then moved back to Illinois to be closer to her family and friends.  She has always had a passion for OB and Women's Health and was very grateful to find such a perfect position here to fit her interests.  She has really enjoyed expanding her knowledge of women's health and getting to care for amazing patients alongside such a friendly and knowledgeable staff.Madison is married and has one puppy that takes up all her free time outside of work.  She enjoys watching TV (especially Grey's Anatomy and Chicago PD), doing craft projects, and hiking with her husband and dog.

name: Advanced Women's Healthcare Specialists, S.C.
bio: Nicole Quigley is a talented Nurse Midwife, who has been providing OB and gynecological care to women of all ages in the practice for more than 13 years. Prior to joining AWHS, Nicole worked in Labor & Delivery for West Suburban Hospital. She also was a Radiologic Technologist for Edward Hines VA Hospital prior to completing her licensing in Midwifery. She holds a Masters of Science with an emphasis in Midwifery from the Institute of Midwifery, Women and Health at Philadelphia University, and a Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Elmhurst College. She is dedicated to supporting womens needs, and has also used hydrotherapy during labor and delivery.

name: Aesthetic Solutions
bio: Francie Ekengren, MDDr Ekengren has worked as an Emergency Department physician for over 20 years. She is also the president and chief executive officer of Mid-Kansas Wound Specialists, and the medical director and physician for Aesthetic Solutions. Dr. Ekengren received her medical education from University of Kansas School of Medicine. She returned to Wichita and completed her medical residency in family practice at Wesley through the University of Kansas School of Medicine-Wichita.  She is a Clinical Assistant Professor with the University of Kansas School of Medicine-Wichita.She has received the Kansas Health Ethics Award and HCA Frist Humanitarian Award. She has provided a number of educational presentations to professional and community audiences.Dr. Ekengrens community activities have included serving as a volunteer physician at Good Samaritan Clinic, an elder at Grace Presbyterian Church, a medical missionary volunteer in the Dominican Republic and a participant in the Susan G. Komen Race for the Cure as a survivor.She and her husband have two sons and a daughter.

name: Aesthetica
bio: Dr. Dan Purser (www.danpursermd.com), graduated with Honors from Brigham Young University and the University of Mississippi School of Medicine, and after years of endocrinology research is the bestselling author of 10 books, including co-writing a textbook, Program120: A Physicians Guide to Proactive Preventive Medicine, and the Program 120 Handbooks. His mens health book, Improving Male Sexuality, Fertility and Testosterone, was #1 in the Amazon Health Sex section for more than a week and his breast cancer book, The Breast Cancer Patients Survival Guide: Amazing Strategies for Winning, was #1 in the Amazon Health Reference section. He is also an entertaining and dynamic educator and speaker (he has never NOT been voted as The Most Popular Speaker at any conference at which hes spoken) and is popular among both the public and physicians, and has travelled many thousands of miles doing book, radio and product tours all over the world. He is also the founder of a couple of successful health product design companies through which he makes a number of products for nutraceutical companies. He is also a BIG fan of Disneyland and Disney World where you can probably find him in his off time with his wife and some of their 10 children.

name: Aesthetica
bio: Stephanie Godfrey is a nationally certified Family Nurse Practitioner through the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners. She has recently joined the Aesthetica Medical Spa and Plastic Surgery team specializing in anti-aging and wellness medicine, medical aesthetics, and bio-identical hormone replacement therapy.  Stephanie is a certified BioTE practitioner utilizing one of the most widely studied, effective and safest methods of bio-identical hormone pellet therapy available. Stephanie obtained her first Bachelors of Science degree in Health Promotion and Education at the University of Utah in 2008. She then received her second Bachelors of Science degree in Nursing at the University of Southern Nevada in 2011. She worked as an Oncology Registered Nurse while she continued her education at Georgetown University where she earned her Masters of Science in Nursing. Stephanie is a member of Sigma Theta Tau International Nursing Honor Society and the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners. Stephanies passion lies within prevention, wellness and balance, evidence-based practice, and patient education to assist her clients improve their health and overall quality of life.living beauty inside and out.

name: Affiliates of Family Medicine
bio: Dr. Seay has been a physician in the Conroe area since 1998.  She received her undergraduate degree at St. Mary's University.  Her medical degree is from UT Medical Branch.  She completed training at the Conroe Family Medicine Residency.  She has a special interest in preventative care, well woman exams, well child care, hormone replacement therapy and chronic diseases like diabetes, heart disease, and hypertension.  Her hobbies include running, gardening, cooking, and baking.

name: Affiliates of Family Medicine
bio: Dr. Garcia joined her sister in practice in 2002. She graduated from Rice University before attending medical school at UT Houston Health Science Center. She then completed her residency at Memorial Hermann Southwest Family Practice Residency. Dr. Garcia has a special interest in diabetes care, women's issues, and preventive care for the entire family. Her favorite pastimes are camping, hiking, reading, and dancing.

name: Affiliates of Family Medicine
bio: Aprill Rowe, M.D. is the full-time physician at the new Spring location. She has her undergraduate degree from Texas A&M Corpus Christi and her medical degree from UT Medical Branch. Afterwards she completed her residency at the Conroe Family Medicine Residency Program. Dr. Rowe spent a great deal of time practicing at a critical care hospital and rural health clinic where she saw patients of all ages and even delivered babies. Dr. Rowes special interests include womens health, childrens preventative care and providing comprehensive medical to care families. Her hobbies include reading, traveling, gardening and cooking. She enjoys spending time with her family and learning about new places and cultures that she hopes to visit one day.

name: Affinity Medical
bio: I am the founder of Affinity Medical, an independently owned and operated Nurse Practitioner medical office in Tempe, AZ. One of the true secrets is that Nurse Practitioners are Primary Care Providers and provide some of the most advanced and satisfying care! My practice is a fusion between traditional medicine and nursing innovation. I hear and respond to your unique needs and tailor all treatment to you!I specialize in Bio-Identical Hormone and thyroid replacement, for men and women, while offering services in preventative\/sick care to adult patients. My passion for prevention on all levels makes me an outstanding educator and mentor. I have an intense post Nurse Practitioner school training in cardiovascular and thyroid health, which is implemented into my practice. Life is full, fun and fast; I am blessed with 4 children, 3 grandchildren, and I still find time to mentor Nurse Practitioner students!Life long learning is my passion! Learning from other cultures and having the freedom to implement them into my practice is exciting. For example, being able to offer my patients energy healing (a 5000 year old philosophy). Come see me and learn how to tap into your energy!

name: AG Patel MD Anti-Aging & Regenerative Medicine
bio: Dr. A.G. Patel, MD, FAARFM was born and raised in Lusaka, Zambia, Central Africa. He graduated college\/medical school from the M.S. University of Baroda in Baroda, Gujarat, India.  He moved to London, England and worked for two years in the Radiology Department of a suburban London hospital and then two more years in a suburban London General Practice. In late 1978, he moved to the United States to pursue his career as a medical doctor. In 1980, Dr. Patel moved to Dallas, Texas and enrolled in the Residency Program at the Methodist Hospital of Dallas\/Southwestern Medical School. In October 1983, he was board certified as a Diplomat in Family Practice by the American Board of Family Practice and became a Fellow of the American Academy of Family Physicians. In January 1984, he began a solo family practice in Cedar Hill, Texas, where he has been practicing medicine for more than 27 years. In 2000, Dr. Patel incorporated Integrative Medicine into his family practice. Integrative Medicine is defined as healing-oriented medicine that takes account of the whole person  body, mind, heart and spirit  including all aspects of lifestyle. It emphasizes the therapeutic relationship and makes use of all appropriate therapies, both conventional and alternative. In 2001, Dr. Patel became a certified Zone physician and added counseling and education on high dose, highly refined fish oil for chronic illness to his list of practice services. In 2004, Dr. Patel attended an Anti-Aging Conference in London (AACL), England, which further stimulated his interest in anti-aging and alternative medicine. He has consistently continued to grow in wisdom and knowledge, resulting in him incorporating Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement Therapy (BHRT) into his practice in 2006.him becoming board certified as a Fellow in Anti-Aging & Regenerative Medicine by the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine (A4M) in 2007.  He is certified in Ondamed - Pulsed Electromagnetic Therapy (PEMF) in 2008.  He is board certified as a Fellow in Integrative Cancer Therapy by The American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine (A4M), as well as  certified in BioPhotonic Therapy (BPT) and Intravenous Nutrient Therapy (IVNT) in 2010.  He created The AG Patel MD Anti-Aging & Regenerative Medicine Center and became certified in Ozone Therapy (OT) and Prolozone Therapy (PT) by Dr. Frank Shallenberger of The Nevada Center of Alternative and Anti-Aging Medicine in early 2011.  He is board certified as a Certified Chelation Therapist by The American College for Advancement in Medicine (ACAM) in June 2011.  He is currently enrolled in the Masters in Metabolic Nutrition program at the University of South Florida.

name: Age Well MD
bio: Dr. Engsberg grew up in the Ozark Mountains of Missouri and her interest in a medical career started early. She worked in a small, rural hospital and there she discovered that anesthesia truly blended the science and art of medicine. These early years helped to form a career centered upon compassion, commitment, care, and competence. She was graduated from the University of Missouri  Kansas City School and Medicine and continued on at the Baylor School of Medicine with her Anesthesiology Residency and Cardiac Anesthesiology Fellowship and Advanced Anesthesia Clinical Care. After she completed her time at Baylor, Dr. Engsberg joined the United States Army and earned the rank of Major. During this time, she was the Chief of Anesthesia for the 67th Evac Hospital in Wurzburg Germany. She concluded her service obligation at Fitzsimmons Army Medical Center and continued her career in Denver as President of Mountain Anesthesia Concepts in Morrison, CO.  So after 30 years of working in the world of anesthesiology, Dr. Engsberg is now completing a fellowship training program in preventive medicine through the American Academy of Anti Aging and Regenerative Medicine. Dr. Engsberg is also enrolled in the University of South Florida School of Medicines masters degree program in  Regenerative Medicine and Nutrition. Essentially, her plan is to extend the safe, critical care environment provided by her anesthesiology career into the outpatient preventive medicine world of anti aging and regenerative medicine. Simply, Dr. Engsberg believes that each individual should have a choice how he\/she ages and each person also deserves a healthcare experience surrounded by compassion, care, and competence.Dr. Engsberg has a son, Christopher, who lives in Crested Butte and is enjoying the Colorado lifestyle to its fullest. She and her spouse, Kathy Vieth and their terrific Great Dane, Wilhm Dakota, all work together to provide you with the best care at AgeWell MD.

name: AgeDefy Hormone Health and Weight Loss
bio: Dr. Adams received his DMD and MD at UAB. He performed his residency at Huntsville Hospital in 1983 working in family practice. In 1992 he entered private practice in the Huntsville area, and spent 13 years at the Center for Cancer Care.Dr. Adams practices functional medicine, blending natural and prescription medicine.Dr. Adams loves animals - in fact he has 4 dogs, and 6 chickens! He enjoys hunting and fishing on a regular basis.

name: Ageless Aesthetics
bio: Anayo Umerah MD, FAFP is certified by the American Board of Family Medicine and is a Fellow of the American Academy of Family Physicians. She is also a member of the American Academy of Anti-aging and Aesthetics Medicine as well as several other professional medical associations.Prior to joining the Women's Health Institute, Dr. Anayo Umerah served as a Medical Director and adjunct clinical faculty with the University of Pittsburgh (UPMC-Mercy) department of Family Medicine. She completed her post graduate training in Family medicine at UPMC. Her major interest is in anti-aging, aesthetics, and alternative medicine.

name: Ageless Atlanta
bio: MILLARD J. COLLIER, JR., M.D. is a native of Atlanta. He received his Bachelor of Science degree from Morehouse College and his medical degree from the Medical College of Georgia in Augusta. Dr. Collier then returned to Atlanta and the Morehouse School of Medicine where he completed a three year Family Practice Residency program. During his final year he served as Chief Resident for the Department of Family Practice.Dr. Collier became a Diplomate of the American Board of Family Practice in 1988. He became a Diplomate of the American Academy of Occupational Medicine in 1991. Dr. Collier's professional memberships include the American Medical Association, the Atlanta Medical Association, the American Academy of Family Practice, the Medical Association of Georgia, the National Medical Association, the Southern Medical Association, the Georgia Academy of Family Practice and the American College of Occupational and Environmental Medicine. Dr.CoIlier is on the medical staff of HCA Parkway Medical Center and West Paces Ferry Hospital

name: Ageless Atlanta
bio: As an associate medical director of VITAS, Dr. David Blake oversees the medical care and treatment of VITAS patients in their homes, nursing homes and assisted living communities in Atlanta Georgia.Dr. Blake has a private practice in Lithia Springs, is medical director of Family First Healthcare and serves as ring physician for the Georgia State Boxing Commission.  Dr. Blake has been practicing medicine since 1996.  He earned his medical degree at Morehouse School of Medicine, where he was a Fellow and Chief Resident in the Department of Family Medicine.  He was the schools National Alumnus of the Year 2011-2012.A native of the Bronx, NY, Dr Blake has four daughters.  He enjoys sports and music, and plays basketball every week.

name: Ageless Expressions MedSpa
bio: Dr. Minton received his medical degree from the University of Colorado followed by his residency training at St. Josephs Hospital in Denver. He is Board Certified in obstetrics and gynecology. Dr. Minton encourages patient and family involvement with health care decisions. He started in private practice in 1988. Doug is married and has three children. He enjoys sailing, scuba diving, theatre, reading and hiking with his family.

name: Ageless Expressions MedSpa
bio: Becky Vanicelli, RN, is the co-founder and owner of Ageless Expressions MedSpa. She holds two degrees, one in Psychology and one in Nursing, which has supported over 35 years of exceptional service in health and wellness. Passionately empathetic, she is the office guinea pig when it comes to safe, advanced medical treatments and technology; she often jokes that she buys the treatments she wants for the business for the tax write-offs! One of the most recent, life-changing additions for her clients has been The MonaLisa Touch brings the spark and intimacy back into your romantic relationship. Collaborative care is essential to your relationship with Becky. For example, with every type of treatment from BioTE bio-identical hormone replacement to Botox facial injectables, Becky starts with your unique needs and desires; then, you collaborate with her on a treatment plan to achieve your goals. Becky is the ultimate provider in that she understands what you need from a similar perspective. In her superior care, you will age healthier and live happier.

name: Ageless Expressions MedSpa
bio: Allison has 13 years of experience as a nurse, with 10 years focusing on the care of women and families as a labor and delivery nurse. She holds an extra certification in Inpatient Obstetrics since 2009. Allison received her BSN from Georgetown University in Washington, DC and is currently finishing her MSN as a Family Nurse Practitioner from University of Colorado-Colorado Springs, graduating in December 2017. She served for 6 years in the United States Army Nurse Corps, achieved the rank of Captain and is married to a combat veteran, who deployed twice to Iraq. She has two daughters, Maggie (8) and Penny (4). Allison values most the individual connections that she can make with her patients and develop a sense of trust that comes from active listening and compassion. What motivates her is learning new skills every day and helping her patients receive the best research-based, individualized care available. Her hobbies include volleyball, reading, snowboarding, and traveling with her family. Allisons goal in joining the Ageless Expressions team is to learn from her patients about their goals for aging healthier and happier and creating a unique treatment plan with the amazing treatments we have available.

name: Ageless Expressions MedSpa
bio: Kimberly Paine is a board-certified Nurse Practitioner who joined the practice in April 2018. She holds multiple degrees; her first degree is in Business Administration\/Finance. After working for a few years in a variety of financial positions she returned to school for a bachelors degree in nursing and then furthering her education with a masters degree in nursing. She spent most of her nursing career in the Emergency Room and had the incredible opportunity of working as a Flight Nurse for Flight for Life, which prepared her for a busy environment and taught her how to manage a large patient flow. She is currently holds a position as a Nurse Practitioner in Cardiology while advancing her knowledge in the aestheticfield along the way. She has a passion for aesthetics and has a growing interest in learning everything she can to pass along to her patients in order to care for them better. She enjoys learning new procedures and treatments that benefit her patients for an individualized treatment experience. She is passionate about her work and loves getting to know herpatients. She looks forward to collaborating for a personalized treatment plan designed for you.

name: Ageless Expressions MedSpa
bio: Dr. Minton received his medical degree from the University of Colorado followed by his residency training at St. Josephs Hospital in Denver. He is Board Certified in obstetrics and gynecology. Dr. Minton encourages patient and family involvement with health care decisions. He started in private practice in 1988. Doug is married and has three children. He enjoys sailing, scuba diving, theatre, reading and hiking with his family.

name: Ageless Image Med Spa
bio: Dr. Eldore was born in Spokane, Washington.  In 1988, he married  his high-school sweetheart and began the educational process that would eventually lead to his medical degree.  Dr. Eldore and his wife have four children ranging in age from late teens to  mid-twenties.  He is a dedicated husband and father and loves, above all else, spending time with his wife and children. Dr. Eldore graduated from Creighton University School of Medicine in Omaha, Nebraska in 1995. Afterwards, he and his family moved to Temple, Texas to complete his  OB\/GYN residency training program at Scott and White Hospital until 1999. He spent the next 4 years practicing medicine in The United States Air Force at Barksdale Air Force Base in Bossier City, Louisiana. His desire to return to Texas brought him to Athens in 2003, where he planted roots, raised his family, and has owned and operated Athens Women's & Children's Center ever since.Driven by a desire to develop new skills and help his patients in different ways, Dr. Eldore developed an increasing interest and involvement in aesthetic treatments. In 2006, he began serving as medical director for a local aesthetics practice, owned by Julie Harrell LE, CLT and began administering Botox and Juvederm after receiving hands on training in California. In 2009, Dr. Eldore and Ms. Harrell opened Ageless Image, a medical spa in Athens.  Ageless Image is now the premier med-spa in the region and, together, Dr. Eldore and Julie offer essentially all types of aesthetic, hormonal, and wellness services for men and women.In 2012, Dr. Eldore was introduced to bio-identical hormone therapy using pellet implants.  He quickly became fascinated with this therapy and, with great excitement, he incorporated it into his medical practice.  The powerful benefits, the prolonged effectiveness, and the ease of administration made estrogen and testosterone pellet therapy an instant hit and, before long, hundreds of patients throughout the region were receiving hormone pellet therapy through his practice.  He now focuses a large amount of time and effort on providing BioTE, an incredible hormone replacement solution for fatigue, sexual dysfunction, mood elevation\/stabilization, vasomotor symptoms ( hot flushes, etc. ), genitourinary atrophy, sleep disruption, weight gain, and much more.  Dr. Eldore is the area expert on bio-identical hormone therapy and, due to the success and rapid growth of his hormone therapy clientele, he was chosen to help provide clinical training to new BioTE physicians and practitioners from around the nation at the companys corporate headquarters in Irving, Texas.  Over the last several years, Dr. Eldore has provided essential training and insight to scores of BioTE trainees.  He considers it an honor and a privilege to be able to be part of the process that is spreading the availability of BioTE throughout the nation and beyond.

name: Ageless Image Med Spa
bio: Kaylie Eldore, PA-C recently graduated from Texas Tech Universitys Physician Assistant Program and is currently practicing in Athens, TX at  the Athens Womens and Childrens Center. As a women's health physician assistant, shell be working as a part of the healthcare team providing comprehensive healthcare to the women of East Texas.

name: Ageless MD
bio: Grew up in the deep South in Atlanta, Georgia and received a full academic deans scholarship from Emory University where he received his B.S. and M.S. in quantum chemistry within four years and graduated Summa Cum Laude. He then attended Medical College of Georgia on a full academic scholarship. What that means is that he was no slouch in school. Dr. TJ moved to the beautiful city of Los Angeles where he completed his residency training in Compton South Central Los Angeles treating the most critical medical patients including some of the worse trauma cases in the country. He has been practicing Emergency Medicine for the last 15 years at a major metropolital hospital.While growing up in Georgia, Dr. TJ was cast in two feature films as a child actor which earned his membership into the Screen Actors Guild and worked as a model for print as well as television commercials. Therefore he is very aware of how a persons self image has a huge impact on their self confidence and overall well being. He is now dedicating his career to helping people look and feel their best in the field of aesthetic medicine and noninvasive cosmetic procedures. This is where the art of medicine meets the science of medicine. He has a keen eye for beauty among different cultures and even knows of certain special techniques to achieve the look that you want to make you feel beautiful and bright naturally. Come visit Dr. TJ and see how he can make you look 10-20 years younger and have you feeling like your prime.

name: Akron Clinic
bio: Dr. Caitlin Ahern received her medical degree in 1993 from the University of Utah School of Medicine.      She then went on to complete her residency at Poudre Valley Hospital in Ft. Collins, CO.  Dr. Ahern initially started working for the Yuma District Hospital in December, 1995, as a weekend locum, covering the Emergency Room.  She worked occasional weekends through July, 1996.  In September, 1996, Dr. Ahern began working for the Yuma District Hospital as a family practitioner.  In July, 2002, Dr. Ahern made a difficult decision to leave the Yuma District Hospital in order to start her own practice in Ft. Collins.  It didnt take her long to learn that trying to run her own business took too much time away from her love of practicing medicine.  She rejoined our medical staff in 2006, working at the Akron Clinic.Dr. Aherns expertise in medicine, certification in medical acupuncture, coupled with her sincerity and compassion for her patients helped her to successfully build a loyal and trusting cliental.

name: Akron Clinic
bio: Tiffany graduated from the Physical Assistant program at University of Colorado Health and Sciences, the Rural Medicine Track. Her area of specialty is Pediatrics.  She enjoys doing clinical procedures.Tiffany joined the Akron Clinic in 2008.

name: Alaric Health Beauty and Wellness
bio: Jim Whited, is a Board Certified Emergency and Family Nurse Practitioner. Jim's career started in 1987 as a Hospital Corpsman in the United States Navy, where he started out as an E-1.  After much time and study Jim spent much of his time advancing up the ranks and after obtaining his Bachelors in the science of nursing Jim commissioned in the Navy as  Nurse Corps Officer. After almost 20 years of service Jim went on to join the United States Army where he at present is a 1LT in the Army Reserves. Jim then proceeded to complete his Masters in the Science of Nursing and became a Board Certified Advanced Registered Nurse Practitioner specializing in Emergency, Family and Mental Health Medicines. Jim currently works with both adults and children in the arena's of mental health at Dr. Carlos Torrellas's Office, PSI and CRC. Jim's well balanced approach to mental health in concert with positive demeanor make a great candidate to help those in their most troubling times. Patient care and positive outcomes for both the patient and family are what Jim strives the hardest to achieve. Jim now is the acting chair of the North Florida Advanced Practice council, and is a key player in the advancement of the scope of practice for all ARNP's in the state of Florida. An instrumental team player Jim enjoys his daily practice as well as he is the sole owner of Alaric Health and Family Practice one of the very few Nurse Practitioner owned Family practices in the state.

name: Alaska Center for Pain Relief
bio: Dr. Jill is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a Fellow of The American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists. She has the distinction of being able to converse with patients in 4 languages: English, Spanish, American Sign Language and conversational Mandarin Chinese.At the early age of 7, Dr. Jill knew that she wanted to become a medical doctor. While watching a televised special on the St. Judes Cancer Research Hospital she was moved by the impact the doctors had on the lives of those for which they cared. Thus, she continued to pursue this dream while earning her Bachelor of Science degree from Duke University and Medical Degree from the University of Kentucky, where her family is from. After marrying her college sweetheart, further training took them to New York City where she completed an OB\/GYN Internship at Cornell University\/NY Presbyterian Hospital and residency at Beth Israel Medical Center\/Mt. Sinai. Dr. Jill decided to become an Obstetrician and Gynecologist because she enjoys providing care and education to patients throughout their lives. She is also humbled by the role she plays in one of the most special events in her patients lives, the birth of their children. She has had the privilege of caring for women from different cultures and backgrounds, first in Brooklyn, NY where she practiced following residency; then in her 4 years working in the DC area at Kaiser Permanente. She has a passion for providing medical care and other volunteer services abroad. She has volunteered in Guatemala and Mexico to educate patients as well as perform pelvic floor surgeries, remove large abdominal masses and surgically treat cervical abnormalities for the indigent populations. Currently, in her new practice she has a special interest in bio-identical hormone therapy, she is happy to offer a service that helps women feel better as we age, not just normalizes our lab values. She also focuses on cosmetic gynecology, and the evaluation and treatment of heavy vaginal bleeding. My goal is to deliver a personalized womens care experience. I am board certified, but I am not your traditional gynecologist. I will provide cutting edge medical care in a relaxing spa setting.

name: Ali'i Wellness
bio: Dr. Nancy Lins, ND is a board certified Naturopathic Physician licensed in the State of Hawaii.  She received her doctoral training from Southwest College of Naturopathic Medicine and Health Sciences in Tempe, Arizona which included a four year didactic program and clinical residency.  Dr. Lins completed her clinical training in 2001 on the Big Island of Hawaii focusing primarily upon health issues pertaining to hormonal imbalances, healthy aging, rejuvenation, preventative care, complimentary and alternative medicine.A comprehensive and individualized treatment plan is developed for each patient using nutrition, lifestyle, botanical (herbal) medicine and vitamin therapies to health the body, mind, and spirit.  Dr. Lins is excited to be a BioTE certified provider to offer her patients a way to be optimal in your health and feel your best while reducing risk of disease.

name: Ali'i Wellness
bio: Dr Lopes graduated from the prestigious Bastyr University in Seattle, Washington, with a degree in Naturopathic Medicine. She has experience with pediatrics, womens health and general patient-care populations. Working as a primary care physician, Dr Lopes is well adept at treating acute and chronic medical conditions, performs physicals and well woman exams, provides nutritional and lifestyle coaching, offers homeopathic consultations, and many other services.Born and raised on the island of Maui, Hawaii, Dr. Lopes has made it her lifes work to bring quality and comprehensive natural health care to her community. Dr Lopes combines integrity, compassion, and a vast medical background in both traditional and evidence-based medicine to provide dependable and accurate healthcare.  Becoming BioTE certified completes this care as a whole to all her patients and shes excited to offer such a comprehensive approach to aging healthier and feeling your best at any age.

name: Alison Wellness Clinic
bio: Dr. Bill Alison grew up in Huntsville, Alabama. His father was a distinguished obstetrician for over 35 years. He is a Huntsville High graduate and Suma Cum Laude from Washington & Lee University. After attending medical school at UAB, he completed a General Surgery residency at Tulane in New Orleans. The emphasis was on trauma and critical care at Charity Hospital in New Orleans. During this time he spent a year of research at the Shriners Burn Institute in Galveston, Texas. His research included national publications on infections in nerve injury and burn scar contractures. He also contributed a book chapter on pediatric burn trauma. He worked extensively on several early growth hormone, growth factor and wound healing projects. His interest turned to Plastic Surgery where he completed his residency at Vanderbilt University. In this training, he learned the obvious Plastic & Reconstructive surgery, but also innovative hormone manipulation, cultivated skin grafting and critical care while running Vanderbilts burn center.Beginning practice in Huntsville in 1995, he is one of the premier Plastic Surgeons in our area. His practice is primarily Cosmetic Plastic Surgery, however, he still takes trauma calls weekly and has been chief of Plastic Surgery for over 5 years at Huntsville Hospital. For the North Alabama Community he is head of the Childrens Rehab Cleft Palate Clinic.HE IS CURRENTLY A MEMBER OF:American Board of Plastic SurgeryAmerican Society of Plastic SurgeryAmerican Society of Aesthetic Plastic SurgeryAmerican College of SurgeonsAmerican Academy of Anti-Aging MedicineDr. Alison feels with his extensive experience in surgery, critical care and research in hormone and growth factors gives him a unique ability to customize a weight-loss, wellness, and anti-aging plan for you as a patient.

name: All About Women
bio: Dr. Alvarado has maintained a private OB\/GYN practice in Bayamon, PR since 1997.  Previously worked in a multispecialty practice in Lake City Fl. Simultaneously has been the legal advisor for Health Law and Medico Legal Affairs to the Speaker of the House of Representatives of the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, as well as for the Municipal Legislatures of Catao and Toa Alta.Worked as Administrative Law Judge at the Puerto Rico Board for Medical Examiners dealing with disciplinary actions and Puerto Rico Emergency Management Agency for human resources disciplinary actions. Previously he also worked as legal advisor for the Mayor of Catao in health law and medico legal affairs acting as Chief Compliance and Risk Management Officer.As an Attorney, he was part of Landrn & Vera LLP Law Firm, he handled active stateand federal litigation, with emphasis in medical malpractice cases (both for plaintiffs anddefendants). Previously he had rendered services as a legal counselor at Patient's Advocate Office.

name: All About Women's Care
bio: Board-Certified Obstetrician\/GynecologistSusan Peck has worked in a wide range of professions in nursing and medicine since 1974. Because of her background as a nurse in Seattle, a nurse practitioner in rural Idaho and a physician in Denver, she understands health care issues from different perspectives. Following medical school at the University of Colorado, Dr. Peck completed four years of specialty training in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Minnesota. She continues to enhance her education to provide you with the latest medical developments and technology.

name: All About Women's Care
bio: Board-Certified Obstetrician\/GynecologistNancy has practiced medicine in Denver since 1980. She graduated from the University of Nebraska Medical School and completed her Residency at Mount Zion, San Francisco. She lives in Englewood with her husband and has three adult children.

name: All About Women's Care
bio: Board Certified by the American College of Nurse-MidwivesAnne obtained her Midwifery degree from the University of Southern California in 1994. After 7 years of practicing in California, she moved to Colorado where she has been practicing since. Prior to becomming a midwife she was an EMT, EKG Tech and Lab Tech.

name: All About Women's Care
bio: A Colorado native, Michelle is a Certified Womens Health Nurse Practitioner who completed her Bachelor of Science in Nursing at the University of Colorado, a Masters in Psychology at Regis University, and a Masters in Advanced Practice Nursing from the University of South Alabama.This intertwined physical and mental educational pursuit of patients wellbeing is supported by her extensive nursing, counseling\/psychology, and Obstetrics\/gynecology practical work experiences. Ultimately, Michelles priority is to her patients and their families, and her background in psychology provides her insight into understanding patients difficulties with lifes changes.Michelle lives in Arvada with her family and three dogs. Michelle loves being outdoors and taking advantage of living in the beautiful state of Colorado.

name: All About You Medical Spa
bio: Dr Gould founded All About You Medical Spa in 2013. With her top of the line training combined with her vast experience in Emergency Medicine and Ivy League education has helped place her at the forefront of a booming industry.  She knew that she was going to be on the front line of cutting-edge technologies that would revolutionize the field medical aesthetics and hormonal health. Biote is a huge piece of our practice and Dr Gould is truly committed to helping men and women live healthier, happier lives.

name: Allen Family Medicine
bio: Dr. Laura Miller is a trained practitioner of both natural and traditional medicine. She strongly believes that optimal patient care can be achieved through a synergistic combination of both methods.As a Naturopathic Medical Doctor, Dr. Miller is trained in the various disciplines of integrative\/alternative medicine: acupuncture, homeopathy, nutrition, environmental medicine, botanical medicine, and detoxification. She is also trained in conventional medicine principles and minor surgery. Dr. Miller specializes in esthetics, nutrition, vitamin therapies and womens health including anti-aging and bio-identical hormone therapy.Dr. Miller and her husband along with their 2 children reside in Mesa, AZ. When shes not practicing, Dr. Miller enjoys spending time with her family, fitness and spending time outdoors.

name: Allen Health Clinic, LLC
bio: Heather Prentice, APRN-CNP- BiographyHeather Prentice is a board certified family nurse practitioner. Her experience includes Emergency Department, Urgent Care, Internal Medicine and most recently Family Practice. She has been working in the profession for 10+ years and is currently practicing in rural Allen, Oklahoma.  She is excited to help her patients improve their quality of life through bio-identical hormone replacement therapy.Being someone who's life was changed by Biote, Heather has an excellent understanding of what it take to meet the needs of her patients. She is an advocate of integrative medicine and conserving health. She looks forward to taking care of you.

name: Alliance Medical Spa
bio: Dr. Michael Bailey has been in private practice for over 13 years. He is a graduate of the University of North Texas Health Science Center. He received his residency training at John Peter Smith Hospital. He is board certified by the American Board of Family Medicine. Dr. Bailey is also a member of the Texas Medical Association and American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine.

name: Allied Health and Wellness
bio: Jill is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner who has been working in the medical field for over 24 years.  She has made a career out of investing in the health & wellness of the Carlsbad community and the surrounding areas. Jill has worked alongside other medical colleagues in private practice settings as well as serving as Nursing Administrator for several Home Health & Hospice agencies.  To better serve the needs and growing population of Carlsbad, Jill and her husband started Allied Health & Wellness where she is able to provide medical care and wellness services focusing on the individual needs of each patient.  Jill served on the NM State Board of Home Health & Hospice, the NM State Board of Nursing Education Development Division, the NMSU Carlsbad Continuing Education Committee, and was voted Best of Carlsbad in health care over multiple years.  She graduated with honors from her BSN, MSN, and Family Nurse Practitioner Program.  She specializes in Preventive Medicine, Medical Weight Loss, Bio-Identical Hormone Optimization with Pellet Therapy, & Nutraceuticals.

name: Alpha Omega Health Center
bio: Holly Ridgley is a board certified Nurse Practitioner in the state of Georgia. She received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing, as well as her Masters of Science in Nursing, from Valdosta State University. She received a previous Bachelor of Science degree in Business and Marketing from Ball State University in Indiana in the 1980's.She has worked with many hospital systems in in the state of Georgia. This includes Glancy Rehab Center in Duluth and Piedmont Hospital in Atlanta. Other hospital systems include Phoebe Putney in Albany, GA, Georgia Southeast Health Systems in St. Mary's, GA and South Georgia Medical Center in Valdosta, GA.Holly has a passion is bringing new, safe health care technology to her patients. She is focused on HCG Medical weight loss, bio-identical hormone replacement (testosterone and estrogen), PRP (Platelet Rich Plasma injections), stem cell injections, and much more.Holly received  Bio Te pellets this past year and it has made such a difference in her life.  She is excited about bringing this to her patients as both men and women have the potential to fell so much better in midlife and beyond!!

name: Alpine Women's Center
bio: Dr. Mirna Bowden, a native of New England, came to the Flathead Valley in 2002 after finishing residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Baylor College of Medicine in Houston, TX. Prior to that, she attended medical school at University of Miami School of Medicine.Dr. Bowden enjoys providing a full spectrum of health care for women of all ages, including care during pregnancy and childbirth and gynecologic services. She has a special interest in treating infertility and urinary incontinence, and is trained in minimally-invasive laparoscopic and robotic surgery.Dr. Bowden has also received advance training in Bioidentical Hormone replacement therapy from BioTE Medical. Studies show that BHRT pellet therapy can provide superior protection to bones, brain, breasts and heart. Please visit www.biotemedical.com for additional information.She and her husband, Brett, and their children enjoy the active lifestyle of the Flathead Valley. They spend much of their free time skiing, horseback riding, and boating on Whitefish Lake.

name: Altaire Medical Spa
bio: RICK SCHUE, MS, FNP-CAn ANCC (American Nurses Credentialing Center USA) board-certified practitioner, Rick Schue uses advanced cosmetic dermatology procedures and lasers to restore aging and damaged skin. He has more than 16 years of proficient practice using advanced cosmetic dermatology procedures and lasers.Rick is one of North Dakotas most experienced practitioners of Halo skin regeneration procedures  and BBL lasers, and is currently the exclusive provider of PicoSure tattoo removal procedures. In conjunction with his regular practice, Rick is a preceptor for North Dakota State Universitys nursing program and a published author in his field.Through and through, Rick is a family man. He grew up with three brothers and four sisters, and he has three children and three grandchildren. On summer weekends, you can often find Rick competing in obstacle-course mud runs with his son or teaching his grandchildren how to water ski. He has brought his daughter, Dr. Tami Schue-Garberg, into the family business at Altaire.Rick feels his dream has come true with Altaire, but if he ever won the lottery, Rick would take on a second career as a philanthropist. Rick just really loves making people happy.

name: Altitude Family Medicine
bio: Dr. Doug Hansen, M.D. is the CEO and Medical Director of Altitude Family and Internal Medicine, a multiple location, multispecialty, wellness-based medical clinic in Denver, Colorado.  In addition to being recognized as a Level 3 Patient Centered Medical Home, Altitude Family and Internal Medicine is one of fewer than 500 highly innovative practices nationwide to be recognized by the Department of Health and Human Services in the Comprehensive Primary Care Initiative.Dr. Hansen earned his medical degree with honors at the University of Illinois College of Medicine and completed his residency training at St. Anthony Hospital in Denver.  Dr. Hansen is the only triple board-certified Primary Care Physician, Clinical Lipidologist, and Nutrition Specialist in the United States.  Dr. Hansen also has advanced training in Acupuncture and Bioidentical Hormone Replacement therapy for men and women.  Dr. Hansen has been practicing in Denver since 1999, and in addition to his clinical practice, serves as Professor of Medicine at the University of Colorado School of Medicine, on the board of directors for Colorado Health Neighborhoods, and on the medical executive board for Fullwell.Dr. Hansen is a nationally-featured expert on heart disease, hypertension, cholesterol, diabetes, nutrition, and longevity.  He has been featured on NBCs TodayShow.com and MSNBC and has contributed to many books and publications including Breakthroughs in Natural Healing 2012 and Building Foundations for Change from the bestselling Wake Up and Live the Life You Love Series.For his clinical work, Dr. Hansen is proud to be distinguished as a Patients Choice Award winner, an honor bestowed to the top 5% of physicians in the United States as voted by patients, for the past 8 years.Dr. Hansen is married to his childhood sweetheart and has 2 young daughters.  He enjoys spending time outdoors being active and spending quality time with his family.

name: Altitude Family Medicine
bio: Shara Hansen, FNP-C is a Board Certified Nurse Practitioner specializing in Family Medicine. Shara earned her undergraduate degree in Nursing from Bradley University in Peoria, Illinois and her masters degree as a family nurse practitioner from the University of Colorado.  Shara has been practicing in family medicine for over 15 years.  She has advanced training in Clinical Nutrition, Acupuncture, Medical Aesthetics, Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy, and in Executive Leadership.  Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Pellet Therapy, from BioTE Medical, is a safe and effective way for women and men to regain a happier and healthier lifestyle. Shara joined Altitude in 2010 and has had a major role in influencing Altitudes direction.  Shara believes in providing quality, patient- centered, holistic care to every patient. Shara is married to her childhood sweetheart and has 2 beautiful daughters.  She enjoys spending time with her family and spending time outdoors hiking, biking, running, swimming, snowshoeing, and snowboarding.

name: Altitude Family Medicine
bio: Dr. Ashleigh Sartor, MD is a graduate of Swedish Medical Center Family Medicine Residency. Prior to moving to Denver for residency, she received her medical degree from Wayne State University in Detroit, and undergraduate degrees in Chemistry and Biology from Hope College in Michigan.Dr. Sartor enjoys the opportunity that Family Medicine provides for forming therapeutic relationships with a large variety of patients. Dr. Sartor brings a broad scope of care to Ascend Medicine and active in all aspects of medicine including Womens Health.Dr. Sartor is currently completing a second board certification in Functional Medicine.  Functional Medicine uses a whole person approach to address the underlying causes of disease, engaging both patient and practitioner in a therapeutic partnership.  She embraces healthy living and healthy cooking and brings this expertise to her patients and as the director of the Elite Medical Weight Loss program at Altitude Family and Internal Medicine and Ascend Medicine.

Amarillo Ufirst, Med Spa and Wellness
Amelia Urgent Care
bio: Cheryl McGuire has been a Nurse Practitioner since 2015.  She received her Family Nurse Practitioner degree from Jacksonville University.   Her career consists of provided care to ages of the life spam; from pediatrics to geriatrics.  She enjoys working with all age groups and shares her passion of healthy eating and active lifestyle at every opportunity possible. When not working Cheryl enjoys a wide variety of activities from paddle boarding to boxing to spending time with her family.

name: Amethyst Wellness
bio: Dr. Amy Coopersmith is a doctorate-prepared, board-certified family nurse practitioner. She brings more than 20 years of experience in the healthcare field to Amethyst Wellness in Palm Coast, Florida, where she serves as lead practitioner and specializes in preventive medicine and aesthetics. After completing her undergraduate degree in nursing from Georgetown University in 1995, Coopersmith completed a master of science degree in nursing from the University of San Diego in 2002. In 2012, she received her Doctor of Nursing Practice from the University of Florida. Dr. Coopersmith served in the United States Army Nurse Corps for more than 10 years and achieved the rank of major. Before launching Amethyst Wellness, she spent 8 years servings as a primary care nurse practitioner at the Department of Health Flagler County.

name: Amethyst Wellness
bio: Jerry Coopersmith is board certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner.  He first obtained his associate's degree in Physiological Psychology from Mesa College in San Diego, California. He then continued his career in healing as an Officer in the United States Army Nurse Corps. He received his Bachelors Degree in Nursing from the University of Oklahoma. He then went on to obtain a Masters degree as a Nurse Practitioner from the University of San Diego. He was a National Health Service Corps Scholar and worked for the Federal Bureau of Prisons as a Uniformed Officer for the United States Public Health Service Corps. He then went on to work for the Department of Veterans Affairs, and eventually became the managing Nurse Practitioner for Home Based Primary Care.   A Certified Clinical Hypnotherapist, he also owns Flagler Hypnotherapy and specializes in men's health and wellness.

name: Ancient Art Health Center
bio: Dr. Minton received his medical degree from the University of Colorado followed by his residency training at St. Josephs Hospital in Denver. He is Board Certified in obstetrics and gynecology. Dr. Minton encourages patient and family involvement with health care decisions. He started in private practice in 1988. Doug is married and has three children. He enjoys sailing, scuba diving, theatre, reading and hiking with his family.

name: Andrew Jimerson II, MD
bio: Dr. Andrew Jimerson II, located outside Atlanta, Georgia, is one of the worlds most sought after plastic surgeons. Dr. Jimersons practice specializes in the latest techniques in cosmetic surgery.  Most commonly known as Dr. Curves for his talent to artistically shape the female body, he fell in love with Atlanta during his undergraduate education at Morehouse College. He then traveled to Ohio for medical school. After completing a dual MD\/MBA at the top-rated Case Western Reserve University, he was one of three medical students from across the nation selected to train in plastic surgery at the Ohio State University Medical Center.Dr. Jimerson performs a wide range of cosmetic surgery procedures for the body, breast, and face. He is most known for his artistry and use of fat grafting to reshape the buttocks and breast.  Other unique procedures offered by Dr. Jimerson include Scarless Hair Transplant, ThermiRF Skin Tightening, Liposonix Treatment, Hi- Definition liposculpting (abdominal etching, for example), Laser Vaginal Rejuvenation, Designer Laser Vaginoplasty as well as non surgical Vaginal Rejuvenation. Dr. Jimerson takes the time to tailor a procedure or set of procedures to each patient's desires.Dr. Jimersons expertise is know across the country.  He has been featured on several reality shows including T.I. & Tiny the Family Hustle, Love and Hip Hop Atlanta and SWV reunited and The Real Housewives of Atlanta.  He has contributed to Essence magazine and has conducted several radio interviews.  He is also recognized by his peers and has given lectures to colleagues at both the Georgia Plastic Surgery Society and the Ruberg Symposium in Columbus, Ohio.In addition to his busy solo practice, Dr. Jimerson enjoys giving back to the community.  He is especially proud to support the institution that helped shape him into the man he is today.  In addition to regular financial support, he spoke to aspiring physicians at the the Morehouse College Health Careers Society.  Philanthropy is an important ethic for him as evidenced by his financial support to Morehouse College, the National Alumnae Association of Spelman College, the Sickle Cell Foundation, No Kid Hungry and the Atlanta 2 Day Breast Cancer Walk.

name: Anna Family Healthcare
bio: Janet S. Wheat, RN ,MS FNP-C  Jan has been a Registered Nurse since 1993.  She studied at Texas Womans University and received her Masters of Science in 2006 and her Family Nurse Practitioner Certification in 2007.She previously worked at Baylor University Medical Center Dallas as a Neonatal Intensive Care Nurse, Care Flight Transport Nurse and NICU Educator.  She also served as a Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner (SANE) for the state of Texas.  Over the past 7 years, she has been providing healthcare to her patients in McKinney.  Currently, she is an Adjunct Professor in the Masters of Science Program at Texas Womans University with focus on the Family Nurse Practitioner program, serves on the Serenity High School Board in McKinney ISD and provides health care to the uninsured (ages 0-99) at the Children and Community Health Clinic in McKinney.  Jan has loved caring for her patients and is excited about offering family healthcare in Anna and the surrounding area.

name: Annapolis Integrative Medicine
bio: Dr. Alan Weiss serves as the Medical Director of Annapolis Integrative Medicine. He earned his bachelors degree from the University of Virginia and his medical degree from McGill University. He completed his internship in integrative medicine at the University of Hawaii and his residency in internal medicine at St. Elizabeths Hospital of Boston.He is board certified in internal medicine and is a fellow of the American Academy for Advancement in Medicine and the American College of Physicians.Dr. Weiss has practiced medicine since 1988. His clinical interests have led him to conduct studies and publish various articles relating to diabetes, chronic pain, fibromyalgia and chronic fatigue syndrome as well as authoring chapters in nutritional medicine textbooks.  Dr. Weiss goal is to educate and treat his patient by incorporating the latest research in the areas of conventional and alternative medicine. He continues to pursue and educate himself in leading-edge methods of achieving wellness.Dr. Weiss is also a senior program leader with Landmark Education and has traveled extensively leading breakthrough transformational programs.

name: Arata Medical
bio: Dr. Michael A. Arata graduated from the University of California, San Francisco School of Medicine in 1994. He completed residency training at Duke University in 1999. In 2000 he returned to California after a fellowship at the Hospital for the University of Pennsylvania. He works in Newport Beach, CA and specializes in Metabolic and Functional Medicine. Dr. Arata is board certified in Radiology with added qualification in Interventional Radiology. He is also board certified in Venous and Lymphatic Medicine. He founded California's largest outpatient based Interventional Radiology group and spent a decade specializing in limb salvage. While saving countless legs from amputation he yearned for a way to help these patients before their feet hit the end of the road. Functional Medicine allowed him to pursue his dream of preventing the need for invasive, limb salvaging procedures. He is the worlds first Interventional Radiologist certified in Functional Medicine.   Dr. Arata has an insatiable appetite for learning.  All doctors are required to do a minimal Continuing Medical Education to maintain their medical licenses, but Dr. Arata attends several courses per year, constantly adding to his expertise.  He has taken courses on Anti-Aging, Hormones, and is currently completing a fellowship in Metabolic Medicine.  As a member of the American Society of Bariatric Physicians (ASBP) and is eligible for board certification by the American Board of Obesity Medicine (ABOM). Dr Arata has joined the fight against obesity and is dedicated to the treatment of obesity and associated conditions.

name: Arax Nazarian DO
bio: Dr. Nazarian completed her medical education and residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of North Texas Health Science Center in Fort Worth, Texas. She has been in private practice in Lewisville, Texas since 1999.She is committed to individualized care of women at all stages of life, and feels privileged to be involved in the most personal and private aspects of her patients lives.  Her special areas of interest are minimally invasive surgery, preventative care, hormone imbalance, and the over-all well being of her patients.She is a member of the American College of Osteopathic Obstetricians and Gynecologists, is Board Certified, the American Osteopathic Association, and the Texas Osteopathic Association.Her awards are: The Patients Choice Award, Compassionate Doctor Recognition, Patients Choice 5th Anniversary, and in 2008 and  2009 in D Magazine, she was voted by her peers as the top physician that they would send their patients or loved ones to.

name: Aria Integrative Health
bio: Sonia Mookherjea, PA- C is a Physician Assistant who is passionate about uncovering and treating the underlying cause of disease for each individual. She graduated Summa Cum Laude with a Bachelor of Science in Biology and Psychology from the University of Hartford and earned her Masters in Physician Assistant studies from the University of Medicine and Dentistry of NJ in 2012. She has devoted her career to developing expertise in integrative and personalized medicine to optimize health and wellness. Sonia brings to our team clinical experience in integrative psychiatry and neurology, functional medicine and bioidentical hormone replacement therapy. In addition, she has experience in educating clinicians and patients how to interpret genetic testing data and tailor personalized medicine treatment strategies accordingly using evidence based nutraceuticals and pharmaceuticals. She has furthered her training through the American Academy of Anti Aging Medicine (A4M), The Amen Brain Health Courses, and BioTe Medical BHRT Training.

name: ARR Medical Group, PSC
address: Torre San Francisco, Suite 609, 369 Calle De Diego
bio: Ariel Rosado, M.D., has over 12 years experience internal medicine practitioner, diagnosing and treating adult conditions such and diabetes, hypertension and obesity.  He is a graduate of Guadalajara's Autonomous University and trained for internal medicine at the Ramon Ruiz Arnau University in 2005.    Dr. Rosado is passionate about helping patients to improve their health, giving the proper treatment for their conditions and balancing their hormones.  He has an extensive experience in weight loss, helping male patients with their testosterone levels and helping patients to achieve improvement in their overall health.

name: Arviv Medical Aesthetics
bio: Dr. Arviv is a caring, compassionate physician who takes the time necessary to educate and evaluate her patients and discuss their concerns. She provides each one of her patients with a comprehensive customized treatment plan that suits their needs. She has been trained in laser skin resurfacing and brings the latest technology to her practice, combined with the skincare necessary for maintaining a healthy and youthful appearance and enhancing one's natural beauty. Dr. Tali Arviv is an Aesthetics and Board-Certified Internal Medicine physician. She graduated with honors in 2006 from the University of South Florida with a Bachelor's in Science. She then pursued a degree in medicine and completed her medical education at Ross University School of Medicine in 2011 followed by her Residency at Orlando Regional Medical Center.Dr. Arviv's passion for aesthetics stems from her love for art, photography, and theater. In high school, she studied architecture, interior designing and graphic designing exposing her creative side which at first encouraged her to pursue a degree in architecture. However, she realized her connection to people and the community and wanted to be more involved and have more interaction with people. She then decided to take a different path in her education. After taking an EMT course at HCC, she felt compelled to pursue a career in medicine. While attending college, she worked as a surgical assistant doing hair transplants, received additional training to become a Certified Medical Electrologist and was trained in the art of Botox and Dermal Fillers, worked part time at as a laser hair removal technician, obtained additional education in aesthetic medicine, and attended conferences and workshops held by the American Academy of Anti-Aging.Dr. Arviv is the Vice President of Beauty and Health Institute and provides education and courses in aesthetics for other physicians and nurse practitioners. In addition to her aesthetics practice, Dr. Arviv encourages her patients to make lifestyle changes to improve their health from the inside out. She finds it rewarding that she is able to complement patient care with personalized medical aesthetic services that are safe, effective and meet her patients' needs.
