name: BEST Hormonal Wellness, PLLC
bio: Dr. Glenn Morgan is a board certified physician specializing in Obstetrics and Gynecology. He has practiced in Houston for over 20 years. In that time, he has seen Hormone Replacement Therapy (HRT) treatment options evolve to greatly improve patient care and results. Dr. Morgan believes natural hormonal therapies can offer patients a way to age with energy and vitality.Dr. Morgan is originally from New Orleans, LA. He graduated from LSU Medical School and completed his residency at Tulane University Medical School. He is a fellow with the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology (ACOG). He served five terms as chairman of the OB\/Gyn department and was chief of staff in 2007. Dr. Morgan currently serves as Chairman of the Board of Houston Northwest Medical Center.

name: BestMed Urgent Care
bio: Jeffrey Thompson, MD brings with him 10+ years of Emergency Medicine experience. He completed his Emergency Medicine residency in 2004 at Summa Health System, in Akron, OH. He earned his medical degree from the University of Texas, Health Science Center of Houston and his bachelors degree in Biochemistry and Genetics from Texas A&M University. Dr. Thompson is a current member of the American College of Emergency Physicians, the Emergency Medicine Residents Association, the Texas College of Emergency Physicians, and the American Medical Association. Dr. Thompson is a partner and is the Medical Director for BestMed Urgent Care

name: BestMed Urgent Care
bio: Jason Bedair is a board-certified Family Nurse Practitioner for BestMed Urgent Care in Lumberton, TX. He earned his Bachelors degree from Lamar University and later received his Masters degree as a Nurse Practitioner from the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston, TX. He has spent all 17 years of his nursing career working in the emergency room setting in a variety of capacities.

name: BestMed Urgent Care
bio: Fletcher Shoemaker, FNP graduated from Lamar University with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing in 2000.  The majority of his nursing experience includes the emergency room and flight nurse.  In 2014, Fletcher graduated from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center where he earned his Master of Science in Nursing with a focus in Family Practice.  He is a partner with BestMed Urgent Care in Lumberton, TX, where he works as a family nurse practitioner.

name: Bethany Mears RN WHNP-BC CNM
bio: Bethany Mears RN, Women's Health Nurse Practitioner, Certified Nurse MidwifeBethany first started her career at Hopkins County Memorial Hospital as an RN in Labor and Delivery after earning a Bachelor's Degree from Texas Woman's University. She then furthered her education at UT Southwestern to become a Woman's Healthcare Nurse Practitioner. She earned a Master's Degree from TWU in 2008 and later served as adjunct faculty for their school of nursing. Bethany is a Registered Nurse First Assistant and assists surgeons in various types of surgical procedures including cesarean sections and hysterectomies. Most recently she became a Certified Nurse Midwife and is excited to catch babies in the same Labor and Delivery unit she began her career. Bethany has over 9 years of experience in Women's Healthcare.

name: Beverly Hills Institute of Cardiology and Preventive Medicine
bio: Dr. Bereliani is a Board Certified Cardiologist, Assistant Clinical Professor of Medicine and Cardiology at UCLA School of Medicine,and specialist in Preventive Medicine and Health Optimization, located in Beverly Hills, California. As Medical Director of Beverly Hills Institute of Cardiology and Preventive Medicine, Dr. Bereliani has more than15 years of experience in diagnosing and treating complex and potentially life-threatening cardiac conditions with both traditional and integrative, and always highly personalized approaches.Dr. Berelianis practice is unique as he is among an extremely small group of mainstream\/traditional cardiologists worldwide, who also possess an in depth knowledge of functional and orthomolecular medicine,  an integrative approach that seeks to use all scientific and proven means available (not just medication) to treat heart disease.Dr. Bereliani further specializes in the field of Preventive Cardiology- This is a field that incorporates the latest cutting-edge research in advanced genetic testing along with highly specialized and sophisticated biomarkers to predict individuals chances of developing significant cardiovascular disease within specified subsequent years. Dr Bereliani will then create a personalized, comprehensive treatment approach for each individual patient. In treating patients, both those with and without cardiovascular disease, he combines the best of traditional and integrative medicine.Dr. Bereliani is actively involved in research on the latest and the most advanced cardiac monitoring technology many of which are being used in his practice - As an example, these projects include working on algorithms that not only allow full monitoring  of patients cardiac status anywhere in the world but also detect an upcoming heart attack minutes before it occurs.In addition to working in private practice for over 15 years, Dr Bereliani has served as a clinical assistant professor of medicine and cardiology at UCLAs Geffen School of Medicine since 2003. He is also on staff and part of Cedars-Sinai Medical Centers renowned Center of Excellence.Dr. Bereliani graduated number one in his medical school class of 1997, and was awarded the Alpha Omega Alpha honor society membership. He went on to complete his internal medicine and cardiology training at Ronald Reagan UCLA Medical Center.Along with teaching and research, Dr. Bereliani strives to give back to his community by extensively fundraising to further heart disease, cancer and alzheimers research. Equally important, he has created a non-profit organization to help patients with no or low income get access to free health care.Consultations are by appointment only.

name: BeYoutiful Spa
bio: Bio: Dr. Vakey is from the Texas Hill Country and attended the University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio for medical school. He completed his  residency at Vanderbilt University Medical Center and is board certified in Emergency Medicine. He is married with 2 children

name: Bio-Logique
bio: Dr Jose Negron Perez has 15 years of experience in emergency medicine, owner of Platinum Emergency Group, a leading physician group practice that provides services in the emergency medicine field. Platinum Emergency Group has been serving the healthcare industry since 2006, providing excellent patient care services. Served as Chairman of Faculty and Director of Emergency Department at Hospital Pavia Hato Rey , achieving successful Joint Commission Accreditation and organization of faculty programs to ensure excellent patient care services and satisfaction. In 2016 completed Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy certification.Dr Jose Negron

name: BioAge MD
bio: Daniela Dadurian, M.D., has been practicing Internal Medicine for over a decade. She specializes in Anti-Aging medicine, laser treatment and Cosmetic Medicine and has traveled the world researching the safest and latest technologies on the market. Dr. Dadurian received her medical degree from the University of Miami School of Medicine and is Board Certified in Anti-Aging Medicine*. Her expertise in anti-aging techniques and passion for excellence are reflected in the extraordinary and personal care she gives each patient. MD Beauty Labs at The Whitney in West Palm Beach was designed by Dr. Dadurian to provide Anti-Aging and Cosmetic services. This state of the art facility offers Medical, Spa and Body Treatments in a luxurious contemporary loft environment. With Dr. Dadurian's team of Nurses, Medical Estheticians, Massage Therapists, Permanent Makeup Specialist and Medical Spa Concierge, MD Beauty Labs is dedicated to providing a revitalizing experience.

name: BioBalance CA
bio: Rebecca L. Rogers, DNP(c), FNP, MSN, RN is a Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner who currently resides in Aptos, CA.  Ms. Rogers is obtaining her Doctorate in Nursing Practice from Samuel Merritt University where she is also full time faculty and an Assistant Professor in the Masters of Science in Nursing, Family Nurse Practitioner program.  Ms Rogers is a graduate of San Joaquin Delta College, where she received her Registered Nursing degree in 1995. After obtaining a Bachelor of Science in Health Care Administration, and a Master of Science in Nursing, she had the honor of pursuing a Post-Graduate Certification as a Family Nurse Practitioner from the University of Phoenix, Sacramento Campus. Rebecca is also an Inaugural Fellow from Duke University, Class of 2013-2014, as part of the Duke Johnson & Johnson Nurse Leadership and Transformative Care Fellowship.   Her experience as a Nurse Practitioner is primarily in Internal Medicine as a Hospitalist as well as Pulmonary, Critical Care, Infectious Disease and Womens Health.Ms Rogers has spent years of training in Integrative and Functional Medicine, obtaining certifications from Scripps Integrative Medicine, BioTE Medical, The Wiley Protocol and Duke Integrative Medicine.  She is specially trained in hormone balancing with the use of BioIdentical Hormone replacement as well as Thyroid Health, Adrenal Health, Nutrition Therapy, Vitamin and Natural Supplement therapy, Weight Loss and Medical Wellness.Ms. Rogers is the owner of BioBalanceCA located in Soquel CA, as part of Pacific Wellness Group.  She operates a Medical Wellness Clinic with emphasis in Integrative and Functional Medicine and Wellness.Ms. Rogers was one of five National recipients of the distinguished US Army Nurse Corps Spirit of Nursing award in 1995.  She is Board Certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner from the American Nurses Credentialing Center and is a member of the American Association of Nurse Practitioners, the California Association of Nurse Practitioners, and the American Association of Nurse Leaders.Ms. Rogers professional interests are focused around Health and Wellness, Education and Integrative Medicine. She enjoys life in the Monterey Bay area with her family and her animals.  She is an avid reader and loves to paint in her spare time.

name: Biocore Hormonal Wellness
bio: Dr. Eldore was born in Spokane, Washington.  In 1988, he married  his high-school sweetheart and began the educational process that would eventually lead to his medical degree.  Dr. Eldore and his wife have four children ranging in age from late teens to  mid-twenties.  He is a dedicated husband and father and loves, above all else, spending time with his wife and children. Dr. Eldore graduated from Creighton University School of Medicine in Omaha, Nebraska in 1995. Afterwards, he and his family moved to Temple, Texas to complete his  OB\/GYN residency training program at Scott and White Hospital until 1999. He spent the next 4 years practicing medicine in The United States Air Force at Barksdale Air Force Base in Bossier City, Louisiana. His desire to return to Texas brought him to Athens in 2003, where he planted roots, raised his family, and has owned and operated Athens Women's & Children's Center ever since.Driven by a desire to develop new skills and help his patients in different ways, Dr. Eldore developed an increasing interest and involvement in aesthetic treatments. In 2006, he began serving as medical director for a local aesthetics practice, owned by Julie Harrell LE, CLT and began administering Botox and Juvederm after receiving hands on training in California. In 2009, Dr. Eldore and Ms. Harrell opened Ageless Image, a medical spa in Athens.  Ageless Image is now the premier med-spa in the region and, together, Dr. Eldore and Julie offer essentially all types of aesthetic, hormonal, and wellness services for men and women.In 2012, Dr. Eldore was introduced to bio-identical hormone therapy using pellet implants.  He quickly became fascinated with this therapy and, with great excitement, he incorporated it into his medical practice.  The powerful benefits, the prolonged effectiveness, and the ease of administration made estrogen and testosterone pellet therapy an instant hit and, before long, hundreds of patients throughout the region were receiving hormone pellet therapy through his practice.  He now focuses a large amount of time and effort on providing BioTE, an incredible hormone replacement solution for fatigue, sexual dysfunction, mood elevation\/stabilization, vasomotor symptoms ( hot flushes, etc. ), genitourinary atrophy, sleep disruption, weight gain, and much more.  Dr. Eldore is the area expert on bio-identical hormone therapy and, due to the success and rapid growth of his hormone therapy clientele, he was chosen to help provide clinical training to new BioTE physicians and practitioners from around the nation at the companys corporate headquarters in Irving, Texas.  Over the last several years, Dr. Eldore has provided essential training and insight to scores of BioTE trainees.  He considers it an honor and a privilege to be able to be part of the process that is spreading the availability of BioTE throughout the nation and beyond.

name: Biocore Hormonal Wellness
bio: Kaylie Eldore, PA-C recently graduated from Texas Tech Universitys Physician Assistant Program and is currently practicing in Athens, TX at  the Athens Womens and Childrens Center. As a women's health physician assistant, shell be working as a part of the healthcare team providing comprehensive healthcare to the women of East Texas.

name: BioEnve
bio: Stefanie McCain, M.D. started her practice in Abilene, Texas in 1997 after serving 12 years in the United States Air Force, retiring as a Major. Dr. McCain attended medical school at the University of Tennessee Center for the Health Sciences in Memphis, Tennessee. She completed her residency in the United States Air force at David Grant Medical in California. Dr. McCain is Board Certified and a Fellow in the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. She has been on staff at Abilene Regional Hospital in Abilene Texas since 1997 and has been a leader in bringing da Vinci Robotic-assisted surgery to Abilene.Dr. McCain has dedicated her practice to providing quality health care to her patients and has completed advanced training in hormone replacement therapy for men and women. Dr. McCain recently received honors for having the fasted growing BioTE practice in the nation. She specializes in bio-identical hormone replacement and has many patients that are firefighters, police officers, and personal trainers. Dr. McCain has a great passion for renewing and changing the lives of her patients.Dr. McCain has three daughters: Piper, who attends New York University and will be working the research field, Hannah, who is pre-med at Southern Methodist University on an equestrian scholarship, and Olivia, who is a freshman at Wylie High School. When not practicing medicine, Dr. McCain enjoys traveling, scuba diving, showing Paint horses; she and her daughters have won several World and Reserve World Championships.

name: BioEnve
bio: After completing her undergraduate studies at Angelo State University, Stacy Hammond began her career as a Certified Emergency Nurse and a Certified Critical Care Nurse, working in the Trauma Center and Critical Care unit at Hendrick Medical Center in Abilene, Texas. In 1997, she earned her Master's Degree from the University of Texas Health Science Center  San Antonio, graduating with honors. She spent the next several years working in invasive cardiology and internal medicine\/critical care.In 2004, she came on board with Dr. McCain and they have spent the last 11 years working together, focusing on Gynecology, Obstetrics, and hormonal health and wellness. Ms. Hammond has completed advanced training in medical aesthetics and laser treatments. She is certified in facial rejuvenation procedures and BioTE hormonal treatment for men and women. Ms. Hammond has served as Clinical Site Coordinator for multiple international research studies. She also works as the medical provider for an outpatient treatment center for eating disorders and other addictive behaviors.In her 20+ years of practice, she has gained comprehensive experience, which has prepared her for managing patients holistically and completely to help guide them towards a wellness model. Having had her life personally changed from hormonal balance, she strives to focus on the patient as a whole and meet their individual needs and concerns in a personal manner.Ms. Hammond is a sustaining member of the Junior League of Abilene. She and her husband have two children. In her spare time, she can be found at the baseball field, a barrel race, or at the beach.

name: Biogenics MD
bio: Dr. Kotelko received his Medical Degree in 1976, at the University of Saskatchewan, Canada. He completed an internship in Michigan, followed by a residency in Anesthesiology at Royal University Hospital in Saskatoon, Canada. He proceeded to specialize in obstetric anesthesia and completed his Fellowship at the University of California, San Francisco.He is Board certified in Anesthesiology both in the US and Canada.Dr. Kotelko went on to work at Cedars-Sinai  Medical Center in Los Angeles from 1984 to 1994. He was the Clinical Research Director in a very busy labor and delivery unit. He went on to author over 30 articles in text books and peer- reviewed journals.He moved to Denver in 1994, trading the surf for the mountains, and worked with Metro Denver Anesthesia until 2008, medically directing high risk OB anesthesia at Pres\/St. Lukes Medical Center.In 2008, his medical career took a new direction as he became passionate about anti-aging, functional and regenerative medicine. He personally is on bio-identical hormone replacement, is gluten and dairy free, and he is a huge proponent of vitamin, mineral and amino acid supplementation.He currently is the Medical Director for Biogenics MD, located in the Denver Tech Center, Greenwood Village, CO.He is an active member of American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine (A4M) and Age Management Medical Group (AMMG) and Physicians Committee for Responsible Medicine (PCRM).Dr. Dennis Kotelko actively helps men and women to heal themselves, to thrive and feel well.He does this by optimizing hormones with Bio-identical hormone replacement therapy. He offers Bio-nutritional support for weight loss such as HCG, medically supervised body detox, IV nutrition (Meyers Protocol), lipotropic Vitamin B12 injections, and ALCAT food intolerance testing, counseling and support.He also specializes in aesthetic facial injections of Botox, Dysport, Juvederm and Restalyne.Dr. Kotelko is the medical director of over 20 active medical laser clinics in Denver. He is also the National Medical Director of the prestigious Rocky Mountain Laser College and he is a leading resource in laser medicine. He is a frequent guest on Denvers Channel 9 KUSA, Colorado and Company.

name: BioIdentical Hormone Replacement
bio: We must establish clarity between our patients expectations and what is a realistic outcome, and then guide them along the path towards achieving their goals James D. Thacker, M.D.Dr. Thacker began his career over thirty years ago at the Medical College of Georgia, Augusta. He has now broadened his repertoire towards his original passion in aesthetics and cosmetic surgery.Dr. Thacker is a Fellow of the Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons, and board certified by the American Board of Minimally Invasive Spine Medicine and Surgery, the American Board of Interventional Pain Management, and a Diplomat of the American Academy of Pain Management. He is a BioTE Certified Practitioner in advanced hormone replacement therapy utilizing bio-identical hormone pellets.Dr. Thackers commitment to excellence in medicine comes from a deep-rooted understanding of patient concerns. His spiritual background serves as the impetus by which he is able to successfully connect with each patient individually in his or her healing process. His attention to detail, comprehensive knowledge of the aging process, and his dedication to patient education, help him achieve exceptional, natural looking results for his patients.

name: bioJourney's Inc
bio: Sondra graduated from Texas Womans University in Denton, Texas with her Masters as a FNP. Her nursing career began in the first Critical Care Internship offered at Parkland Hospital in 1975. She worked in Senior Health Services and in Cardiology at Parkland in Dallas. Currently, her time is divided between a private cardiology practice and a hormonal health and wellness clinic. She became passionately interested in SottoPelle through her own personal experience as well as treating patients finding hormonal balance as the missing link to wellness and the improvement and management of chronic health conditions. Assisting individuals with chronic illnesses remain a primary area of interest. Associations include: American Academy of Nurse Practitioners, Texas Nurse Practitioners, and Heart Rhythm Society.

name: Biote Basu Aesthetic\/Plastic Surgery
bio: Board certified plastic surgeon, C. Bob Basu, MD, MPH, FACS, is the founder and managing partner of Basu Center for Aesthetics & Plastic Surgery - a thriving plastic surgery practice based in the Houston metropolitan area. As an innovator, Dr. Basu created Houstons first virtual group private practice model which employs technology to improve supply chain management over multiple providers, in multiple locations, including two AAAASF accredited surgical centers - a new paradigm in practice management in plastic surgery. His private practice, currently comprised of 90% cosmetic surgery and 10% breast cancer reconstruction\/microsurgery, has achieved performance at the top 1% compared to national benchmarks in plastic surgery as per Allergan Practice Consultants. Given his extensive experience in cosmetic breast surgery, Dr. Basu has established one of the few Allergan Black Diamond private practices in the region. He is also a top ranked plastic surgeon in Houston by Realself.com. He was recognized with the Realself100 award  placing him in the top 2% of cosmetic providers in the nation. Dr. Basu is a national leader in his field. He has served on the Board of Directors of the American Society of Plastic Surgeon (ASPS). He has also served as the Chair of the Patient Safety Committee for the society. Given his expertise in patient safety in cosmetic surgery, he also serves on the Board of Directors of The American Association of Accreditation for Ambulatory Surgical Facilities (AAAASF)  the entity that certifies the safety and quality of cosmetic surgery centers. As a recognized expert in practice management, he is also a member of the Board of Directors of Plastic Surgery Practice Solutions - the private subsidiary of the American Society of Plastic Surgeons. Locally, Dr. Basu serves as the Chief of Plastic Surgery and a partner in one of the nations most successful 100% physician-owned acute-care hospitals\/health systems, North Cypress Medical Center.

name: BioTE Clinical & Research - Tampa
bio: Dr. Tracie Leonhardt grew up as a member of the local community and is a graduate of Largo High School. She graduated from Southeastern University (now known as Nova University) in 1992, completed her internship at Suncoast Hospital in Largo, and, completed her Residency in Emergency Medicine at Midwestern University in Chicago, Illinois in 1996. Dr Leonhardt began her 14 year tenure in emergency medicine at Northside Hospital in St. Petersburg, Florida in 1996, where she earned the titles of Associate Medical Director of the Emergency Department, Chairperson of the Emergency Department and then Medical Director of the Emergency Department.  During her tenure in the Emergency Department, Dr. Leonhardt also worked with medical control for over 10 years as an online medical control physician, in which she worked closely with our first responders in the field while enhancing their education.  Dr. Leonhardt was honored to present a lecture to the American Osteopathic Society in New Orleans in 2010 on the subject of Type II Diabetes.

name: BioTE Clinical & Research - Tampa
bio: Dr. Donovitz started his practice in 1985 in Arlington, Texas.. Born and bred in Dallas, Texas, he graduated from The University of Texas, and finished medical school at The University of Texas in San Antonio. His residency training was at Tulane University in New Orleans. He is Board Certified and a Fellow in the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. Dr. Donovitz has always had a special interest in hormone replacement therapy. Treating both men and women, he was a early proponent of the bio-identical hormones. In 2007, he received advanced training in BHRT therapy.

name: BioTE Clinical & Research PLLC
bio: Dr. Donovitz started his practice in 1985 in Arlington, Texas.. name: Blink Aesthetics
bio: Aleah is a life-long Nevada resident and graduated with honors from the University of Nevada, Reno, with a BS in Neuroscience. Aleah gained valuable experience working as an emergency medical assistant and scribe at the Saint Marys Emergency Department and as a medical assistant for Sierra Nevada Nephrology. She then continued her education at Stanford University School of Medicine where she graduated top of her class and received her Physician Assistant license and a Masters in Medical Science. Aleah is our new PA joining our Aestheticare team and will be working with Dr. Charles Virden in our new clinic called The Skin Clinic. This clinic is a rapidly accessible, high quality, cash pay skin clinic designed to address common concerns such as acne treatment plans, acne scarring, benign lesion removal, simple skin cancer treatment, mole removal, and general skin care. Next time you are in our office, make sure to say hello to Aleah! She will always greet you with a warm, welcoming smile.

name: Blissful Med Spa
bio: Blissful Med Spa & Laser Center reflects Dr. Kuruvilas keen interest in health, wellness and beauty.  His medical experience  spans more than 25 years, evolving from anesthesiology to medical aesthetics.  He is board certified in anesthesiology and is specialized in pain management and medical aesthetics. Denver Spine Institute, located at Blissful med Spa is a referral center for non invasive treatments for lumbar and cervical spine condition. He has practiced at Exempla Lutheran Medical Center in Wheat Ridge, CO for over 20 years.Dr. Kuruvila also offers bio identical hormone replacement (Testosterone and Estrogen) using pellet implants. He is an expert in the field and he was trained by BioTE, one of the leading companies in this field. We are excited to offer a natural way to regain your youthful vigor and energy with BioTE hormone replacement therapy.Dr. Kuruvila personally performs all Botox, dermal filler injections and BioTE pellet implants. In addition, he consults with every laser client before the procedure. Attention to detail and safety define his medical approach.  Clients have the added peace of mind at Blissful Med Spa & Laser Center, knowing that the medical director is located on site. Dr. Kuruvila and his staff take pride in consistently providing safe and effective treatments using state-of-the-art technologies.

name: Bluegrass Preventative Medicine
bio: My name is Alana Leavell.  I am a Family Medicine Board Certified Nurse Practitioner certified by the AANP.  I have clinical experience with Family Medicine, Wound Care, Urgent and Emergency care.  I currently am a full time Emergency Medicine NP in a Level 3 Trauma Center in Central Kentucky.  I also work part time practicing in addiction, preventive and aesthetics medicine.  I received my Bachelor and Masters degrees in Nursing from Eastern Kentucky University in 2009 and 2014 respectively.  I am married with one son and we live on a beautiful cattle farm in central Kentucky.

name: BNG Aesthetics Skin & Laser Center
bio: Dr. Boris Gabinskiy's passion for minimally invasive and noninvasive aesthetics medicine and cosmetic surgery is evident in his commitment to help his patients look and feel their best at any stage of life.From your very first consultation, Dr. Gabinskiy listens to your concerns to understand your aesthetic goals, helping you achieve the best results possible. Using state-of-the art technology and treatments, Dr. Gabinskiy provides you with stellar results with minimal discomfort and downtime.Dr. Gabinskiy is board-certified through the American Board of Family Medicine. He has carefully researched and trained in the latest and most advanced cosmetic treatments with top plastic surgeons and cosmetic dermatologists in the country. He was the first in Central Pennsylvania to offer the revolutionary new Smartlipo laser lipolysis procedures such as, laser liposculpture and autologous fat grafting, a procedure which takes fat from one part of the body and transfers it to another.He continues to work and study to ensure his patients always receive the safest, most effective treatments available in the cosmetic medical industry, frequently attending local, national and international industry conferences and seminars, including, but not limited to, the International Soctiety of Coemetogynecology, American Society of Costmetic Physicians Conference, the American Academy of Costmetic Surgery, THE Aesthetic Show and meetings held by the Sciton Laser Company.Dr. Gabinskiy has lived in Central Pennsylvania, in both Lock Haven and State College, since 1998. He received his medical degree in 1983 and completed his internship and residency program at the University of Pittsburgh Medical Center. He has acquired hands-on training in advanced aesthetics medicine and skin rejuvenation from the American Association of Aesthetics Medicine and Surgery and stays active in continuing education to better serve the needs of his patients.In addition to his board certification, Dr. Gabinskiy is a member of the American Academy of Cosmetic Surgery, the American Society for Laser Medicine and Surgery, the International Society of Cosmetogynecology, the International Association for Physicians in Aesthetics Medicine, the American Association of Aesthetic Medicine and Surgery, and the American Academy of Family Physicians.He enjoys biking Pennsylvania roads, fishing in the Susquehanna river with his wife where they have competitions who can catch the most. He also tries to make time to get together with his friends to play tennis and go cross country skiing.

name: BNG Aesthetics Skin & Laser Center
bio: Natalie is a board-certified physician assistant providing our patients with a wide range of cosmetic treatments at BNG Aesthetics. She works closely with our patients to match you with BNG's best-fitting treatments and procedures, allowing for optimal results. Natalie takes the time to answer any questions you may have before your treatment, whether they be about downtime, outcome or risks.Natalie graduated with a Medical Doctor degree from Tashkent Medical Institute in 1985, and later received her Bachelor of Science degree from Pennsylvania College of Technology in Williamsport, PA. She received her advanced training in Aesthetic Medicine from the American Association of Aesthetic Medicine and Surgery and is committed to advanced ongoing training and continuing education in aesthetic and cosmetic medicine to provide the best possible care for all of her patients. She regularly attends industry conferences, including, but not limited to, the Aesthetics Laser Training & National Certification Courses, the American Society of Cosmetic Physicians, THE Aesthetics Show, and annual meetings presented by International Society of Cosmetogynecology.. Natalie is highly skilled in injectable filler techniques through certifications and advanced training. The only local injector in this area, she is a national certified Bellafill Trainer for Suneva Medical, instructing physicians, physician assistants and nurse practitioners on the use of Bellafill. Her artistic techniques have been recognized by Suneva Medical, naming her one of their top Injector Trainers.Natalie is also certified in the following cosmetic enhancements:Laser treatments (hair removal, tattoo removal, skin rejuvenation)BOTOX CosmeticDermal fillersChemical peelsLaser Tattoo removalAcne treatmentsSkin careBellafill  Expert Trainer for Suneva MedicalBioTE Medical Hormone Replacement TherapyDr. Gabinskiy and Natalie are committed to using only the latest equipment and medical-grade skin care products in order to provide each of their patients with extraordinary care, top-quality service and excellent cosmetic results. They are always ready to meet with patients to discuss their cosmetic goals and the best treatments to meet those goals.

name: Boca Center for Healthy Living
bio: My vision is to help others achieve the dream of humanity - for a long life in a healthy, vigorous, youthful body. The Boca Center for Healthy Living marks a shift in my practice from treating disease to preventing disease. It is now possible to modulate the process of aging prior to the onset of degenerative disease. We can be proactive and take a preventative approach to preserve optimal function and quality of life. Very often in the early stages of many health problems, finding the root causes help to reverse or eliminate chronic disease. Set up an appointment so that we can discuss a plan that suits your lifestyle needs. I look forward to meeting you! Dr. Matilsky is board certified in Family Medicine and a Fellow of The American Academy of Anti Aging Medicine.

name: Boca Raton Medical Management
bio: For over two decades Bradley S. Douglas, M.D. F.A.C.O.G.  board certified Obstetrician and Gynecologist has served the Boca Raton greater community in private practice in his same office location. Dr. Douglas expertise includes mastering the latest obstetrical and gynecologic surgical techniques. He is skilled at performing minimally invasive surgery using advanced Robotic, Laparoscopic, Hysteroscopic and Laster methodology. Many of his patients benefit from outpatient procedures without having to stay overnight at the hospital and without prolonged or disabling recoveries. Dr. Douglas is a graduate of Case Western Reserve University School of Medicine and is a Kennedy Scholar of the Cleveland Clinic of Cleveland, Ohio. He completed his OB\/GYN training through the Medical College of Virginia Hospital. Dr. Douglas is active in educating the public and medial communities, including being a national speaker. He has served on numerous medical advisory boards and hospital committees including past Chairman of the OB\/GYN Department at the Boca Raton Regional Hospital and past President of the Palm Beach OB\/GYN Society. Dr. Douglas also founded the colposcopy clinic at Florida Atlantic University. Dr. Douglas feels sincerely privileged to take care of the growing families in our community and looks forward to many more years of service in our community.

name: Boca Raton Medical Management
bio: Dr. McCormick has been an Obstetrician and Gynecologist in Boca Raton, Florida for close to twenty-five years. He has practiced general Obstetrics and Gynecology with a strong interest in abnormal vaginal bleeding. He has done a large number of uterine ablative procedures for abnormal bleeding. This minor surgery is done as an outpatient and the patient is usually able to return to her normal actives the next day. This allows many women o avoid the much more invasive and painful abdominal hysterectomy surgery. He also has an extensive background in Obstetrics and has delivered thousands of healthy babies. Dr. McCormick went to Emory University where he graduated Magna Cum Laud in chemistry. His medical training was at the University of Miami School of Medicine and his residency was at Jackson Memorial Hospitals prestigious OB\/GYN program.

name: Body Goal Medical
bio: Anthony Davis, M.D. is well-known for his interest in integrating medical school medicine with appropriate nutritional and common sense practices. His track record of success is both a personal success story and one that many of his patients have experienced. His down to earth approach focused on education and inspiration has helped countless people reach their goals. Dr Davis has undergraduate degrees in Molecular Biology and Cell Biology, with a minor in Chemistry. For the past decade Dr Davis has also been very interested and well versed in the use of natural hormones in finding metabolic road blocks. This provides a unique look into the inner workings of each individuals roadblocks to success. However, success begins with proper nutrition, avoiding foods that are harmful to your body, exercise, and proper vitamin and supplement recommendations. There is no magic pill, doctor, or cure  hard word, dedication, and a willingness to change are the cornerstones to successful body transformation.

name: BodyRenu
bio: Brian Rodgers, D.O. currently serves as Medical Director of the Family Wellness Clinic. He grew up in Minnesota, went to undergraduate school at BYU and Completed Osteopathic Medical school in Kansas City, Missouri. It has been Dr. Rodgers' dream to help people live more healthy, happy and productive lives.         Dr. Rodgers provides a full spectrum of family practice care including: preventative medicine, childrens health care, adult healthcare, and osteopathic manipulation. Dr. Rodgers is a Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine. Osteopathic physicians receive an additional 300 - 500 hours in the study of hands-on manual medicine and the body's musculoskeletal system.               Dr. Rodgers offers an open minded approach to your healthcare; he begins this approach in taking the time to get to know you and your history. Dr. Rodgers realizes your physical, mental, and emotional well-being are all inter-related; he will do what it takes to identify and address underlying causes to your health concerns. As a Doctor of Osteopathy, Dr. Rodgers has the ability to prescribe medication, care for hospital patients, and use Osteopathic manipulative medicine. Dr. Rodgers focus is on the entire person from the young to the elderly and everyone in between.                                     Education, Certifications and Fellowships:Board Certified Family PracticeOsteopathic PhysicianAnti-aging and Regenerative MedicineBio-identical HormonesInjections for Pain Management (Prolotherapy and Neural Therapy)Skin cancer screening

name: Bogata Health Clinic
bio: Mary Lynn Palmer is a Womens Health Care Nurse Practitioner. She attended Nurse Practitioner School in 2003 at UT Southwestern Medical Center in Dallas, and has National Certification through NCC. She has been in the nursing field for the past 20 years, working in Labor and Delivery and Post Partum at Titus Regional Medical Center in Mt. Pleasant. She also worked in an OB\/Gyn office and was a Child Birth Educator. For the last nine years she has worked at the Community Women's Clinic owned by TRMC and is currently working part-time at a Satellite Clinic located in Higgins Family Clinic in Bogata. Mary Lynn is also a Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner, certified in both Adult and Pediatrics through the Texas Attorney General's Office. Mary Lynn has been a SANE examiner since 2004. Mary Lynn lives in the Bogata Community with her husband Kenneth. They have 6 children and 5 grandchildren. She is active in her church and also serves on the Advisory Board for the Medical Assistant Program at Northeast Texas Community College. Preventative health care is a primary focus of her practice and teaching people to be an active participant in their health and well-being.

name: Bone & Hormone Wellness Center
bio: Dr. Duchamp is a graduate of the University of North Texas Health Science Center at Fort Worth. He completed a residency in Orthopedic Surgery at Mount Clemens General Hospital in Michigan.  Being an orthopedic surgeon and having treated patients with fractures due to thin bones, he developed an interest in bio-identical hormone therapy as being a solution to help the body increase the strength of its bones.  Studies show that normal bone mass will increase while a person is being treated with bio-identical testosterone and estrogen.  Not only will they help the bones, but the bio-identical hormones protect the heart, brain, and breast.  Dr. Duchamp is excited about helping his patients to have a better and fuller life.

bio: Pam's goal as a health care provider is to work in partnership with patients to help them identify and address the underlying causes of dis-ease, balance their hormones, and optimize their health.Pam Chandler is an FNP and CNP with over 30 years of experience caring for women and their families.  As an FNP, she has worked in urgent care and family medicine in the Taos, NM area, and been a part of 2 practices in Boulder offering a blend of complementary and conventional therapies.  She currently has a private practice in Boulder offering this model of integrative care to women of all ages and their familiesAs a CNM her experiences range from running a home birth practice in rural NM to joint faculty appointments in the Schools of Medicine and Nursing at the University of Colorado Health Sciences Center.  She enjoyed a long relationship with People's Clinic, a Community Health Center in Boulder for low-income patients where she provided full scope midwifery care as well as postpartum home visits for new moms and babies.Pam is currently an Adjunct Professor at the Denver School of Nursing where she has been an active participant in the Global Health Perspectives Program, taking students to work in Peru and Haiti.Pam is passionately interested in the measures to improve maternity and newborn care in underdeveloped countries and areas of limited resources.  Toward this end, she has worked on a variety of programs in Afghanistan, Haiti, Liberia, Kenya, Uganda, Peru, Ecuador, and Guatemala.

name: Boulder Whole Health
bio: Allison Galloway is a certified Family Nurse Practitioner, as well as a Certified Bariatric Nurse, Surgical Assistant, and a Masters prepared nutritionist.  She has worked in surgery and bariatrics, in both the office setting as well assisting in surgeries, for over 12 years. She also owned her own nutritional practice in Boulder for many years, counseling patients on healthy diet and disease management. But her main passion has always been in womens healthAfter graduating from Boston College in 1999 Summa Cum Laude, Allison moved to Boulder, CO. Her first job was at Wellspring for Woman, an amazing womens practice that consisted of numerous Nurse Practitioners, alternative health providers and forward thinking Doctors. This began her love for comprehensive holistic womens healthcare.  She was trained by some of the best healthcare workers in Colorado, which inspired her to get her Masters in Nutrition at CSU with honors and then become a Nurse Practitioner through Regis University, with honors.Allison strives to create a partnership with you in order to optimize your health, hormones, and diet. She has been trained to listen to how the patient actually feels vs. what tons of expensive labs say that other providers tend to demand.  Some of the modalities Allison uses are bioidentical hormones, diet, exercise, supplements, and medications if needed.  She is also trained in Botox and fillers, and is a certified BioTE Provider. She has a passion for preventative medicine and helping women and men age gracefully. She looks forward to working with you in your healthcare journey.

name: Bourget Skin
bio: Bourget Skin - Dr. Judy L. Bourget, MDDr. Judy Bourget is a highly trained cosmetic surgeon who studied at leading institutes including Harvard and Vanderbilt. She specializes in minimally invasive techniques designed to deliver optimal results with little downtime. With over 15 years experience treating and advising patients on how to age radiantly and optimally from the inside-out, her patients rave about her holistic approach to skin health and the art of aging beautifully. From her deep understanding of and passion for functional medicine to her unparalleled experience in the field of hormone replacement therapy, Dr. Bourget takes pride in helping her individual patients achieve their immediate and long-term health and beauty goals without unnecessary costs or procedures.Dr. Bourget obtained her medical degree from the University of Nevada School of Medicine and her surgical training at St. Josephs Exempla Health, Vanderbilt University, and Ochsner Medical Clinic. She completed a fellowship in burn surgery at the University of California San Diego and did research and training in limb transplantation at Harvard Medical School.Dr. Bourget is driven by her passion of encouraging people to live life to the fullest, and feeling the best you can from the inside out. She strives to create long-term relationships with each and every one of her patients, providing them with her unsurpassed knowledge, training, and most importantly care for every patient.On a personal level, Dr. Bourget is a competitive skier, swimmer, surfer and equestrian. Dr. Bourgets commitment to her profession and to her patients is rivaled by her passion for living life to its fullest!

Dr. Axline completed his internship\/residency at Akron City Hospital and joined Obstetrics & Gynecology Associates in 1996. He is board certified in Ob\/Gyn.

Her undergraduate work was at the University of Texas at Tyler, Bachelor of Science, 2002, and her Associate of Applied Science, Tyler Junior College, Respiratory Therapy, 1993Professional\/Academic Honors and Awards include Resident Trainee Award - American Federation Medical Research, February 2009, Southern Society Regional MeetingsVolunteer Work includes Mission Medical Trip to Niger Africa, 2006 working at a hospital in Rural Niger providing medical services to adults and children and a Christian\/Medical Mission Trip to Zimbabwe, Africa, 2009 to set-up clinics in rural villages in Northwestern Zimbabwe and provided care to children and adults.

name: Brazos Family Clinic
bio: Joe L. Clark IV was born at Ft Walters in Mineral Wells, Tx October 22, 1968 to Joe L. Clark III and Barbara Clark. He has three brothers he was raised in the country with. He is married to Mariko Clark they have six children they raised together. Joe has lived in Graham all of his life. His children grew up on the same land he, his father, and grandfather grew up on. He started his healthcare career as a nurses aid in 1988. In 1991 he graduated from LVN school and became a licensed nurse. Joe attended Vernon College and graduated in 1994 and became a Registered Nurse with an Associate's Degree. His nursing experience includes surgery, mental health, and Med Surg. He worked for a cardiology clinic for several years while he attended Midwestern State University to get his Bachelor of Science in Nursing and Master's Degree in nursing practice as a nurse practitioner in family practice. His philosophy is to treat his patients as he would want his family treated. He has been practicing in Jacksboro, Tx. since 2010 at the Jacksboro Rural Healthcare Clinic.  His collaborative physician is Dr. Brent Shepherd, MD. Joe recently started studying healthy aging, hormone balance, and disease prevention through hormone balance and healthy living with the assistance of BioTE and it's knowledgeable staff and professionals.

name: Brenda Marshall, MD
bio: I started my career in medicine serving my community as a Paramedic Firefighter for 10 years. As my interest in medicine grew I attended the University of Washington School of Medicine Physician Assistant Program graduating with honors in 2004. I chose to work in multiple areas of medicine including hematology\/oncology with stem cell transplantation. In 2008, I completed a critical care fellowship from Oregon Health Sciences University. I provided care as an internist and in the ICU as well as volunteering in the homeless veterans clinic, and traveling to Mexico for medical mission work, until a debilitating accident in 2010. After years of pain, multiple surgeries, and countless procedures to repair fractures, nerve and soft tissue damage I sought out regenerative medicine experts. I was fortunate to experience first-hand the incredible capability of ultrasound diagnostics and the effects of regenerative medicine with cellular therapy and PRP injections. After regaining my health, I focused my education to support the evolving practice of cellular therapy, and regenerative medicine. In 2015 I became the first Physician Assistant to complete the Emergency Medicine Fellowship in Ultrasound, at the University of California Irvine School of Medicine and continued to volunteer teaching medical students and residents the clinical capabilities of ultrasound diagnostics. Since 2014 I have traveled all over southern California working with doctors preforming injections and utilizing ultrasound. My less conventional path continued, and I obtained training in bio-identical hormone replacement methods. I am passionate about bringing a full sense of vitality to our patients and utilized regenerative medicine for chronic pain, neuropathy, joint conditions, sexual health, erectile dysfunction, urinary incontinence and anorgasmia. I find the combination of therapies to improve relationships and quality of life for many of my patients.In November of 2017 West 2 North medical solutions opened its 4th location in San Marcos, California and I finally found my home and team to implement my dream of helping more people with cellular therapy and PRP.I am passionate about treating the whole patient and acknowledge that life stress and hormone imbalances play a key role in the bodys inability to heal and can cause disease.  Our team is committed to assisting our patients, and community, in reaching their goals of healing, and continued health and longevity.

name: Breton Village Pediatrics and Family Medicine
Briant G. Herzog MD
bio: Briant G. Herzog, MD has served the Plano, Frisco, McKinney and Allen areas of North Texas since 1991. Dr. Herzog received his Bachelors of Science, cum laude in 1974, from the University of Utah. He completed his medical degree at the University of Utah College of Medicine. He is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics & Gynecology.He has published several articles, lectured extensively and taken part in numerous scientific presentations.Dr. Herzog is Medical Director of Nu-Age Med Spa, specializing in body contouring, skin tightening and resurfacing. He also offers injectables, skin care and Intraceutical Oxygen Infusion Therapy.

name: Bridge City Family Medical
bio: Teri Bunker, DNP, FNP is Board Certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner. She has over 15 years experience as a Nurse Practitioner. Dr. Bunker graduated from Oregon Health Sciences University in 1998 with a Maters of Science degree and in 2012, graduated with her Doctorate of Nursing Practice (DNP), which is the highest degree possible in clinical nursing.  Dr. Bunker specializes in in gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender health care as well as geriatrics, providing house calls to patients who are not able to travel to the office for a visit.  Dr. Bunker has research the amazing health benefits of BioTEs method of pellet therapy and became a certified BioTE physician to optimize YOUR health and be proactive in disease prevention.

His personal philosophy of medicine is The best way to care for the patient is to care about the patient. Schedule with Dr. Norcom for Botox, dermal filler, laser skin resurfacing, acne treatments, scar revision, mole removal and more. Dr. Norcom is a member of the American Board of Family Practice and the American Academy of Private Physicians.

name: Bristol Plaza Family Medicine
bio: Advanced Medicine of Orange County is a medical practice dedicated to using state of the art technologies to restore the entire body.   Our treatment basis begins with bioidentical hormone balancing, reversing the aging process and establishing a rejuvenated canvas.   With renewed energy and focus, we then turn to the use of stem cells to rebuild and regenerate old tissue.   Skin and joints begin to look and feel years younger.   Throughout all of our treatments we incorporate the use of high dose vitamin IV infusions, nourishing the body with an invigorating boost of energizing hydration. Coupled with individually recommended supplements and Nutraceuticals the result is better sleep, increased endurance, improved mood, decreased anxiety, increased libido, greater mobility and a more youthful overall appearance that lasts. Our treatments truly provide hope for a healthy youthful future.

name: Broussard Family Practice
bio: Juliette (Julie) Broussard RN, MSN FNPC graduated from the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston and has been a certified Family Nurse Practitioner since 2004.  Prior to that, she practiced as a Registered Nurse from 1998 until 2004.  She is experienced in the areas of Labor and Delivery, Internal Medicine, Geriatrics, Family Practice, Hormone Replacement Therapy, Aesthetics and Infectious disease including being a provider to HIV clients.Currently, Julie is the owner of Broussard Family Practice and skinologie in Beaumont Texas. Broussard Family Practice is a unique clinic in that the goal is disease prevention!  We believe that disease in the body is an interruption, cessation or disruption of the mind, body or spirit.    This, in turn, affects the normal flow of the body system as a whole.   Since our goal is disease prevention, we believe this begins with a lifestyle changes and modifications that are individualized to each patient.  We focus on proper nutrition with adequate vitamins, minerals and supplements, a consistent exercise program that keeps the body in motion and attention paid not only to the body but also to the mind and the spirit.  We believe that working towards the body being in total balance will bring a harmonious state within the mind, body and spirit thus making you less susceptible to disease!However, if disease is already present in the body we will focus on management and healing to work towards the goal of a harmonious state within the entire body. Julie is also the owner of skinologie Southeast Texas, which is a medical and laser spa that wants you to not only feel your best but look your best.  Julie is a current member of Texas Nurse Practitioners, American Academy of Nurse Practitioners, and the Age Management Medicine Group.Julie is a certified BioTE Medical bioidentical Hormone replacement provider and she is also certified in advanced facial aesthetics including fillers and neurotoxins. Julie has a passion for disease prevention and will work diligently with her patients to achieve this goal.Julie supports may local community resources and loves to volunteer doing work with underserved adults and children in the community.On her free time she enjoys exercising, relaxing by the pool or at the beach and loves spending time with her family!

name: Buchanan Health Center
bio: As a certified Family Nurse Practitioner and graduate from Eastern Kentucky University, I am passionate about my patients wellbeing and quality of life. In my personal life, I enjoy traveling, spending time with my husband and children, and relaxing poolside with a good book.

name: Burbank Aesthetics Medical Spa
bio: Doddie Wilson is a certified adult nurse practitioner who assists in providing primary health care to Dr. Cynthias patients. Doddie has over twenty years of high-level nursing experience including coordination of in-hospital cardiac clinical trials, serving as the primary nurse in Dr. Cynthias congestive heart clinic, and involvement in community home health nursing.Doddies goal is, to develop a practice that is based on mutual trust, respect and responsibility to the patients and their families.Education:Doddie received her Bachelors in Nursing from California State University, Los Angeles. Doddie is bilingual  fluent in both English and Spanish.

name: Burbank Aesthetics Medical Spa
bio: Dr. Cynthia is a Harvard-trained Los Angeles cardiologist who practices with her heart. She helps replace stress, fear, anxiety in her patients and instills a sense of inner calm and peace by educating and inspiring them to take proactive steps towards health and healing. She has helped thousands of people transform their lives through the ways they think, feel, and act.Intuitively, Dr. Cynthia has known that she would serve this calling since the age of five, after accompanying her physician mother to the medical clinic in their home country of Myanmar, formerly known as Burma. There, she witnessed the pure hands-on art of healing, free from the modern-day challenges of drugs, bureaucracy, and the threat of malpractice.This experience laid dormant deep within her as she navigated her American life, completed her modern medical training at Harvard Medical School, and subsequently began practicing Western medicine. It wasnt until the opening of her own wellness center three years agowhere she guided her patients to experience tremendous improvement in their health and well-being through integrative lifestyle practices that focused on nutrition, fitness, and spiritual or meditative practicesthat those early childhood memories of the art of self-directed healing were reawakened.Rediscovering her life purpose has inserted authenticity to her work and filled her with joy, energy and spirit. She believes the mind-body connection for health is best served through the practice of being centered and present in each moment. A practicing Buddhist, Dr. Cynthia is on a mission to deliver that message, best outlined in her new book, Your Vibrant Heart: Restoring Health, Strength & Spirit from the Bodys Core.As one of the best holistic doctors in Burbank CA, Dr. Cynthia manages two successful cardiology clinics and is the founder of Revitalize-U, a wellness center focused on health, nutrition, weight loss, and detoxification. Beyond her academic and professional achievements, she is most proud of the praises that she receives from her patients who describe her style of practice as caring, compassionate, service, and bio: Eliza Parker, MD is a board-certified physician and the founder and medical director of Cadella Aesthetics and Wellness. A graduate of Harvard University and trained at Cornell Weill Presbyterian Hospital in New York City, Dr. Parker is focused on the whole individual and lifelong wellness, with recognized expertise in non-invasive facial aesthetics, cosmetic injections, laser resurfacing and skin rejuvenation. A master injector for Allergan, makers of Botox Cosmetic, Dr. Parker is a gifted artist, earning the trust of patients by evaluating and understanding your goals, and formulating a plan to achieve realistic, natural-looking results.Dr. Parker places significant emphasis on patient-centered care and strongly believes that a persons unique perspective and self-understanding are twin guides to defining and enhancing his or her own beauty.Outside of work, Dr. Parker enjoys spending time with her family, including her two lovely daughters, whose names are the inspiration for Cadella.

name: Cadella Medspa and Wellness Center
bio: Dr. Chua  is a board-certified neurologist with a special interest in Integrative Medicine. She completed her neurological training at Northwestern University and a fellowship in Integrative Medicine at the University of Arizona, under the supervision of Dr. Andrew Weil. Her focus is on taking care of the whole person, rather than treating a specific symptom, through nutrition, mind-body approaches, and balancing the neurohormonal, immune and digestive systems.  She guides patients in discovering the bodys innate capacity to seek wellness, look for balance, and heal itself, and works as a partner in identifying treatment options that reflect a patients unique needs and life circumstances

name: California Longevity and Vitality Medical Institute
bio: Dr. Rachel Frankel Meek is the Medical Director of The California Longevity and Vitality Medical Institute. She was born in the San Francisco Bay Area. She is a graduate of University of California at San Diego (Muir College, 1981) with a B.S. degree in Biology. Dr. Meek received a Masters Degree in Public Health (M.P.H.) from University of California at Berkeley in 1983. She subsequently graduated from The College of Osteopathic Medicine of the Pacific at Western University of Health Sciences in California in 1987. Dr. Rachel Meek completed her Internship in Family Medicine and then a Residency in Pediatrics at Kaiser Hospital in Oakland, California. From 1991-2004, she was a Partner at Kaiser Permanente Medical Group in Antioch and Walnut Creek, California. Between 2004 and 2008, she has practiced Family Medicine in the Bay Area. In 2009, Dr. Meek completed the full continuing medical education program in Age Management Medicine at Cenegenics Medical Institute in Nevada. She is certified by Cenegenics in Age Management Medicine. Subsequently, Dr. Meek completed a 2-month Preceptorship in Age Management Medicine with Dr. Harvey S. Bartnof at California Longevity and Vitality Medicine Institute in San Francisco. Dr. Rachel Meekjoined the Institute as a Staff Physician in 2009, where she practices Age Management Medicine.

bio: After being involved in large group practices for 20 years, Dr. Baird opened his solo practice in the summer of 2009. Located in the east Carrollton\/west Plano area, he is easily accessible from all areas in the north Dallas to Mid-Cities area. Born in Texas, and raised in several states (but mostly in Texas), he and his family made north Texas their home in 2002. Along with practicing routine Family Medicine, he became involved in aesthetic medicine in 2005. He widened his scope of practice in the fall of 2013 when he became a BioTE Certified Medical Practitioner and began administering bio-identical hormone replacement therapy. He has first hand knowledge of the benefits of receiving BHRT as he actively trains in Tae Kwon Do, currently holding the rank of second degree black belt. He also enjoys running. Dr. Baird and his wife of 31 years, Pam, are active in their church. They also enjoy spending time with their three children.

name: Calobrace Plastic Surgery Center
bio: M. Bradley Calobrace, MD, FACSDr. Calobrace is a graduate of Indiana University Medical School and completed residencies in both General Surgery and Plastic Surgery at the University of Southern California in Los Angeles.   Subsequently, he completed a cosmetic and breast surgery fellowship with Dr. G. Patrick Maxwell and began practice  in Louisville, Kentucky in 1997.   He has dual clinical faculty appointments with the Departments of Plastic Surgery, at the University of Louisville and the University of Kentucky and received teaching honors in 2007, 2011, 2014, 2015 and 2016.Dr. Calobrace is board-certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery and member of  American Society of Plastic Surgeons and American Society for Aesthetic Plastic Surgery. He has a thriving cosmetic surgery practice, performing approximately 1000 major cosmetic procedures each year, including  facial surgery, body contouring, breast surgery, hair transplantation and post-bariatric rejuvenation. Dr. Calobrace is considered one of the leaders in the field of cosmetic breast surgery today in the United States performing over 400  breast surgeries per year.     He has participated in multiple  FDA clinical breast studies  and has been a consultant and speaker for Allergan, Mentor and Sientra.  Dr. Calobrace lectures extensively in the US and Internationally, is an ASAPS visiting professor , performed live surgery at the 2009, 2014 and 2016 at the Atlanta Breast Symposium and has published extensively on the subject of aesthetic breast surgery.

name: Calobrace Plastic Surgery Center
bio: Dr. Chet Mays BioChet Mays, MD, is a plastic surgeon who has been selected by Dr. Bradley Calobrace to become the second associate to join Calobrace & Mizuguchi Plastic Surgery Center in August 2016. A native of Somerset, Dr. Mays holds a shared vision with Drs. Calobrace and Mizuguchi in bringing the most advanced techniques and technology to the region. He is honored to join the practice and have the opportunity to return to his home community to share the expertise and skills he acquired while training in New York.  Dr. Mays is ambitious and dedicated to excellence in patient care.After completing an undergraduate degree at the University Of Louisville (summa cum laude) and a medical degree (cum laude) at the University Of Louisville School Of Medicine, Dr. Mays moved to New York to continue his education and training at the University Of Rochester.  He completed a 6-year integrated plastic surgery residency, training under surgeons from such prestigious institutions as Johns Hopkins, NYU, Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center, MD Anderson Cancer Center, and Manhattan Eye, Ear, and Throat Hospital. Working alongside them gave Dr. Mays a well-rounded experience that prepared him well for the distinct challenges and rewards of plastic surgery. The unique curriculum of an integrated plastic surgery residency also afforded Dr. Mays the rare opportunity to begin his training as a plastic surgeon from the very first day. Dr. Mays performs a range of procedures, with a focus on facial aesthetics surgery, breast reconstruction, breast enhancement and body contouring. Dr. Mays is a compassionate physician who strives to provide the best result for his patients, and he understands that the best result comes from collaboration between patient and surgeon. Every patient has a personal vision, and Dr. Mays works to bring that vision to life. Blending traits of the artist and the innovator, Dr. Mays looks to provide his patients with the improvements they are seeking, while offering his own perspective on each patient's aesthetic ideal. With every patient, he strives to not just meet the goals the patient comes in with, but also to improve that patient's self-image and confidence.Professional Memberships American Society of Plastic Surgeons, candidate for membershipThe American Society of Aesthetic Plastic Surgery, Inc. Candidate for membershipAlpha Omega Alpha Medical Honor SocietyGold Humanism Medical Honor SocietyKentucky Medical Association Greater Louisville Medical Society

name: Calobrace Plastic Surgery Center
bio: Bethany Shively, APRN, DNP, FNP-CBethany Shively is a Louisville native and Nurse Practitioner at Calobrace and Mizuguchi Plastic Surgery Center in Louisville, KY.  She began her career in 2011, serving as a medical-surgical and operating room nurse before joining the practice in 2013.  She completed two years as an operating room nurse before transitioning to the role of Nurse Practitioner.Bethany completed her Doctor of Nursing practice and Master of Science in Nursing with a 4.0 from the Medical University of South Carolina, after obtaining her Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Western Kentucky University.  She is certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner with the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.   She is passionate about providing holistic care and prevention of disease through bioidentical hormone replacement.

name: Camden OB\/GYN
bio: Eva T. di Lorenzo, M.D. of Camden OBGYN in Saint Marys, Georgia has been practicing medicine for over twenty years, and her commitment to her patients is to always be honest, caring, and professional. She offers a wide range of services, skills, and knowledge, while being devoted to the care of women throughout their everyday lives.One of Doctor di Lorenzos specialties is Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy, and during the last fifteen years, she has treated over 3,000 patients with custom tailored Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapies.Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy helps to replenish and balance hormones in the body with hormones that are identical to those produced naturally. Customized Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy plans are available, and Doctor di Lorenzo of Camden OBGYN in Saint Marys, Georgia has helped many patients to regain balance and vitality with her expert treatment plans.Thousands of women that come into Doctor di Lorenzos practice are suffering from the effects of reduced hormone levels that accompany perimenopause and menopause. Many women experiencing hormone decline often have symptoms that include fatigue, low libido, weight gain, thinning hair, anxiety, depression, thinning bones, or vaginal dryness. Correcting imbalances can help women to regain their quality of life and sense of wellbeing. Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy offers women a natural solution to hormone decline. Bioidentical hormones are identical in chemical structure and function to the hormones produced in the human body, which can allow them to be easily used with few to no side effects.While women most commonly experience symptoms of hormone decline, men also can experience changes with dropping hormone levels. Some of the symptoms that men can encounter include muscle atrophy, fatigue, hair loss, poor workout performances, anxiety, erectile dysfunction, and low libido. Replenishing deficient hormones can allow men to recover from imbalances and improve overall levels of health and wellness.

name: Capital Internal Medicine, Inc.- CIMA

name: Care Access Adult Health Clinic
bio: Bukola Adeniran is a dedicated and engaged adult nurse practitioner serving the community of Babylon, NY. Ms. Adeniran attended Stony Brook University, where she received her masters in adult health nursing, and earned her bachelors degree at the same institution.Ms. Adeniran is a member of the Long Island Chapter of the Nurse Practitioner Association. Patients see her for a variety of reasons, including hormone replacement therapy.Ms. Adeniran has earned the privilege of being enrolled in several honor societies including the Theta Tau International Honor Society of Nursing and the National Scholars Honor Society. She is sensitive to the uniqueness of each patient's situation and adapts her consultations and treatment options appropriately to accommodate individual needs and concerns.

name: Care United Medical Centers of America LLP
bio: Shilpi Mittal, MDDr. Mittal received her medical degree from Jawaharlal Nehru Medical College in India. She completed a Medical Internship at St. John Medical Center in Detroit, Michigan, and her residency in Family Practice at the Goppert Family Practice, Baptist-Lutheran Medical Center in Kansas City, Missouri. Dr. Mittal is Board Certified in Family Practice and is a member of the American Academy of Family Medicine, the American Medical Association, and Southwest Clinical Society of Family Physicians. She has worked for a large outpatient practice in Missouri where she also held a faculty position teaching new physicians. Dr. Mittal was born in India and immigrated to the United States. Although she lived in Missouri she got to Texas as soon as she could! She is married with 2 wonderful sons and enjoys reading, traveling and gardening.

name: Care United Medical Centers of America LLP
bio: Sarah Lembke, PA-CSara obtained a Bachelor of Science with emphasis in Nursing from Texas Woman's University in 2005. Upon graduation, she worked as a Registered Nurse in the Emergency Department at Parkland Hospital. In 2011, she graduated from University of North Texas Health Science Center with a Master's in Physician Assistant Studies. After graduation, she moved to Oregon to start her career as a Physician Assistant. Mrs. Lembke continued to work in the Emergency Department at Mercy Medical Center in Roseburg, Oregon. Soon, she relocated back to Texas and continued to practice medicine at Parkland Hospital and Baylor Hospital.Sara joined Care United Medical Center in 2014. She has enjoyed working at CUMC and has great respect for the staff and fellow providers.Outside of work, she is married with two sons. As a family they enjoy going to the park, the zoo, and local festivals.

Dr. Alvarez Romagosa graduated from Other with his medical degree in 1986. He is affiliated with numerous hospitals in the Hato Rey area including Hospital Espanol Auxilio Mutuo De Puerto Rico, Inc and more. Dr. Alvarez Romagosa is accepting new patients at his medical office and practice location is: Auxilio Medical Bldg, Hato Rey, PR. name: Caring for Women & Men Wellness Center
bio: Stanford University trained in obstetrics and gynecology, Dr. Michael Goodman began his practice in rural Mendocino County, California in 1972, where he was one of the early pioneers of Family-Centered Maternity Care. In the early 1980s his interest turned to the then-new area of operative laparoscopy.  Credentialed as an Advanced Operative Laparoscopist, Dr.Goodman has lectured extensively and contributed to the peer-reviewed literature on the subject.Beginning in the 1990s, Dr. Goodman developed an interest in integrative, age-management, menopausal and sexual medicine, as well as female genital plastic and cosmetic surgery.  He is certified as a Clinical Bone Densiometrist and Menopause Practitioner, and was recently designated a Fellow of the International Society for the Study of Womens Sexual Health.  His present practice in Davis, California specializes in difficult gynecologic and andrology issues, peri-menopausal medicine, health and vitality enhancement, male and female sexuality issues, bone densiometry, pelvic ultrasound and vulvovaginal aesthetic surgery.   He has been an invited guest at numerous seminars on these subjects, and is a peer reviewer for the Journal of Sexual Medicine, Journal of Obstetrics and Gynecology Research, British Journal of Ob-Gyn, World Journal of Urology, Journal of Minimally Invasive Surgery (Emeritus), among others.  He is published in the area of Menopausal Medicine, and has several citations in peer-reviewed scientific literature on the subject of female genital plastic\/cosmetic surgery.  He is the Editor and major chapter contributor of the new medical textbook currently in production from Wiley-Blackwell, Female Genital Plastic\/Aesthetic Surgery. Dr. Goodman has almost 20 years experience with Bioidentical Hormnes in both men and women, and is the author of a peer-reviewed medical journal article on the subject (Oral vs Transdermal Hormone Therapy) and specializes in cream, patch, and injectable pellet therapy.Dr. Goodman is the proud father of four children, ages 16 to 41, and enjoys exercising, tennis, gardening, music and writing.  He is the author of two popular books on menopause and one on genital plastics, all available from Amazon, his office, and local outlets.

name: Caring for Women & Men Wellness Center
Carol Wood DO
bio: Dr. Carol Wood graduated medical school from University of North Texas Health Science Center in Fort Worth, TX. She then completed a family medicine residency at the UT Southwestern Health Science Center in Dallas that included training at St. Paul University Hospital, Parkland Hospital and Children's Medical Center. She is board certified in Family Medicine. Prior to attending medical school, Dr. Wood was a registered dental hygienist who practiced many years at an Arlington dental office. She obtained her dental hygiene training from University of Michigan.Osteopathic medicine's emphasis on prevention, the interaction of all the bodies' systems and the treatment of the total body in order to achieve and maintain health attracted Dr. Wood to pursue her medical education at an osteopathic medical school (D0). From there, she chose a residency at an allopathic (MD) health care system. This allowed her to draw knowledge from both disciplines of medicine and also to take advantage of the vast patient base in the UT Southwestern system where she was exposed to a wide range of pathology and health care needs. She received this residency training at the busiest county hospital and children's hospital in North Texas. She remains steadfast in her belief in all the osteopathic tenets and she utilizes this philosophy in treating her patients. She practices the osteopathic manipulative treatments (OMT) that she learned in medical school to promote the health and healing of her patients. She addresses the patient's physical, mental and spiritual well-being since each contributes to an individual's overall health. She welcomes patients of all ages, from infancy to the elderly.Dr. Carol Wood has developed an interest in bio-identical hormone therapy in recent years. After diagnosing hormone dysfunction, she prescribes replacement hormones that closely resemble those naturally produced in our bodies and follows the levels of these hormones to ensure that each patient's levels are appropriate. Dr. Wood is excited to now offer hormone pelleting utilizing bio-identical hormone pellets.Dr. Wood and her husband Barry have 2 grown children, Scott and Kristy. The Woods attend First Baptist Church in Midlothian where they live. Dr. Wood's interests include Bible studies, hiking, camping and reading.

name: Carolyn Quist DO
bio: Dr. Quist completed medical school and residency at Texas College of Osteopathic Medicine, University of North Texas Health Science Center. She specializes in endometriosis and pelvic pain, minimally invasive surgery, urinary incontinence, menopause and hormone therapy, fibroids, abnormal pap smears, and polycystic ovarian syndrome. Dr. Quist has been practicing medicine in Fort Worth, Texas since 1991. She was originally on faculty at the Texas College of Osteopathic Medicine from 1991 to 1998. She went into private practice in 1991. She just opened Revitalize Wellness Center, PA to offer SottoPelle natural hormone pellet therapy. She performs gynecological surgery with the DaVinci Robot at Harris Hospital, Baylor All Saints Medical Center, and Baylor Surgical Hospital in Fort Worth. She performs minimally invasive surgery for urinary incontinence and offers the Intone Medical device therapy for those patients with milder forms of bladder problems. She offers the Zerona laser body sculpting and Botox treatments.  She is Vice Chair of the American Osteopathic Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  She is a member of multiple organizations and is passionate about women's healthcare.

name: Carter Hays Martin & Wells
bio: Dr. Carter attended The University of Texas in Austin where he received his undergraduate degree in biology and psychology. He graduated from the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston with his MD and a masters degree in renal and cardiovascular physiology. Well into a residency in Internal Medicine, his first child was born. This life changing experience prompted him to start residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology the following year. He is board certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology and a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. For the last decade he has been voted by his peers as one of the best doctors in Dallas, in Texas, and in the United States. As a portion of his patient population has matured, he has become increasingly more involved in general women's wellness care and in the developing field of menopausal medicine involving the careful administration of bio identical hormones.
