She completed her residency in Ob\/Gyn at Baylor University Medical Center where she received the Joseph Warren award for leadership and balance.  She has been in private practice in obstetrics and gynecology for fifteen years now at Baylor in Dallas.  She is married with two sons and enjoys hunting, running, and jewelry making. Visit Dr. Hays' website at http:\/\/tracyhays.md.com\/

bio: Dr. Lauren Dew attended Michigan State University in East Lansing, Michigan where she received her undergraduate degree in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology and graduated with honors.  Dr. Dew then went on to study medicine at Wayne State University School of Medicine in Detroit, Michigan.  She moved to Dallas to complete her residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Baylor University Medical Center.  During her residency she received the Resident Teaching Award and Academic Achievement Award, and was selected to be Chief Resident during her fourth year.  Dr. Dews love for Texas grew and she now lives and practices full-time in downtown Dallas.  She has a passion for maintaining the health of women throughout adult life and providing individualized preventative health care measures.  She offers a full range of services in the field of obstetrics and gynecology from the initial exam, to pregnancy and childbirth, through the menopausal transition and mature life. Visit Dr. Dew's website at http:\/\/drlaurendew.com\/

bio: Dr. Barfield is a Board Certified physician in the specialty of obstetrics and gynecology.  He is a Fellow of both The American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology, and The American College of Surgeons.  Dr. Barfield completed his residency in obstetrics and gynecology at Emory University.  He is a 2000 graduate of NOVA Southeastern University School of Osteopathic Medicine, and completed his internship at the Childrens and Womens Hospital of the University of South Alabama.  He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in microbiology from the University of Georgia.  His cosmetic surgery training was with the International Society of Cosmetogynecology.

bio: Dr. Staci Kenner-Fuller is a Board Certified OB\/GYN.  She has been practicing at Cartersville OB\/Gyn since 2012.  She performed her ob\/gyn residency at Methodist Dallas Medical Center, where she served as chief resident from 2011-2012. Dr. Kenner received her Medical Doctorate from Case Western Reserve University School of Medicine in Cleveland, Ohio, and holds a Bachelor of Arts in Psychology Pre-Medicine from Spelman College in Atlanta. She is a Fellow of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (FACOG), she also is a member of the American Medical Association and the American Association of Gynecologic Laparoscopists.

bio: Dr. Ribot is a Board Certified physician in the specialties of obstetrics and gynecology, and advanced operative laparoscopy, and the managing partner of Cartersville Ob\/Gyn Associates.  A 1981 graduate of Dartmouth College, Dr. Ribot received his medical degree from the University of  Miami School of Medicine in 1986.  He completed his residency in obstetrics and gynecology at Emory University Affiliated Hospitals in 1990, receiving its first-ever annual Best Laparoscopic Surgical Resident Award.  Since joining Cartersville Ob\/Gyn in 1990, he has introduced to the northwest Georgia region numerous advancements in the speciality.  Dr. Ribot also is the co-founder, and medical director of the practices onsite outpatient surgical facility, the Georgia Advanced Surgery Center for Women.He has many years of experience performing bioidentical hormone pellet therapy.

name: Castle Rock Family Physicians
bio: Dr. Kasunic is a graduate of Denison University (BS Chemistry), Case Western Reserve University (MS Chemistry), and The Ohio University College of Osteopathic Medicine. He is Board Certified in Family Medicine and is a Fellow of the American College of Osteopathic Family Physicians. He has practiced medicine in our community since 1987. Dr. Kasunic is the founder and Director of the Strong Heart Institute (located within Castle Rock Family Physicians); using cutting edge technology to help patients avoid heart attacks and stroke. He speaks nationally on a variety of medical topics and continues in his role as a clinical professor training medical students, interns, and resident physicians. He lives in Castle Rock with his wife, Wanda, and their three children where he enjoys coaching, reading, shooting and landscaping. He was voted \Best of the Best\" Physician in Castle Rock by readers of Colorado Community Newspapers. Dr. Kasunic founded Castle Rock Family Physicians in 1994. "

name: Castle Rock Family Physicians
bio: Kristine is a graduate of the University of Colorado Denver Anschutz Medical Campus, where she was a member of the Child Health Associate\/Physician Assistant program. During her time with the program she acted as President of the CHA\/PA Student Association and now is a member of the Colorado Academy of Physician Assistants and American Academy of Physician Assistants. As a provider, Kristine enjoys all aspects of family medicine with an emphasis on pediatric, adolescent, and womens health.  After joining the practice in 2011, she and her husband, Jake, moved to Castle Rock.  She enjoys cooking, soccer, reading novels, and collecting piggy banks.

name: Castle Rock Family Physicians
bio: Dr. Boekes graduated from the University of North Dakota School of Medicine in 1995 and completed his Family Medicine Residency at St. Mary-Corwin Hospital in Pueblo, Colorado. Dr. Boekes enjoys the multiple aspects of Family Medicine and the prevention of disease. He continues to teach medical students in his role as clinical professor with the University of Colorado School of Medicine. He joined Castle Rock Family Physicians in 1998. He lives in Larkspur with his wife Margie and their 3 daughters. He is a pilot for single-engine aircraft and enjoys woodworking as a hobby.

name: Castle Rock Medical Weight Loss Center
bio: I was born and raised in Anchorage, Ak. I moved to Colorado in 2001. I earned my undergraduate degree at University of Alaska Anchorage and my Masters Degree at University of Colorado Denver. I been working as a womens health nurse practitioner for the last 7 years. During this time I have really enjoyed caring for women at all stages of their lives and health. Along the way I have gone through a weight loss journey that has made me very passionate about helping others be successful in regaining their health and quality of life. I am so happy to have the opportunity to help people achieve their weight loss goals and to optimize their quality of life through hormone balance. I enjoy kickboxing, running obstacle races, leading fit camps, as well as camping, traveling and enjoying time with my husband, six children and my grandson.

bio: Clay Caldwell, FNP is originally from Tyler. Attended University of Texas. He has been a nurse practitioner at Cedar Creek Lake for 17 years.Married high school sweetheart, Amy. They have two boys and one granddaughter.He enjoys fishing and boating.

name: Cedar Creek Clinic
bio: Jennifer Lunceford, PA-C has been a physician assistant for 18 years. She graduated from the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston and has practiced in the East Texas area in family practice, internal medicine, pediatrics, women's health, and urgent care. She resides in her hometown of Athens, Texas with her husband and 7 year old twin daughters and has older twin girls in college.

name: Cedar Male Medical
bio: Dr. Brenden Witte is a Naturopathic Medical Doctor focusing in mens health.  He specializes in bioidentical testosterone replacement therapy and sexual\/reproductive health.  By combining effective scientific medical techniques and naturopathic, common sense approaches to lifestyle, Dr. Witte has become a BioTE certified physician in pellet therapy.  He provides BioTEs method which supports optimal health and vitality, addressing and treating both the symptoms and the root cause of low energy, weight gain, poor mental acuity and erectile dysfunction in men.

name: Celebrate Primary Care
bio: Lisa Magary, dual certified in family practice and pediatrics as a nurse practitioner, is passionate about helping patients maximize their health. After a thorough education including a Doctorate of Nursing Practice from the University of Florida in 2010, a Masters in Nursing in 2006, and years of working in a healthcare system that revolves around insurance starting with home health care as a graduate from the respiratory care program at Santa Fe Community College in 1995, Lisa knew there had to be a better way. Her years in a primary care where the expectation was to see each patient for less than 15 minutes pushed Lisa to seek out a new model for health care, a model that put the patient at the center not billing codes and government requirements. Opening a practice was a dream. But that dream was always at the mercy of rapidly changing insurance laws and heavy burdens placed on health care providers by insurance companies. Late in 2014, after reading an article about direct primary care everything changed as new options came into focus. Options like earning a living and getting to spend a lot of time with patients while making a lasting positive impact on their health. The direct primary care model allows just that.

name: Celebrate Primary Care
bio: Della Tuten is founding partner and health care provider with Celebrate Primary Care of Gainesville. Della and Lisa attended grad school together and always knew that they wanted to open a practice together some day. Della grew up in Gainesville and then graduated from the University Of Florida in 1999, 2005 and 2006. She has been practicing as a Nationally Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner in North Central Florida since finishing her education at UF. She is focused on preventive medicine and holistic care. She works diligently to educate her patients and help each individual achieve optimum health. Della is passionate about having a positive impact and making a difference in the lives of each her patients. Her goal is to improve the delivery of primary care to the Gainesville community and beyond. It has been my dream to provide care outside the factory medicine model, that is why I am excited to provide care to you in such a personalized way through the direct primary care model. I have been married to my husband Travis since 2002 and we have two beautiful children, Eli (9) and Emma (6). We enjoying traveling every chance we get. I am a diehard Gator and love all college sports. Go Gators!

name: Centennial OB\/GYN PA
bio: Dr. Alisa Ward is a native Texan, born in Nacogdoches. She received a BS in Biomedical Science at Texas A&M University, then went on to medical school at Texas Tech University School of Medicine in Lubbock. She completed her residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Texas Tech University in Amarillo. She practiced in Richardson, TX upon completion of residency in 2001. She gave birth to a baby boy (Jackson) in March, 2011, then moved her practice to Frisco, TX where she joined Drs. Leslie Welborne and Melissa Bailey of Centennial Ob\/Gyn. She loves traveling and cycling when she is away from work, but enjoys spending time with her patients and taking care of all women from puberty to menopause.

name: Centennial OB\/GYN PA
bio: Dr. Melissa Bailey completed her obstetrics and gynecology residency at Georgia Baptist Medical Center, in Atlanta, Georgia, where she served as chief resident in her fourth year. Upon graduation, she received the J. Marion Sims award for excellence in gynecologic surgery. Dr. Bailey was awarded her doctor of medicine degree from the University Of Texas Medical Branch at Galveston, Texas. As a medical student, she performed research on life developmental delays suffered by low birth weight and premature birth.Dr. Bailey completed her undergraduate studies at the University Of Texas, at Austin, with a Bachelor Of Arts Degree in Biology and a minor in Chemistry. She is a graduate of Lewisville High School and is a current resident of Frisco, Texas with her husband, John, also a physician, and her two children, Wesley and Sarah. After having a private practice in Atlanta, Georgia for five years, Dr. Bailey recently moved back to the North Dallas area. She and her husband enjoy being close to family and friends and raising their children in our fabulous community. Joining her best friend, Dr. Leslie Welborne, in practice, has been a life long dream. Together, they look forward to providing compassionate, comprehensive, and state of the art medical care to the women in this community.

name: Centennial OB\/GYN PA
bio: Dr. Leslie S. Welborne, who is originally from the metroplex, was happy to return to the North Dallas area, after completing her residency at the University of Missouri in Kansas City. She was awarded her doctor of medicine degree at the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston, Texas, where she met her best friend and partner, Dr Melissa Bailey. Dr. Welborne received her undergraduate degree in chemical engineering, from the University of Arizona, after graduating from J. J. Pearce High School, in Richardson, Texas.Although Dr. Welborne has been practicing in the Collin County area since 1999, she was so excited to have the opportunity to become a member of the Frisco healthcare community, in 2004. She lives in Frisco with her husband, Patrick and sons Brittan and Kieran. She is happy to be serving this great community. Her goal is to promote a friendly and caring environment, while offering the women of our community a full range of obstetrics and gynecology.

name: Center for Cosmetic Enhancement
bio: Dr. Farr holds a Bachelors of Science in Nursing from Madonna University, a Master of Science of Nursing from the University of Cincinnati and a Doctorate of Nursing Practice from Oakland University. Dr. Farr is a Board Certified Nurse Practitioner in Family Practice (FNP) and he specializes in aesthetic medicine and internal medicine\/adult health. Dr. Farr does practice as a FNP in internal medicine and in the urgent care setting in the Metro Detroit area.  Dr Farr has as extensive background teaching in nursing education, both on ground and online.  He currently serves as an Assistant Professor of nursing at Eastern Michigan University.  Dr. Farr is also a BioTE certified provider and is excited to offer BioTE pellet therapy in his practice.  He loves that this therapy increases vigor for life and well being for his patients with a proactive approach to disease prevention.  Dr. Farr loves working with his patients to help them maintain their health and wellbeing using a patient centered approach.

We enjoyed our time, but have desired to return to our California \roots\" and our extended family. In my free time

bio: Dr. Thomas W. Clark is a four time best-selling author and one of the most experienced and sought after bariatric surgeons in the United States.  He has performed nearly 4,000 weight loss procedures and is one of the elite few Board Certified surgeons who is also board certified in bariatric medicine.  Dr. Clark is also fully trained and certified as a BioTE specialist for bio-identical hormone replacement therapy.  He is passionate about helping people add life to their years through effective weight loss, balanced hormones and wellness programs\/services that help to ensure long term success.  Dr. Clark not only helps people look and feel their best, he personally puts into practice what he teaches every day as well. Dr. Clark is the founder of the Center for Weight Loss Success and the Medical Director for the Center for Hormone Health and Wellness, both located in Newport News, VA.  Dr. Clark not only provides surgical tools for weight loss success, he has created effective programs that help his patients finally understand how to be successful for life.  For weight loss surgery patients, this includes a 12 month step-by-step educational program called Weight Management University for Weight Loss Surgery.  Additional programs include My Weight Loss Academy and Losing Weight USA (www.LosingWeightUSA.com)   Dr. Clark and his passionate staff of professionals also offers free weekly podcasts, tips sheets, recipes and a convenient smart phone app for clients to track their success.  His comprehensive surgical and non-surgical programs attract patients from in and around the United States.Dr. Clark speaks frequently for national organizations such as the American Society of Bariatric Physicians and contributes regularly to publications in and around Virginia.  For more information about Dr. Clark, visit www.cfwls.com. You can also follow him on Twitter at www.twitter.com\/docweightloss , Facebook at www.facebook.com\/weightlossdrclark, You Tube at www.youtube.com\/docweightloss, follow his blog at www.cfwls.com\/blog and his podcasts at www.cfwls\/com\/podcasts Dr. Thomas W. Clark graduated from Davidson College and The Bowman Gray School of Medicine in North Carolina and currently resides in Virginia with his wife and four children.

name: Center for Wellness and Pain Care of Las Vegas
bio: R. NEVILLE CAMPBELL, M.D. \/ M.B.A. Dr. Neville Campbell is a board certified anesthesiologist and a board certified interventional pain management physician. He completed both his medical training and his anesthesiology residency in New York City at renowned Mount Sinai School of Medicine and State University of New York at Downstate respectively. After completion of residency training, he returned to Mount Sinai Hospital to complete an ACGME-accredited pain medicine fellowship program, in the department of Anesthesiology. Additionally, Dr. Campbell holds a Masters in Business Administration degree with a concentration in Health Care Management. Dr. Campbell has received numerous appraisals and letters of commendation from his patients for his ability to effectively listen while providing comprehensive care using a multi-disciplinary approach. An approach aimed at treating the whole person mind, body and spirit. With his empathetic demeanor and outstanding skill set in the clinical practice of pain management, Dr. Campbell considers himself the go to guy for the simplest to the most complex pain conditions. Employing multimodal strategies, minimally invasive therapies and spinal implantable devices, he aims to improve his patients functionality and quality of life. Dr. Campbell is actively involved in community service both locally and internationally. He currently serves on the board of directors of a non-profit organization that lead mission trips to under privileged countries. Dr. Campbell is married with three children. His hobbies include reading, meeting people, and global volunteerism.

name: Center for Wellness and Pain Care of Las Vegas
bio: Dr. Ruben G. Alexander, M.D. is a board-certified anesthesiologist and interventional pain management physician. Dr. Alexander graduated as the valedictorian from Morehouse College with a perfect 4.0 GPA. After college, he completed his medical school training and internship in general surgery at the University of Pennsylvania School of Medicine in Philadelphia, PA. Dr. Alexander subsequently went to Brooklyn, New York to complete his residency in anesthesiology at the State University of New York at Downstate, where he served as chief resident. After completion of residency training, he completed an ACGME-accredited fellowship in pain management at Emory University in Atlanta, GA. Dr. Alexander brings his expertise in medical management and interventional skills in order to help patients dealing with acute and chronic pain states. He is revered by both peers and patients alike. He has earned awards and accolades such as induction into honor societies (Phi Beta Kappa and Alpha Omega Alpha) and being named a Gamble 21st Century Scholar and FOCUS Research Fellow. Additionally, Dr. Alexander serves not only his local community but also serves abroad in medically underserved communities, sharing his knowledge and compassion to those in need. Dr. Alexander hails from Atlanta, GA and lives with his wife and daughter. In his free time, he enjoys travel, photography, golf and movies.

name: Center for Wellness MD
bio: Dr. Russell, MD has been practicing medicine in the Denver are since 1987. She has extensive experience in the management of hormone imbalances including menopause, andropause and polycystic ovarian syndrome using bio-identical hormone therapy and pellets. A graduate of Duke University School of Medicine, Dr. Russell completed her residency training at the University of California, San Francisco. She is board certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology.

name: Center for Wellness MD
bio: Ruth Ann Zisser, WHNP-BC, MS has been a reproductive health nurse practitioner since 1979. She trained at the University of Oklahoma and the University of Colorado, becoming certified in 1980. Hormone balance from puberty throughout a womans lifetime has been a special interest throughout her career. She is a member of the Association of Reproductive Health Professionals, American Menopause Society, American Association of Nurse Practitioners and the Association of Womens Health, Obstetric and Neonatal Nurses. She is a peer reviewer for multiple professional journals. From a personal perspective, Ruth Ann has lived and worked in each of the hormonal stages in a womans lifetime and has a compassionate understanding of what hormonal balance truly means to health and wellness.

name: Center for Wellness MD
bio: Dr. Leslie Scariano has had the privilege of practicing Obstetrics and Gynecology since 1995.  She moved to Colorado from Illinois after being an owner of a successful multi-specialty benchmark practice for 10 years.  She has enjoyed practicing at the Center for Womens Health since 2006 and lends her considerable experience in improving the lives of those who have entrusted their care to her.  She received her medical school degree from Creighton University in Omaha, Nebraska in 1991 and completed her OB\/GYN residency at St. Johns Mercy Medical Center in St. Louis, Missouri.  She grew up in Montana and met her husband, Lawrence Scariano MD, a local internal medicine physician during residency.   Dr. Scariano has been board certified with the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology since 1997. Dr. Scariano strives to provide cutting-edge, timely and comprehensive care in a warm, welcoming environment.   She has a special interest in adolescent gynecology, has two teenage children and enjoys giving talks to local middle schools concerning special health topics unique to this age group.   She loves and feels privileged to deliver babies and enjoys seeing them grow-up through the lives she touches.  Dr. Scariano strives to deliver patients vaginally and prides herself on a low Cesarean section rate.   She enjoys performing both hospital and in-office procedures and has been performing the Essure sterilization procedure since its approval over ten years ago.Dr. Scariano enjoys scrapbooking, gardening, skiing, getting together with friends, and watching her children play soccer and basketball.

name: Central Texas Wellness & Rejuvenation Center
bio: Dr. Irwin is an accredited associate of the Laser Vaginal Rejuvenation Institute of America, and is the first gynecologist to offer LVR\/DLV in the Central Texas region.  Dr Irwin is one of the few doctors in the United States with advanced training in aesthetic reconstructive vaginal surgery.The Laser Vaginal Rejuvenation Center of Central Texas was founded and directed by Teresa Irwin, MD, FACOG.  Dr. Irwin is a board certified obstetrician and gynecologist.

name: Central Texas Wellness & Rejuvenation Center
bio: I am so excited to be a part of the CTWRC team.  Please allow me to introduce myself.  My name is Donata Elber, but most folks just call me Donna.  I have been a registered nurse for many years now.  My love in nursing led me to specialize in womens health.  Reminding women to take care of themselves is my passion.  Over the years I have gained great knowledge and as a woman I have been able to put much of this knowledge into practice on myself, being both student and patient.  You see I am also an educator.  I believe that knowledge is power, but it must be shared.  My latest endeavor is getting my masters degree.  We should never stop learning.  As I reflect on the path I have been on and now the path that lies ahead, I hope to share all that I can with you.  As both a working wife and mother I know first hand that we as women often times put ourselves last.  It has become my mission in life to offer the very best medical care, in particular when it comes to womens overall health and well-being.  I look forward to enriching your life as you travel your own path to a happier, healthier you.

Chad Curlee DO
bio: Dr. Curlee was born and raised in Fort Worth, Texas. He graduated from Lake Country Christian high school and then went on to Dallas Baptist University where he graduated with honors with a degree in Biology. Dr. Curlee then went onto Hanover, New Hampshire where he graduated from Dartmouth College with a Master of Public Health degree in 2003. After this he returned to Fort Worth to pursue his medical education. Dr. Curlee graduated from University of North Texas Health Science Center in 2007. He then completed a residency in Family Medicine, graduating from John Peter Smith Hospital in 2010. Dr. Curlees clinical interests include office based procedures, preventative medicine, men and womens health, pediatrics and geriatrics. He is married to Laura Curlee, who is also a physician, and he has two beautiful daughters. Dr. Curlee is truly excited to be working and living in the Fort Worth area. He looks forward to helping the people of his hometown become healthier and happier.

name: Chambers Clinic
bio: Dr. Keith Chambers is medical director of Chambers Clinic and has a Doctorate in Naturopathic Medicine from Southwest College of Naturopathic Medicine as well as an MBA from Webster University. He earned his undergraduate degree from College of the Ozarks in biology and chemistry.Dr. Chambers is an accomplished speaker on the subject of natural medicine and a member of the American Association of Naturopathic Physicians. He sits on the Advisory Board of World Nutrition, Inc. and is active with the Board of Integrative Medicine at Banner Health.A direct proponent in the writing of the Electronic Signature Bill, Dr. Chambers has worked with U.S. Congress on illustrating the benefits of incorporating electronic signatures into medical records and how they could work within the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) program.Dr. Chambers has been involved in marital arts for nearly 35 years and received his 4th Degree Black in 2014. In addition to practicing marital art, he enjoys training and teaching Koei-Kan Karate-Do, traveling, snow skiing and fishing.

Charles P. Virden
bio: Aleah is a life-long Nevada resident and graduated with honors from the University of Nevada, Reno, with a BS in Neuroscience. Aleah gained valuable experience working as an emergency medical assistant and scribe at the Saint Marys Emergency Department and as a medical assistant for Sierra Nevada Nephrology. She then continued her education at Stanford University School of Medicine where she graduated top of her class and received her Physician Assistant license and a Masters in Medical Science. Aleah is our new PA joining our Aestheticare team and will be working with Dr. Charles Virden in our new clinic called The Skin Clinic. This clinic is a rapidly accessible, high quality, cash pay skin clinic designed to address common concerns such as acne treatment plans, acne scarring, benign lesion removal, simple skin cancer treatment, mole removal, and general skin care. Next time you are in our office, make sure to say hello to Aleah! She will always greet you with a warm, welcoming smile.

name: Charles P. Virden
bio: Dr. Virden is one of the elite plastic surgeons in Reno, Nevada, and Tahoe\/Truckee to be board-certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery, which means that he has extensive training in all aspects of plastic and reconstructive surgery. He has a strong interest in aesthetic surgery of the face, including the latest techniques in laser surgery and endoscopic (minimal incision) surgery.Dr. Virden was raised in Southern California and attended Occidental College for his premedical studies. In 1987, he graduated from the University of Southern California with a medical degree. Dr. Virden completed his general studies internship and residency at the University of California, San Diego, in 1993.

name: Charles P. Virden
bio: Darian Thorp is a board-certified Nurse Practitioner, who has more than 15 years of experience working in medicine with various areas of interest and providing the highest-level of care. Darian is passionate in providing attentive care for patients\/clients undergoing elective cosmetic procedures, including: pan-facial injectable rejuvenation, laser treatment, and other minimal invasive treatments. She displays exceptional attention to detail and is vehement about offering the optimal level of innovative, evidenced-based techniques, resulting in the most natural and aesthetically pleasing outcome. In addition, Darian provides a patient-centered, gentle, and caring environment that is remarkable and soothing.Darian came from Northern California to attend college at University of Nevada in Reno. She eventually resided in Reno with a degree in pre-medicine and her BSN. She became a Family Nurse Practitioner, shortly thereafter. Darian has vast training in cancer detection, disease recognition, hormone replacement therapy, birth control, and other womens and mens reproductive health issues. Darian has been an accomplished Nurse Practitioner providing an exemplary of care in several areas of medicine.Several years ago, Darian recognized her original area of enthusiasm was to serve patients in the anti-aging and facial rejuvenation area of the medical profession, and has dedicated herself in learning the most up-to-date and innovative techniques in minimally invasive aesthetic procedures, and received board certification as a Medical Aesthetic Provider (MEP-C). She has since become a valued member of the Reno Community providing these services.In Darians spare time she enjoys taking in Reno & Tahoes many experiences with her wonderful husband and 2 lovely children. She is an avid snowboarder (past national competitor) and takes any chance to be outside and active. Darian and her family also enjoy traveling and are often visiting family and friends in Europe.

name: Charles Safely MD
bio: Dr. Safely M.D., a native to Texas, opened his practice in 1996 with the commitment to providing his patients with compassion and the highest quality of women's healthcare.As a licensed and board certified M.D. in the state of Texas, he carries degrees from multiple Texas Scholar Universities. Trained in obstetrics and gynecology at John Peter Smith Hospital in Fort Worth, Dr. Safely cares for what matters most. Happily married for more than 25 years and with two children is how he spends his time. Dr. Charles Safely is a member of the Better Business Bureau, ACOG, and AAGL.We provide a complete range of Ob\/Gyn services and in-office procedures. Dr. Safely also performs at the cutting edge of medical technology using the Da Vinci robotic surgery; specializing in Pelvic Prolaspe, Endometriosis, Heavy Menstruation and Pelvic Pain.

name: Charleston Women's Wellness Center
bio: Dr. Paula Orr is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics & Gynecology, and a Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians & Gynecologists, and a member of the American Medical Association. She is a current Board of Trustees member of MUSC where she was appointed by the former Governor of SC. She has been practicing in the Charleston area for over ten years and has achieved recognition from the Charleston Regional Business Journal She received her B.S. Degree from Johnson C. Smith University in Charlotte, NC, her Post-Baccalaureate from Wayne State University in Detroit, MI & her Doctor of Medicine from Wayne State University School of Medicine in 1994. She completed her residency at Cook County Hospital in Chicago, IL, where she served as Chief Resident (Dept. of Obstetrics\/Gynecology).

name: Chary Tamirisa MD
bio: Dr. T is a board certified Obstetrician & Gynecologist. He is a fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, and was in private practice as an ob-gyn at Southwest Memorial Hospital since 1980. Dr. T is most interested in treating peri-menopause, menopause, premenstrual dystrophic disorder, polycystic ovarian syndrome in women, and andropause (male menopause), hypogonadism and erectile dysfunction in men.

name: Cherry Hills Midwifery and OB\/GYN
bio: Abbey completed her undergraduate at Research College of Nursing in Kansas City where she worked for Overland Park Regional for the Womens unit.  She later went on and received her Master of Science in Nursing from the University of Colorado with a specialty as a Women's Health Nurse Practitioner. Abbey also has an undergraduate in Business and her MBA from the University of Saint Mary in Leavenworth, KS. Abbey has spent 8 years working closely with OB GYN doctors in the GYN Post-Operative Care Unit(PACU) at Swedish Medical Center in Denver. With her passion for womens health, and her extensive knowledge on womans care, she is now joining our practice as a Womens Health Nurse Practitioner. Abbey has 3 young kids so when she is not at work you can find her spending time outdoors with her family or hitting the slopes!

name: Cherry Hills Midwifery and OB\/GYN
bio: Mindy Willits is extensively trained in her field, and, having worked as a nurse practitioner for more than 35 years, shes also one of the more experienced nurse practitioners in Denver. Mindy completed her undergraduate education in nursing at the University of Nebraska and later completed the Womens Healthcare Nurse Practitioner program at the University of Colorado School of Nursing. While Mindy provides a host of healthcare services for women who live in Denver, her special areas of interest are menopause and hormone replacement therapy management as well as diagnosis, treatment, and follow-up of human papillomavirus and abnormal pap smears. In addition, she also provides contraception services, performs ultrasound, and works with the other healthcare providers at the practice to provide obstetrical care. Mindy and her husband, Tom, have three grown children, Lindsey, Whitney and Billy and two grandsons. When she is not at the office she can be found paddle boarding Colorado rivers and lakes, tending to her flower gardens, and spending time with her dog, Zoe.

name: Cherry Hills Midwifery and OB\/GYN
bio: Alisa has extensive experience in both Obstetrics and Gynecology.  She has 14 years of clinical experience and has delivered over 1,000 babies in her career.  She has worked in Atlanta, Georgia;  San Diego, California;  and,  for the past 5 years, here in the Denver metro area.  Alisa combines her clinical expertise with an up-to-date academic excellence as she is currently a professor at Regis University teaching nursing students.  She is not only sharing her knowledge and experience with students, but continuing her own education pursuing a Doctorate degree as a Psychiatric Nurse Practitioner.  Alisas passion is communicating with her patients and treating both their physical and emotional concerns.  As of now, Alisa will see patients on Tuesday mornings and Wednesday afternoons.  She will be delivering babies at Swedish Hospital.  In addition to Obstetrics, Alisa will be providing Gynecologic care and BioTE therapy in our office.

name: Choctaw Women's Clinic PLLC
bio: As a Certified BioTE Platinum Partner and leader of the BioTE Medical team for Choctaw Womens Clinic, Sara Botchlet APRN-CNP brings a wealth of knowledge, experience and genuine passion for helping others to her work. She has specialized in womens health for many years and takes a unique and highly informed approach to caring for clients at all states of life. Ever mindful of how women today stay busy and lead complex lives, she provides solutions that promote wellness, balance and self-carestill while managing families, careers, health changes and more. Her goal for all women seeking help through Choctaw Womens Clinic is to create exceptional experiences that encourage continued attention and investment in their health.Sara earned a Bachelors Degree of Science in Nursing from the University of Oklahoma before embarking on a career working in a variety of healthcare settings. A relocation to Midland Texas led Sara to further her education at Texas Tech University earning a Masters in science with specific focus on Leadership and Management along with a Nurse Practitioner Certification with a specialty in family medicine. While in Texas, she worked as a Registered Nurse in Labor and Delivery. Before moving back to her native state of Oklahoma, Sara gained valuable experience as a surgical nurse assisting on all types of gynecological procedures. As a Nurse Practitioner for a thriving clinic, she has continued to provide comprehensive health care to women throughout their lifespans, including reproductive\/ gynecologic health needs, as well as well-woman care, prenatal\/postpartum care, contraceptive management, menopause care, treatment for acute\/chronic illnesses and advanced hormone replacement therapy.Today, in addition to her work at Choctaw Womens clinic, Sara Botchlet serves as the current chairman of the Choctaw Area Chamber of Commerce. She is mother to two boys, Dayton (9) and Reid (4)both of whom she loves watching play baseball. When shes not working, Sara loves spending time with family and friends and enjoys trips to the lake to unwind whenever possible.

name: Choctaw Women's Clinic PLLC
bio: Lindsay Flaming, APRN-CNPA Board Certified Nurse Practitioner, Lindsay brings many years of Nurse Practitioner experience diagnosing and treating acute and chronic illnesses and providing primary and preventive health care for all ages. Lindsay is excited to be able to bring hormone replacement therapy to her patients and improve their quality of life.  Lindsay holds a Bachelors of Science in Nursing from the University of Oklahoma, as well as a Family Nurse Practitioner Degree\/Masters of Science in Nursing from Vanderbilt University in Nashville, TN.

name: Christian Medical Associates
bio: Dr. Anthony Olofintuyi is the proud owner and operator of Christian Medical Associates in Columbus, Georgia.Dr. Olofintuyi is a board certified medical internist who specializes in the treatment of and adult medicine with a focus on wellness and healthy aging. He has been practicing medicine for the last 2 decades and takes pride in treating the whole person, whether it is spiritually or physically. He is a man of God with many special giftings that are evident in his daily walk and are evident throughout his entire medical practice. Dr. Olofintuyis decision to explore bio identical hormone replacement therapy was birthed out of the need to help his patients take a more holistic approach to wellness with each and every patient. Dr. Olofintuyi is very involved in his local community and spends quite a bit of time mentoring and teaching others. He enjoys spending time with his immediate and extended family. He is the father to four beautiful and intelligent children.

name: Christina Pena MD PA
bio: Dr. Pena is a native of Miami, Florida, where she enjoyed her youth and excelled at dance, mainly ballet, folklore and jazz. It was in high school when she took her first anatomy class that she fell in love with the workings of the human body. Dr. Pena explained that she was amazed at how God made us and how everything works together. She quickly realized, right then and there, that her calling was to become a doctor. It was while Dr. Pena attended the medical school at George Washington University in Washington, DC. That she decided OB\/GYN was going to be her specialty. During rotations she saw firsthand the critical decisions that women had to make, some of them life altering. Dr. Pena felt that the field of womens health would force her to really carry out her beliefs and philosophy about her passion for life.

name: Christy Walker, MD
bio: Dr. Christy Walkers mission is to loyally and ethically serve the community of women with quality health and cosmetic surgical care, by providing individualized and compassionate care that meets the needs of the whole woman, inside and out.Extensive fellowship training in cosmetic surgery and related procedures has allowed Dr. Walker to serve her patients in a way few board certified Obstetricians and Gynecologists are able by offering care for the whole woman. She completed a post-residency Clinical Fellowship Training Program in Cosmetic Surgery through the American Academy of Cosmetic Surgery (AACS) in 2014, as one of only 18 physicians chosen annually to participate in this training. During this training she performed over 1000 cosmetic procedures. Dr. Walker also received additional training under the direction of renowned surgeon Suzanne Yee and vaginal rejuvenation pioneer Dr. David Matlock. Dr. Christy Walker is ONE of the few Gynecologists in the country who is Fellowship trained in Cosmetic Surgery and Dual Board Certified as a Gynecologist and Cosmetic Surgeon by the Certification by the American Board of Cosmetic Surgery.Because of her experience treating thousands of women over the past decade, she recognizes the sensitive nature and emotional challenges associated with a womans body and her sense of femininity. As a woman, Dr. Walker identifies with the need to look good, be well, and feel great on the inside and out. Her unique gynecologic surgery skills, coupled with her broadened expertise in cosmetic surgery allows her to address the most sensitive and confidential cosmetic and vaginal surgical needs.Dr. Walker is a member of the American Academy of Cosmetic Surgery, American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology, and the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology, and the American Board of Cosmetic Surgery.She is married to Dr. Torrance Walker, an orthopedic surgeon. They have two school-aged children. Dr. Walker has a strong faith and she believes in being a good steward of the community, actively volunteering, and supporting causes she is passionate about.

name: Chronos BHW
bio: Dr. Mace Scott is a New Orleans native who earned his Doctor of Medicine degree from the LSU Health Sciences Center. He is a Board Certified of Physician and has served as Medical Director for multiple hospitals in southeast Louisiana.  Dr. Scott is Certified in General and Advanced Botox, Dysport and Dermal Filler Techniques. Dr. Scott is co-founder and co-owner of Chronos and is taking new patients.

name: Clinique Dallas Plastic Surgery
bio: John W. Antonetti, M.D. established Clinique Dallas Plastic Surgery in 2010, with the goal of providing unsurpassed, cutting edge plastic surgery and laser rejuvenating treatment options.Dr. Antonetti comes from a long family line of physicians. He is a Dallas native and a graduate of Texas A&M University, obtaining his medical degree from the University of Texas Medical Branch, and completing his residency in plastic surgery. In Ghent, Belgium, he completed Fellowship for Microsurgery, Perforator Flaps, and Advanced Breast Reconstructive techniques.He specializes in cosmetic and reconstructive surgery and performs a variety of procedures including breast augmentations, breast lifts and the Brazilian Butt Lift, love handle reduction, face and neck lifts, eyelid lifts, rhinoplasty, browlifts, liposuction, tummy tucks, thigh lifts, arm lifts, male gynecomastia, laser resurfacing, fat transfer, and injections such as Botox and Dysport, as well as fillers such as Juvederm, Voluma and Restylane.Dr. Antonetti is certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery, a member of the Dallas Society of Plastic Surgeons, Texas Society of Plastic Surgeons, and American Society of Plastic Surgeons. His office at Clinique Dallas is located in Building C, Medical City Dallas. Dr. Antonetti has published articles on topics including facial reconstruction, microsurgery, cosmetic surgery and burn surgery and presented research at national and international plastic surgery meetings.

name: Coastal Georgia Wellness Center and Family Medicine
Coastal Gynecology & Obstetrics
bio: Dr. H. Wade Boatwright specializes in minimally invasive surgery and female pelvic reconstructive surgery. He is certified in the da Vinci Robotic Surgical System. He has been performing laparoscopic hysterectomies since 1991. Known as early advocate for minimally invasive surgery, Dr. Boatwright is one of the few gynecologists in the area who performs the total laparoscopic hysterectomy through a single small incision. Medical advancements in surgery have changed what used to be a 3-day hospital stay, into a 23- hour outpatient observation. This means less cost for the patient and quicker recovery time and back to work in as little as 7 days! Ask if you are a candidate.Dr. Boatwright has been in the practice of obstetrics and gynecology since 1988 and is Board Certified in Gynecology and Obstetrics .Dr. Boatwright grew up in Columbia, South Carolina, graduated from Davidson College. He is married and has two grown daughters. His interests include equestrian sports, tennis, and outdoors activities.

name: Cobb Vinings Gynecology - Dr. Nanette Cook, MD
address: 4480 N. Cooper Lake Rd. SE Suite 220
bio: Dr. Cook is committed to providing you with quality gynecological care. DrCook prides herself in listening to and connecting wtih her patients. Shefeels that 50% of the ability to diagnose a problem comes from trulylistening to the patient. To that end, Dr Cook provides 100% of the care ofeach patient: there are no ancillary providers or nurse practitionersinvolved in the treatment of her patients.Dr Cook graduated Magna Cum Laude both from Spelman College and theMedical College of Georgia. She then completed four years of residency atEastern Virginia Medical School where she received awards for her work inresearch. The award that she covets the most, however, is \The MostCompassionate Resident\" award she received.Dr Cook worked full time for Wellstar for 8 years and for 2 _ of thoseyears also operated a medical weight management office part time. Duringthose 2 _ years

name: Cobb Womens Health, P.A.
bio: Dr. Nandita Mainthia is a Board Certified Obstetrician and Gynecologist practicing in the Austell and Smyrna area over the last 25 years. Affiliated with Wellstar Cobb Hospital, she has delivered over 2000 babies and performed countless gynecologic procedures. Currently, she specializes in treatments for all gynecologic conditions, including female sexual dysfunction, infertility, uterine fibroids, menstrual cycle disorders, and menopause. Dr. Nandita Mainthia is a graduate of Bombay University, India and has completed her residency from Albert Einstein College of Medicine in New York. She is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists. Dr. Mainthia is committed to helping her patients make well-informed choices about their health care.

name: Cobblestone Family Health
bio: Since 1983, Dr. John Amick has cared for patients in Liberty, MO and the surrounding area with the belief that medical management of diseases and health risk reductions will promote optimal health and prevent the future development of illness. He founded Cobblestone Family Health in 1993 and continues to practice the time-honored tradition of family medical care that includes periodic health-maintenance exams, in-office labs, x-rays, and a staff to coordinate medical referrals and testing.Dr. Amick graduated from Liberty High School and received a Bachelor of Arts in Chemistry from William Jewell College. He attended medical school at the Kansas City University of Medicine and Biosciences and completed his internship at the Tulsa Regional Medical Center. His is a member of the Psi Sigma Alpha Scholastic Fraternity for Academic Achievement. He is Board Certified in Family Practice and serves on the medical staffs of Liberty Hospital and North Kansas City Hospital. He is also the medical director of three local nursing homes.Dr. Amick and his wife have called Liberty and the Northland home for over 30 years. They raised their daughters and watched Liberty grow while maintaining its small-town appeal. Similarly, his practice has grown staying current with the medical technology while keeping the values of a small family practice.

name: Cobblestone Family Health
bio: Dr. John Burroughs joined Cobblestone Family Health in the summer of 2000. He had been in private practice outside of Boise, Idaho before moving to Liberty with his family.After graduating Cum Laude from Duke University, Dr. Burroughs earned his medical degree from Wake Forest University. Dr. Burroughs received residency training at the University of Utah where he was named Chief Resident for his final year of training.Dr. Burroughs enjoys teaching and tries to incorporate this into his practice. He believes that the doctor-patient relationship should be one of partners working toward improved health. He uses a focus on evidence-based medicine to counsel his patients and involve them in making decisions for treating acute illness as well as for preventive care visits.Family medicine provides a wonderful and exciting variety of challenges every day in the office and in the hospital. Dr. Burroughs loves the opportunity to work with patients of all ages: from newborns to ninety-year olds (and beyond). He was drawn to family medicine by the opportunity to prevent chronic disease(such as heart disease, diabetes and emphysema) andpromote lifestyle changes (such as weight loss and smoking cessation).  By seeing entire families in a practice, the family physician often gains a more complete understanding of the obstacles (and assistance) that a patient may have in obtaining their goal of excellent health.Dr. Burroughs is a member of the medical staffs of Liberty Hospital and North Kansas City Hospital. He is a medical director of two local nursing homes as well as Crossroads Hospice. He serves as a volunteer physician for Liberty High Schools athletic teams. He stays active outside of the office keeping up with the schedules of his four children and coaching youth soccer. He plays soccer and is traveling the country (slowly) running marathons.

name: Cobblestone Family Health
bio: Dr. Sadia Ali recently joined Cobblestone Family Health in the summer of 2017. After graduating from Arizona State University in Chemistry with an emphasis in Biochemistry, she became a full time mother of two beautiful daughters. Once her girls started school, she worked as a research assistant at the University of Kansas Biochemistry Department. She also completed her second Bachelors in Nursing with Honors from William Jewell College. She then joined Childrens Mercy Hospital in Kansas City as a staff nurse, and deeply enjoyed working with children for four years. To achieve the highest possible educational level in nursing, she earned her Doctorate in Nursing Practice concentrating on Family Practice from University of Missouri, Kansas City in 2017. Throughout her education, Dr. Ali has received several academic scholarships and awards. Dr. Ali believes that an individuals health is deeply linked to prevention of disease through lifestyle changes; hence her focus is on preventive care and education of healthy diet and lifestyle. She also believes in a holistic approach to medicine with evidence-based practice. Having a background in nursing has allowed Dr. Ali to be a compassionate and caring family practitioner for individuals seeking health care. She also believes in use of alternative medicine where it can benefit individuals and is evidenced-based. For the past few years she has been volunteering at Kids Zone of Shoal Creek Elementary School in Liberty to teach children about fall prevention and safety.Dr. Ali is a member of several professional organizations including Honors Society Sigma Theta Tau, American Association of Nursing Practitioners, Missouri Nurse Practitioner Association, Midwest Nurses Research Society, and the Advanced Practice Nurses of the Ozarks. She is always in search of new evidence-based procedures and treatment options.

name: CODY INTERACTIVE
bio: Dr. Donovitz started his practice in 1985 in Arlington, Texas.. Born and bred in Dallas, Texas, he graduated from The University of Texas, and finished medical school at The University of Texas in San Antonio. His residency training was at Tulane University in New Orleans. He is Board Certified and a Fellow in the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. Dr. Donovitz has always had a special interest in hormone replacement therapy. Treating both men and women, he was a early proponent of the bio-identical hormones. In 2007, he received advanced training in BHRT therapy.

name: Collier B. Gladin, Jr., MD LLC
Collier B. Gladin, Jr., MD LLC
Colorado Centers for Hormone Balance
bio: Dr. Woody is a native Coloradoan who specializes in procedural medicine.  He enjoys the challenges of hard to treat niches that are often times overlooked or leave patients trying multiple remedies and potions without resolution of their problems.  These procedures involve the treatment of many disease states including hemorrhoids and the GI tract, skin and nail disorders including nail fungus, medical aesthetics, hormone balance and natural wellness.  He incorporates the latest medical research, laser techniques, and holistic approach to his procedures and care plans. Dr. Woody graduated from Kansas City University of Medicine and Bioscience with his doctorate degree in 2000.  He completed his postgraduate training in Michigan and Colorado before becoming double board certified in Family Medicine and Holistic Medicine in 2003.  With Dr. Woody's diverse educational background and his penchant for developing top notch procedural skills, he offers treatments to his patients that are often only matched by specialists and sub-specialists.

name: Colorado Centers for Hormone Balance
bio: Dr. Woody is a native Coloradoan who specializes in procedural medicine.  He enjoys the challenges of hard to treat niches that are often times overlooked or leave patients trying multiple remedies and potions without resolution of their problems.  These procedures involve the treatment of many disease states including hemorrhoids and the GI tract, skin and nail disorders including nail fungus, medical aesthetics, hormone balance and natural wellness.  He incorporates the latest medical research, laser techniques, and holistic approach to his procedures and care plans. Dr. Woody graduated from Kansas City University of Medicine and Bioscience with his doctorate degree in 2000.  He completed his postgraduate training in Michigan and Colorado before becoming double board certified in Family Medicine and Holistic Medicine in 2003.  With Dr. Woody's diverse educational background and his penchant for developing top notch procedural skills, he offers treatments to his patients that are often only matched by specialists and sub-specialists.

name: Colorado Laser Clinic
bio: Dr. Robert T. Motazedi, MD. Dr. Motazedi is a Board Certified Cosmetic and Dermatological Laser Surgeon. He and his staff have performed well over 60,000 laser procedure in his Colorado Springs based clinic. In operation since 1993, the Colorado Laser Clinic is considered one of the most experienced laser centers in the world.Dr. Motazedi treats all his patients as unique individuals and treatment plans are tailored to address each person's unique situation. Starting with a comprehensive consultation that will take into consideration family history, genetic makeup, personal medical history, hormones, previous treatments, present conditions, etc., he will develop a personalized treatment protocol for each patient. Dr. Motazedi believes strongly that a person's inner vitality and health will reflect how vibrant and beautiful they are on the outside. For more than 10 years, he has been actively practicing anti-aging medicine and is happy to announce that he is making available to patients BioTE Medical therapy. Finally, a form of hormone replacement for men and women that is safe and effective. If you suffer from depression, mood swings, extreme fatigue, low libido, memory loss or fog, joint pain, night sweats or hot flashes, weight gain and loss of lean muscle mass, you may be a candidate for this innovative therapy. Let Dr. Motazedi and his staff bring out your inner butterfly.

name: Columbine Family Practice
bio: Rachele Salter F.N.P has been acting in a nursing capacity for ten years. She received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing at the Denver School of Nursing in December of 2006. She then decided to go back to school to be a Family Nurse Practitioner, which she completed in 2015 at the University of Colorado in Colorado Springs. She is so passionate about helping people of all ages with all of their healthcare needs.In her free time, Rachele enjoys all there is to experience in the beautiful Colorado outdoors.

name: Columbine Family Practice
bio: Returning physician Joseph M. Sharkey M.D. was first a member of Columbine Family Practice in 2007. After taking several years to pursue medical writing and an academic teaching position he has returned to assist Columbine Family Practice in caring for our beloved patients. Dr. Sharkey has an extensive medical career, including working as the ringside M.D. for the Colorado Golden Gloves, acting as a Medical Director for the Salvation Army & Rescue Mission Clinic, and several years in the U.S. Navy as a Medical Officer and Director of Drug and Alchohol Rehabilitation.Dr. Sharkey has extensive experience in the field of Rehabilitative and Addictive Medicine. He also has studied integrative medicine, including nutrition planning and mindful meditation practices

name: Columbus Medical Aesthetics
bio: J. Ronald Hunt, MDMedical Director J. Ronald Hunt, MD graduated from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill Medical School. He is a board-certified internal medicine physician and has lived and worked in Columbus, Georgia since 1983.

name: Columbus Medical Aesthetics
bio: Angela Hunt, NP-C Owner, Nurse Injector Angie Hunt, NP-C has been a registered nurse for more than twenty years. She has several years of experience in critical care and plastic surgery. She trained and developed her skill under the supervision of three board-certified plastic surgeons and has specialized in dermal fillers and Botox for more than ten years. She graduated Cum Laude from Columbus State University with her Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing. She graduated from University of South Alabama in 2015 with her nurse practitioner degree.

name: Columbus Medical Aesthetics
bio: Alysia is a Family Nurse Practitioner in Columbus, Georgia. Alysia began her nursing career in 2006 after graduating from Columbus State University with a Bachelors of Science in Nursing. She has an extensive background Emergency & Trauma nursing, including being Board Certified in Emergency Nursing. In 2014, she completed her Masters of Science in Nursing with a specialty in Family Nurse Practitioner at Troy University. Alysia has been practicing for the last 3 years at Northside Family Medicine until August when she joined Columbus Medical Aesthetics to help grow the BioTE program.

name: Complementary Family Medical Care of Indiana
bio: Linda Spencer, MSN, CPNP, FNP-CHas over 19 years' experience as a Nurse Practitioner specializing in alternative medicine including Bio-Identical hormone replacement therapy. She received bachelor's degree and master's degree from Indiana University School of Nursing. Second master's degree focused on Alternative Medicine received from University of Indianapolis. She is awarded Sigma Theta Tau International Honor Society of Nursing Academic Accomplishment and Leadership Award. Specializing in Bio-Identical hormones for both men and women to optimize your health.

name: Complementary Family Medical Care of Indiana
bio: Ellie Branagin is a Board-Certified Family Nurse Practitioner who specializes in bioidentical hormone replacement therapy, thyroid optimization, adrenal health, and wellness. She started her career 8 years ago at Eskenazi Hospital in the progressive care and med\/surg units. She completed her Bachelor of Science in Nursing at Indiana University Purdue University of Indianapolis and then earned her Master of science degree at Chamberlain School of Nursing. She holds national board certifications with the American Association of Nurse Practitioners.

name: Complete Care Clinic
bio: Coming Soon!

name: Complete Family Medicine
bio: Justin D. Puckett, D.O., is dual board certified in Osteopathic Family Medicine and Manipulative Treatment and Obesity Medicine. He is the Founder and Medical Director of Complete Family Medicine, LLC, headquartered in Kirksville, MO. In 2006, Puckett established Complete Family Medicine with a focus on providing comprehensive care for the entire family.  Services offered now include areas of focus in Family Medicine, Obesity Medicine, Urgent Care, and other specialties services. He is an avid teacher, working with students and residents in a variety of settings. Most recently he was awarded the Steelman\/Seim Educator Award for Excellence in Academics from the American Society of Bariatric Physicians.  In 2012 he was named one of Kirksvilles Top 5 under 40.  Dr. Puckett was raised in rural Southwest Missouri. He obtained his undergraduate degree with honors in Biology, Philosophy and Religion at Drury University in Springfield, Missouri. It is there that he met his wife, Kylene. They have 4 children: Prestin, Alia, Braden, and Camdin. Kylene serves as Complete Family Medicines Chief Operating Officer. He attended medical school at ATSU-KCOM in Kirksville. Dr. Puckett also completed an AOA Fellowship in Health Policy at the New York Institute of Technology-New York College of Osteopathic Medicine during his last year of residency. This is led to an active role in health policy both locally and nationally, always advocating for his patients. He offers staff and patients the opportunity to join him on Capitol Hill each year! Dr. Puckett has served many national and state leadership roles and is the current president of the Missouri Society of the American College of Osteopathic Family Physicians. Dr. Puckett is also a past officer of a variety of state and national medical societies. He was also Chief Resident at Northeast Regional Medical Center his senior year of residency.Outside of medicine, Dr. Puckett loves to travel and explore with his family. He also enjoys SCUBA, thrill rides and amusement parks, and being active in his community. The Pucketts are active members of The Crossing Church.

name: Complete Health & Wellness
bio: Dr. Brown achieved board certified in both family practice and sports medicine.He is a member of the American Academy of Private Physicians, for which he serves as a delegate for the state of Texas.He completed his medical school training at University of Nevada School of Medicine in 1999, and went on to postgraduate training at St. Josephs family practice residency program in Houston, Texas from 1999-2002.In 2003, he completed additional training in sports medicine, earning a fellowship in 2003.Then, it was on to private practice in Sugarland Texas where he remained until early 2011. He then moved just 3 miles down the road to Missouri City, Texas, where he is currently practicing.Dr. B. has taken care of many local sports teams, including University of Houston, Texas Southern University, Houston Baptist University, The Houston Comets, and numerous area high schools. He also continues to work with dozens of professional ball players as well as Olympic athletes. On a daily basis, Dr. Brown provides a highly personalized level of care, focusing on health, wellness, and prevention - regardless of age or medical conditions. The important part is that the medical care provided is a partnership, optimizing the original intent of the doctor-patient relationship. While sub-specializing in sports medicine, and having a niche in functional\/nutritional medicine, Dr. Brown has never considered practicing any in any other sector of medicine than family practice. To Dr. Brown, it has never made sense to treat something in the leg if its root cause is in the back; to address a sports injury without considering the psychological impact; or to neglect considering nutritional deficiencies for something like headaches. While highly specialized areas of expertise are necessary and very much a part of what has given the US the best health care system in the world, an ability to treat the masses has always been Dr. Browns focus. Being able to treat most things in most people, implemented with targeted referrals, has worked out very well. This of course requires a good sense of limitations, mixed with a tremendous breadth of knowledge and ability to make people and keep people well.
