name: Complete Health Integrative Wellness Clinic
bio: Dr. Kenneth Thomas, MDEducationUndergraduate: B.S. Chemical Engineering,Mississippi State UniversityMedical SchoolM.D., University of Mississippi Medical CenterResidencyUrologyUniversity of Virginia, Charlottesville, VAMedical LicenseMississippiCertificationBoard Certified -- American Board of Urology   Our missionOur mission at Thomas Urology Clinic is to serve the greater Mississippi and Alabama community with prompt and excellent urological care that is courteous, compassionate, and state-of-the-art.  We are here for you when you need us, so dont hesitate to contact us with any questions

name: Complete Hormone Solutions
bio: Dr. Adams received his DMD and MD at UAB. He performed his residency at Huntsville Hospital in 1983 working in family practice. In 1992 he entered private practice in the Huntsville area, and spent 13 years at the Center for Cancer Care.Dr. Adams practices functional medicine, blending natural and prescription medicine.Dr. Adams loves animals - in fact he has 4 dogs, and 6 chickens! He enjoys hunting and fishing on a regular basis.

name: Complexions Medi Spa
bio: Dr. Virginia Beaton FNP-BC, is a board certified doctoral prepared nurse practitioner. Her under-graduate training was at Columbia-Presbyterian Medical Center in New York City. She has 2 masters degrees in family nursing practice from New York University and Long Island University with a PhD specializing in primary care. She has advanced training past her post-doctoral work in esthetic medical procedures from the Esthetic Skin Institute in Fort Lauderdale, Florida and continues to attend advanced classes to stay on the cutting edge of her field. Dr. Beaton practices esthetic medicine and healthy aging procedures. Her expertise is sculpting the face with multiple modalities and technology's. The office has the latest technology in laser treatments and she performs regenerative techniques with platelet rich plasma.

name: Comprehensive Family Care\/ Luminescence
bio: Dr. Kenneth Pettit is a highly-trained and qualified physician specializing in family practice, aesthetic medicine and wound care. Dr. Pettit received his medical degree from the Western University of Health Sciences, College of Osteopathic Medicine of the Pacific, Pomona, CA. He graduated in 1997 and completed his Residency at Tempe St. Lukes hospital, Tempe Arizona, in June of 2000. After completing his residency in 2000, he opened his Family Practice in Ahwatukee, Arizona. Dr. Pettit cares for 5,500 active patients himself as well as making hospital bedside visits. He was voted the top physician in Ahwatukee in 2007 and 2010 and in the top 3 physicians in Ahwatukee in 2008 and 2009.Alongside of his Family Practice, Dr. Pettit provides Aesthetic Medicine using non-invasive laser treatments. Dr. Pettit has been an active voice in the discussion of indirect vs. direct supervision while performing laser procedures. His personal touch sets him above all other aesthetic medicine providers.

name: Comprehensive Family Medicine
bio: Dr. Katherine Kate Gordon has been a family doctor for 18 years and is currently practicing  in her hometown of West Columbia, SC. A graduate of Clemson University and MUSC in Charleston, she has special interests in a holistic approach to treating people, including providing traditional family medicine as well as alternative approaches to making her patients feel better.

name: Comprehensive Medical Weight Loss
bio: Dr. Steven Foley graduated from  Indiana University Medical School and completed his obstetrics and gynecology residency at Indiana University Hospitals. Prior to moving to Colorado Springs in 2004, he practiced obstetrics and gynecology in Indianapolis, Indiana for 16 years. Dr. Foley is one of the nation's foremost experts in PCOS and insulin resistance. He has a passion to educate the community, patients and healthcare professionals about the diagnosis and treatment of this important condition.  Dr. Foley is also actively involved with medical research of new treatments for a variety of gynecologic disorders.  He is certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He has medical privileges at Penrose-St. Francis Hospital, Memorial Hospital, Audubon, and Premier Surgery Centers.

name: Comprehensive Pain Care
bio: Dr. Ronit Adler is a highly trained, experienced and licensed specialist in pain management and aesthetic medicine. After receiving her medical degree, she completed her internship at SUNY Downstate Medical Center Hospital, and then her residency in anesthesiology at Kings County Hospital Center in Brooklyn, NY.Dr. Adler went on to serve as Director of Pain Management at the Brooklyn Department of Veterans Affairs, Director of St. Albans Extended Care Center in Queens, Assistant Instructor of Anesthesiology at SUNY Health Science Center in Brooklyn and Chief of Pain Management at Good Samaritan Hospital Medical Center in West Islip, NY.Currently, in private practice in both pain management and aesthetic medicine, Dr. Adler also serves as Chief of Pain Management at Brookhaven Memorial Hospital Medical Center in Patchogue, NY. She received a fellowship in Meso-Lipotherapy from the International Meso-Lipotherapy Society and is a Diplomat of the American Board of Pain Management.Dr. Adler is very active in several medical organizations including the American Medical Association, Suffolk County Medical Society, New York State Medical Society, American Academy of Pain Management, American Society of Regional Anesthesia, American Society of Interventional Pain Physicians and the Society for Pain Practice Management.Dr. Ronit Adler has spent the past 20 years speaking and teaching on the subject of pain management and prides herself on utilizing state of the art, wellness-oriented medicine.Dr. Adler is licensed to practice medicine in New York and Florida.Member of the American Society of Anesthesiologists, and the Florida Medical Association.

name: Conroe Aesthetics & Wellness
bio: Dr. Seay has been a physician in the Conroe area since 1998.  She received her undergraduate degree at St. Mary's University.  Her medical degree is from UT Medical Branch.  She completed training at the Conroe Family Medicine Residency.  She has a special interest in preventative care, well woman exams, well child care, hormone replacement therapy and chronic diseases like diabetes, heart disease, and hypertension.  Her hobbies include running, gardening, cooking, and baking.

name: Conroe Aesthetics & Wellness
bio: Dr. Garcia joined her sister in practice in 2002. She graduated from Rice University before attending medical school at UT Houston Health Science Center. She then completed her residency at Memorial Hermann Southwest Family Practice Residency. Dr. Garcia has a special interest in diabetes care, women's issues, and preventive care for the entire family. Her favorite pastimes are camping, hiking, reading, and dancing.

name: Conroe Aesthetics & Wellness
bio: Aprill Rowe, M.D. is the full-time physician at the new Spring location. She has her undergraduate degree from Texas A&M Corpus Christi and her medical degree from UT Medical Branch. Afterwards she completed her residency at the Conroe Family Medicine Residency Program. Dr. Rowe spent a great deal of time practicing at a critical care hospital and rural health clinic where she saw patients of all ages and even delivered babies. Dr. Rowes special interests include womens health, childrens preventative care and providing comprehensive medical to care families. Her hobbies include reading, traveling, gardening and cooking. She enjoys spending time with her family and learning about new places and cultures that she hopes to visit one day.

name: Contemporary Women's Care PA
bio: Dr. Rice is originally from Dallas  and is thrilled to give back to her hometown community. Prior to her medical education, she earned a B.A. and Masters degree in Social Work and was a practicing Licensed Masters Social Worker.  She attended medical school at The University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio, followed by residency at the Health Science Centers affiliated facility, University Hospital.Dr. Rice is passionate about womens health issues and places great value on patient education.  She believes that health care delivery can be kind and compassionate, and she strives to provide an atmosphere for her patients that is understanding and comfortable. These values are why Dr. Rice is pleased to have joined Drs. Thomas and Franken, who share her enthusiasm for a patient\/physician relationship based on trust and teamwork.  Dr. Rice enjoys traveling, snow skiing, and relaxing with a good book or movie. She and her husband Tom stay busy keeping up with their two daughters, Alex and Cate.

name: Contemporary Women's Care PA
bio: Dr. Jacob is originally from Dallas and is very excited to practice in her hometown.  She received her B.A. in Biology from the University of Texas at Austin.  Dr. Jacob attended medical school at St. George's University, School of Medicine in Grenada, West Indies.  She continued her medical training throughout the New York City area. After receiving her medical degree, she completed residency at Danbury Hospital in Danbury, CT. She is now happy to be back home in Texas giving back to her commuinty.Dr. Jacob is the newest addition to our practice and is dedicated to women's health issues.  Her main focus is in developing long term relationships with her patients based on trust and understanding. She spend time listening to her patients and advocated preventive medicine and patient education. The is thrilled to bring high quality care and personal attention to her patients.Dr. Jacob is recently married and enjoys traveling, watching movies, enjoying good food and spending time with her husband, Suraj, and family and friends.

name: CoraMed Healthcare
bio: Dr. Costello is the Chief Physician and President here at CoraMed Healthcare.  He began practicing medicine after receiving his Doctor of Medicine Degree from the University of California, Davis in 1983, and completing his residency at San Francisco General Hospital.  Dr. Costello is board certified in Family Medicine and Holistic Medicine.  In addition, he has a Master of Arts Degree in Spiritual Psychology, is currently in Fellowship in Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine and is a member of the American Academy of Pain Management.  Over the years Dr. Costello has also received many awards of recognition for his outstanding work in Family Medicine.  Dr. Costello \loves working with the staff and helping our patients\".  One thing you may not know about Dr. Costello is that he plays the drums and was the drummer in a blues band for many years."

name: Core Optimal Health Solutions
bio: Dr. Angelina Alejandro graduated from Southwest College of Naturopathic Medicine.  She is a licensed Naturopathic Medical Doctor.  Her undergraduate degree is from the University of Arizona where she received a Bachelor of Science in Agriculture  specifically Dietetics. She spent many years in the food service industry and her love of clinical nutrition and botanical medicine is where her passion lies.Angelina is a native to Arizona, born and raised in Mesa. She wants to have a relationship with every person like they were a part of her own family. Her experience as a phlebotomist and IV administrator before attending Southwest College of Naturopathic Medicine is where she acquired her inspiration in holistic care. It was through her work in Integrative Medicine, where she finds her inner focus. She is dedicated to nutritional counseling, allergies, detoxification, weight loss, environmental health, hormone replacement therapy and pain management.

name: Cornerstone Wellness
bio: Dr. Choudhry was born and raised in Texas.  She pursued medical school because she genuinely cares for others and had a passion for Obstetrics and Gynecology.  She enjoys caring for women in all stages of their lives and places a focus on their individual needs and desires.Jo Choudhry, M.D., received a B.S. in Genetics at Texas A&M University in 2000.  Graduation from Texas A&M Health Science Center College of Medicine was in 2004.  Her specialty training in Obstetrics and Gynecology was at the University of Kansas in Wichita, Kansas.  Dr. Choudhry is married to Vinnie Choudhry, M.D. and she enjoys movies, dining out, swimming, and shopping

name: Cornerstone Wellness
bio: Kathryn Anger, M.D. was born in Fort Worth, Texas.  She attended college at Taylor University in Upland, Indiana where she received a B.A. in Biology in 2007 she graduated from the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston, Texas.  She then spent four years training in Obstetrics and Gynecology in Syracuse, New York through SUNY Upstate Medical University.  Dr. Anger is married with two children and enjoys painting, ballet, horseback riding, and spending time with her family.

name: Cornerstone Wellness
bio: Dr. Blanca Duncan was born in Mexico and has lived in Louisiana and Texas for most of her life. She received a degree in International Business from Louisiana State University. She then attended medical school and completed her residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Louisiana State University Health Science Center in Shreveport, LA. She is board certified with the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.Dr. Duncan is married to Adam. They have two dogs and a cat. She enjoys: reading, jogging, traveling and spending time with her family.

name: Cornerstone Wellness
bio: Kendra Bookout, M.D., was born and raised in Odessa, Texas. She received her Bachelor's degree from Texas A&M University, graduating magna cum laude. Dr. Bookout attained her Doctorate of Medicine from Texas A&M University Health Science Center College of Medicine and completed her residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Baylor University Medical Center in Dallas. Dr. Bookout is passionate about women's health throughout all phases of life and seeks to give honest individualized attention to every patient under her care. She has been trained to manage both low and high-risk pregnancies, as well as the particular needs of the menopausal patient. Some of her special interests include da Vinci robotic surgery and advanced laparoscopy, hysteroscopy, urogynecological procedures, such as those to treat urinary incontinence and pelvic floor disorders, and the management of uterine fibroids and heavy uterine bleeding.Dr. Bookout lives in the Round Rock area with her husband, Rod, their son Luke, and an energetic dog named Charlie. In her free time, she enjoys bike-riding, theatre and musicals, and spending time with family and friends.

name: Country Home Family Clinic
bio: Dr. Beverly De La Bruere graduated from Washburn University of Topeka with a B.S. in Biology, magna cum laude, with departmental honors, then completed another year of training to become a Medical Technologist. She went on to medical school at the Kansas University School of Medicine, completing her M.D. degree in 1983 and finished a residency in Family Practice in 1986 at the Kansas University Medical Center. She has been practicing family medicine for nearly 30 years. Over the years, Dr. De La Bruere has pursued more natural and integrative courses in continuing education. Nutrition has become a passion of hers and she is also achieving a certification through the Institute of Functional Medicine. The goal is to pursue wellness and recovery of health through understanding the underlying factors that lead to disease or lack of health. There is an emphasis on healthy lifestyle choices. In line with that, she is recently trained to help patients with BioTE bio-identical hormone pellets to enhance their quality of life and disease prevention.  Dr. De La Bruere has found that pellet therapy is the optimal delivery system for hormone balance.  In addition, she treats opiate dependence in an outpatient setting and does some Christian counseling.  She is Board Certified in Family Medicine and a member of the American Academy of Family Physicians.In her free time, she loves square dancing, quilting, gardening, and seeing her grandchildren. If you are interested in better health, improving your lifestyle, or struggling with the traditional medical system and getting no answers, give us a call.

name: Courtyard Family Practice
bio: Mr. Salas is an Advanced Practice Registered Nurse certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners. Born and Raised in Midland, He graduated from Lee High School, is married with three children. Mr. Salas received his Paramedic License from Midland College in 2002, followed by his RN license in 2006 at Midland College, received his Bachelor's Degree in Nursing in 2008, and his Master's Degree in Nursing in 2012 at Texas Tech Health Sciences Center. He also has credentials from the National Registry of Certified Medical Examiners to perform DOT physicals. Certified in OSHA 1910 standards. Currently attending Texas Tech University in pursuit of his Doctorate in Nursing Practice.  As a paramedic, Kevin began his career at Midland Memorial hospital as a Paramedic in the Emergency Department. As a Registered Nurse, Kevin began his career with Medical Center Hospital as a lead trauma nurse and progressed to Emergency Department Director. In 2009, Mr. Salas changed his career path and entered the field of Flight nursing with Care-star in Odessa, Texas. While working as a Flight Nurse Mr. Salas worked towards obtaining his Master from Texas Tech with an emphasis in Family Nurse Practitioner. Mr. Salas has a total of 14 years of medical experience specialized in emergency and trauma. He also holds certifications in Advanced Cardiac Life Support, Pediatric Advanced Life Support, and Advanced Trauma Life Support, Critical Care Emergency Medical Transport Provider, Nationally Registered Certified Medical Examiner. Outside of Work Mr. Salas enjoying coaching his daughters in softball, playing golf and spending as much time as he can with his family.

name: Cratos Health
bio: Dr. Urban has practiced in Colorado since 1990 and is the Medical Director at Cratos Health, having helped open the center with Founder Steve Apodaca.  He is certified by BioTE Medical in bio-identical hormone replacement therapy. Dr. Urban attended the University of Wisconsin, receiving a Bachelors Degree with Honors, and a Doctor of Medicine Degree.  He completed his Residency in Anesthesiology at the State University of New York in Syracuse, and was Chief Resident.  He is Board Certified in Anesthesiology, and licensed to practice Medicine in Colorado.

name: Cratos Health

Andrew also practices ER Medicine as a Physician Assistant in Colorado Springs.  He graduated with honors in 2005.  Having more than 13 years of diverse experiences, Andrew affiliates with many hospitals including Centura Health-Penrose St. Francis Health Services, Centrua Health-St. Thomas More Hospital, and cooperates with other doctors and specialists in many medical groups including Front Range Emergency Specialists LLC.

name: Cross Roads Hormonal Health & Wellness
bio: Dr Cortez is board certified and a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  She attended The University of North Texas for her undergraduate education and received her M.D. from the University of Texas Southwestern.  She completed her internship and residency at Parkland Memorial Hospital in Dallas.  Dr Cortez now practices at Texas Health Resources Denton where she is Chairman of the OB\/GYN Department. Her primary focus is women's healthcare, but she also has a passion for hormonal health and assisting her patients with their weight loss goals so they too can achieve successful, long term weight loss as she has herself.   Dr Cortez treats both men and women for hormonal health and weight loss.

name: Cross Roads Hormonal Health & Wellness
bio: Dr. Collins offers a wide range of obstetric and gynecological services for women.  She has also received additional training through The Center for Medical Weight Loss and hormone management training through BioTe Medical for both men and women.Dr. Collins is a Junior Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. She was born in South Texas and knew from a young age that she wanted to be a doctor. In high school she decided she wanted to be an Obstetrician\/Gynecologist after noticing how difficult it was to find female physicians for herself. She graduated in the top 3 of her high school class in San Antonio and was recognized as a National Hispanic Scholar.She then received a scholarship to attend Stanford University in California, where she graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in Human Biology and a minor in Latin American Studies. During college, she traveled to other countries such as Chile and Cuba, where she studied different healthcare systems and how they compare to the United States. She then decided to return to her home state to pursue a career in medicine that she hoped would influence young women in a positive way.After receiving her medical degree at University of Texas Southwestern in Dallas, Dr. Collins completed her residency at Methodist Health systems in Dallas. There, she participated in leadership roles and learned a lot about high risk obstetrics and minimally invasive surgery. Dr. Collins offers a wide range of obstetric and gynecological services for women. She has special interests in holistic obstetrics and minimally invasive gynecologic surgery. She has also received additional training for weight loss, thyroid, and hormone management for men and women.In her spare time, Dr. Collins enjoys spending time with her family, gardening and reading.

name: Cruzado Ramos Gynecology, LLC
bio: Dr. Gustavo Cruzado-Ramos is a faculty physician at San Juan City Hospital in the program of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  Likewise, he is an associated professor at Universidad de Puerto Rico, School of Medicine and Universidad Central del Caribe, School of Medicine.Dr. Cruzado is Board Certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology and Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He received his M.D. from Universidad Central del Caribe and his specialty from San Juan City Hospital.Additionally, with more than 10 years of experience as a provider, delivering medical and surgical care to women in his private practice at Ashford Presbyterian Hospital, Dr. Cruzados relationship with his patients are long-term and are often maintained through the postmenopausal stage of a patient's life.

name: Cunningham Clinic
bio: Kimberly Cunningham, Nurse PractitionerKimberly moved to Colorado in 2001 after visiting the state for years as a winter and summer sport enthusiast.  With practice experience from the emergency department and inpatient hospital care to skilled nursing facilities and internal medicine clinics, she brings both clinical knowledge and excellent procedure skills to her aesthetic practice.Kimberlys passion in helping people to look and feel better is achieved through a conservative approach.  Her goal is to help clients achieve desired results with the minimum amount of intervention to achieve a natural correction and to avoid looking done.  First time clients can feel comfortable knowing she uses a start low, go slow approach and crafts clinic days to allow for longer visits and time to review each persons individual anatomy, age related changes and the best way to utilize an array of treatment options including Botox, fillers, BioTe hormone optimization, Viora Reaction treatments and microneedling to correct those changes.BOARD CERTIFICATION AND LICENSUREAmerican Academy of Nurse Practitioners: Board Certified Adult Nurse PractitionerAdvanced Practice Nurse: State of ColoradoRegistered Nurse: State of ColoradoPROFESSIONAL AFFILIATIONSAmerican Academy of Nurse Practitioners, MemberColorado Nurses Association, MemberAmerican Nurses Association, MemberSigma Theta Tau Nursing Honorary, inducted 2004

name: D'Lana M. Hitt Aesthetics and Wellness
bio: D'Lana has been a Registered Nurse for 18 years. She graduated Cum Laude in nursing and went on to receive her Master's degree in Nursing from Frontier Nursing University in 2013 and is a Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner with the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners. Her clinical background includes the intensive care unit, emergency department, bariatric surgery and weight loss, urgent care, and family practice medicine. D'Lana has also worked for a leading plastic surgeon in the Houston Bay Area. She is a certified BioTe provider and is very committed with working with her patients and improving their quality of life.

bio: Rebekah Daily, RN, MSN, FNP-C earned her Master of Science in Nursing degree at the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston, Texas where she was inducted into Sigma Theta Tau International Honor Society of Nursing. She also earned an undergraduate degree from Lamar University, Bachelor of Science in Nursing. Rebekah brings a wealth of experience to family practice with a background as an ICU Registered Nurse at Christus St. Mary hospital, and takes pride is helping families maintain optimal health. She has worked as a Family Nurse Practitioner in private practice since 2007. She is credentialed through the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners as a Certified Nurse Practitioner and is a member of Texas Nurse Practitioners as well as Southeast Texas Nurse Practitioners organizations.Mrs. Daily is married to Shane Daily and they reside in Bridge City. They have twin sons, Graham and Eli, who are currently in the 3rd grade. The family loves spending time in the outdoors together. Fishing and boating are some of their favorite pass times. They also enjoy watching their sons play on various sports teams.Jeremy Huff, DO is Mrs. Dailys Collaborating Physician.

name: Daily Green Family Health and Convenient Care
bio: Becky Green, RN, MSN, FNP-C earned her Master of Science in Nursing degree at the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston, Texas where she was inducted into Sigma Theta Tau International Honor Society of Nursing. She also earned two undergraduate degrees from Lamar University, Bachelor of Science in Nursing and Bachelor of Science in Biology.  Becky brings a wealth of experience to family practice with a background as an ICU Registered Nurse at Christus St. Mary hospital and is passionate about helping families maintain optimal health. She has worked as a Family Nurse Practitioner in private practice since 2007. She is credentialed through the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners as a Certified Nurse Practitioner and is a member of Texas Nurse Practitioners as well as Southeast Texas Nurse Practitioners organizations. Mrs. Green is married to Michael Green and they reside in Little Cypress. Their daughter Jillian works for Universal Studios in Orlando, Florida and is a graduate of Lamar University. Their daughter Kendall is a recent Texas A&M University graduate and is working for Freddie Mac in Washington, D.C. When not at home caring for their various pets, the family enjoys traveling throughout the U.S. and around the world. They also enjoy following college and professional football and baseball teams.Jeremy Huff, DO is Mrs. Greens Collaborating Physician.

name: Dallas Family Medical Association of Health and Wellness
bio: Dr. Reihsen has been practicing Family Medicine since 1992. She provides a wide range of care for all ages, including a variety of preventive services. Dr. Reihsens interest in medicine started at a young age as a result of her experiences.  In third grade she was diagnosed with hearing loss.  Over the course of the next 10 years, she had 5 ear surgeries.  During one surgery she had a complication and lost all the hearing on her left side.  She has been wearing hearing aides since that time.  Through these experiences, she developed a desire to learn more about medicine. Dr. Reihsen founded Dallas Family Medical in 1997.  During her training, she found her aspiration  to work with patients to help them to achieve their health goals.  Her enthusiasm for medicine has led her to seek advanced training in sleep medicine, bio-identical hormones and allergy treatment.  She sees her field as challenging and deeply rewarding.    The journey of life is not just to live, but to be challenged, humbled and amazed.  To be able to share this journey with you is a responsibility I take very seriously. Professional Information:College:  Missouri State UniversityMedical School:  University of Missouri  ColumbiaInternship and Residency:  University of Oklahoma Health Sciences CenterBoard Certified in Family Medicine with an additional Certification in Sleep Medicine Personal InterestsFavorite Sport:  TennisFavorite Team:  Texas RangersFavorite Food:  Apple pie with a small serving of vanilla ice cream!

name: Dallas Family Medical Association of Health and Wellness
Dan Tudor MD
bio: Dr. Tudor finished Internal Medicine training in the Yale University School of Medicine system\/Danbury Hospital followed by Nephrology Fellowship at Cleveland Clinic. He joined the medical faculty at West Virginia University where he expanded his expertise in kidney imaging and Procedural Nephrology under the affiliation with American Society of Diagnostic and Interventional Nephrology. He had particular interest in critical care Nephrology and Peritoneal Dialysis. He was a Certified Clinical Specialist in Hypertension by the American Society of Hypertension. He continues to keep his association with the University of Florida in Gainesville and Board Certification in Nephrology.Since 2014 he expanded his scope of practice to hormone replacement therapies.

name: Dana Snell DO PLLC
bio: Dana Snell-Hargrove, DO is a Board Certified Obstetrician\/Gynecologist and a Fellow in the American Osteopathic College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  She received her medical degree from Michigan State University.  She completed her internship and residency at Genesys Regional Medical Center in Grand Blanc, Michigan.  She is a retired Major from the Air National Guard after 20 years of service.  She now delivers at the Medical Center Alliance Hospital.  She provides comprehensive obstetric and gynecologic services to include but not limited to pap smears, abnormal vaginal bleeding, birth control, Davinci Robotic surgery, laparoscopy, menopausal symptoms, obstetrical care, post menopausal bleeding, and well woman exam.  Dr. Snell-Hargrove has received advanced training in hormone replacement therapy and is now providing the benefits of this medical treatment to her patients.

name: Davidhizar Medical PLLC
bio: Dr. John Davidhizar believes medical care should be accessible and timely. Doctors should be directly approachable & responsive (instead of through an answering service), an advocate for you in other environments (in the hospital, E.R., and with other specialists), and a trusted advisor who is accountable to you, knows you by name and cares about protecting your most important asset, your health. A practice should have transparent pricing with no surprises, and be free of government and insurance dictates that oftentimes do not have the best interest of the patient in mind.Dr. John was born and raised in Texas, coming from a family of 12. He earned a Bachelor of Science in Biomedical Sciences from Texas A&M University, completed medical school at the University of Texas Medical School in Houston, and is board certified in Family Medicine. He joined MyMDbcs in July 2014 and is excited about providing care at a practice that makes possible many of the health care principles he is passionate about.

name: Deer Creek Family Healthcare and Wellness Clinic
bio: Kimberly Allen is a Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner at Deer Creek Family Health Care and Wellness Clinic. She has been a registered nurse since 1996 with experience in pediatrics and adult health. In 2001, Kimberly graduated from the University of Oklahoma Masters of Science Family Nurse Practitioner program. She is currently completing her Doctorate of Nursing Practice and plans to be finished sometime later this summer. Kimberly has vast experience in women's health, pediatrics, hospice, and family practice.

name: Deer Creek Family Healthcare and Wellness Clinic
Deer Creek Family Healthcare and Wellness Clinic
Deirdre McMullen MD
bio: Dr. Deirdre McMullen is board certified in family medicine and tries to emphasize wellness in her practice while also managing chronic and acute conditions. She provides traditional family medicine including annual physicals, well woman exams, hormone replacement therapy, immunizations, and well child\/ baby services in addition to her cosmetic procedures and weight loss management. From illness to wellness, we hope you will find a home in our patient family. Dr. McMullen was initially in a larger group but is now in solo practice in Missouri City, where she also resides. She is married and has two children, and six dogs. B.S. name: Dennis Eisenberg MD
bio: Recently elected by his peers as a D Magazine Best Doctor in Collin County for 2013, Dr. Eisenberg has become recognized as a leader in both obstetrics and gynecology. He has been practicing womens healthcare in the Dallas Metroplex for over 15 years and currently practices in three Metroplex offices: Medical Center of Plano, Baylor Medical Center of Frisco, and Baylor Plano. Having performed the first robotic hysterectomy in North Dallas, Dr. Eisenberg has been at the forefront of the da Vinci method, which involves minimally invasive procedures.  At Medical Aesthetics of North Dallas, Dr. Eisenberg puts his passion for leading edge procedures in motion as he addresses the aesthetic needs of both male and female patients.

name: Denovo Health Clinics
bio: John Stevens was born and raised in western Kansas. The initial years of his medical career were spent in the critical care and surgical units of academic hospitals where he gained extensive experience in cardiovascular ICU and trauma. He was called from the Army Reserves in 1990 where he served as a trauma nurse in Operation Desert Storm.John has held nearly every position in nursing, ranging from staff nurse to director of nursing. John founded deNovo Medical Group in 1996 and has utilized his extensive management experience to make the practice one of the most recognized anti-aging facilities in the country. He is a highly respected medical aesthetics practitioner, providing training to medical professionals on behalf of many of the largest companies in laser resurfacing, injectable fillers and anti-aging therapies.________________________________________MEDICAL TRAININGBaccalaureate Degree in Nursing, St. Mary of The Plains College; Master of Science degree, Texas Womans University; currently pursuing Doctorate of Nursing Practice, University of Missouri at Kansas City.AREAS OF EXPERTISENon-surgical facelift, non-surgical browlift, laser skin resurfacing and tightening, Botox, injectable fillers (Restylane, Perlane, Juvederm, Radiesse, Sculptra), Photofacial, dermabrasion and laser hair removal.

name: Denver Diagnostic Pain
bio: Jack Rentz, MD, is passionate about helping his patients optimize their lives. Board-certified in anesthesia and pain medicine, Dr. Rentz incorporates regenerative medicine and wellness by looking at the whole patient. This includes optimizing hormones, testing for food sensitivities and micronutrient deficiencies along with restoring function through injections.After completing his undergraduate degree at the University of Georgia, he attended the Medical School of Georgia where he received his doctorate. Dr. Rentz then moved to New Orleans where he completed his residency in anesthesiology at Ochsner Hospital. There he was honored to serve as chief resident before receiving a fellowship at the prestigious Pain Medicine Center at Texas Tech University in Lubbock, TXDr. Rentz is excited about serving his patients at his practice, Denver Diagnostic Pain, where his goal is to provide the highest level of care to those who entrust him with their health. Each patient that comes to his practice is on a journey to improve their quality of living and is choosing to partner with Dr. Rentz along the way. This is a responsibility with which he is honored to be trusted.

name: Dept. OBGYN Hamilton Medical Group
bio: Dr. Fuller has provided compassionate quality care for women since 1985 as an ABOG Board Certified member of the Obstetrics and Gynecology Department of Hamilton Medical Group.  He was raised in New Iberia and obtained a degree in Biology from Louisiana State University in Baton Rouge, and his MD from Louisiana State University School of Medicine in Shreveport. He completed his Internship and Residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of South Alabama Medical Center in Mobile where he served as chief resident. He is a fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.Dr. Fuller lives in Lafayette with his wife Sarah. They have two grown sons, Ryan and Ben. They enjoy short getaways including camping and hiking in state parks and attending LSU games.As a gynecologist, he specializes in evaluating and treating hormonal imbalances, including perimenopausal issues, with bioidentical hormone replacement therapy. For many years he has performed hormone pellet procedures with outstanding results for his patients. A woman has many complex medical issues throughout her entire adult life. From puberty to pregnancy to the perimenopausal and menopausal years, it helps to have an OB\/GYN  physician to partner with each patient during every stage of her life.Along with hormonal imbalances, women have many other associated issues including infertility, abnormal bleeding, reproductive problems, and pain. Dr. Fuller has extensive experience as a womens health care specialist. His professional interests include care of routine and high risk OB patients and minimally invasive GYN surgery, including being certified to perform da Vinci robotic cases.  Another special interest includes treating heavy vaginal bleeding with outpatient hysteroscopy and NovaSure ablation of the uterine lining. Dr. Fuller finds it rewarding to be able to offer help for all of these concerns.One thing Dr. Fuller knows after taking care of women for over thirty years, is that each womans individual needs must be handled with individualized care. Being a certified bioTE provider, he feels he can offer the best possible plan to evaluate and treat all of the aspects that cause a womans hormone imbalance. Dr. Fuller also offers bioidentical hormonal testosterone pellet therapy for men. Many men discover how much better their partner feel after her hormones are optimized and want to feel better also. Many men wonder why they waited so long to get tested after seeing how much better their lives have become. I am truly honored to have been part of the lives of many women in Acadiana, from the thrill of delivering healthy children, to the heartbreak of infertility and pregnancy losses and cancer.  One of the most gratifying experiences I've had is taking care of three generations of women in the same family. I have also had the amazing experience of delivering babies of mothers and fathers that I delivered.Compassion, trust, and calmness are virtues I strive for each day, and I feel my years of experience can better help me to care for the variety of medical issues affecting our patients.Please visit our website www.georgefullermd.com to learn more about our practice.

name: Derma-Tech
bio: Joined Derma-Tech Medical Spa located in Joplin, MO in Jan. 2016 Currently practicing gynecology at Barton County Memorial Hospital since 2006 located in Lamar, MO Prior to moving to Lamar had a gynecology practice in Joplin, MO from 1994-2006 Undergrad in physiology from Oklahoma State OSU in 1986 Graduated Medical School from University of OK OU in 1990 Did OB\/GYN residency at University of Oklahoma in Tulsa and graduated in 1994 Board Certified in Obstetrics & Gynecology I am married with 3 children and love doing family activities together as well as sewing and crafting.

name: Desert Wellness Center
bio: Dr. Kris Wallace is a licensed Naturopathic Physician with a passion for family medicine.  She graduated summa cum laude from Northern Arizona University with a Masters Degree in Health Psychology and began her career as a health educator and health coach.  Recognizing the whole person in a journey to health, Dr. Wallace continued her education and earned her Doctorate of Naturopathic Medicine from Southwest College of Naturopathic Medicine in Tempe, Arizona.  With over 20 years in the health field, she now practices Naturopathic Medicine with a focus on the whole person not just symptoms. She uses the most effective natural treatments in conjunction with the latest medical research.  Her practice focus includes pediatric and adolescent health, hormone balancing, anti-aging, acne and other skin conditions, mental health and acute routine illness.   Kris has received advanced training in anti-aging and acne facial treatments including PRP (Plasma Rich Platelet), Botox, and facial fillers, pediatric and adolescent specific health concerns including behavioral\/attention issues, allergies and gastrointestinal disorders, advanced endocrinology\/hormone\/thyroid balancing, and biogenomic testing and treatment.  In addition to being a member and former Board Member for the Arizona Naturopathic Medical Association (AzNMA), she is also a member of the American Association of Naturopathic Physicians (AANP).Kriss passion for family medicine stems from her love of her own family as a wife and mother of 4 children.  As a native Arizonan she enjoys hiking, spending time with her family, practicing yoga, and cooking.

name: Destination Health
bio: Dr. Robin Hall is a board certified family physician who has been practicing medicine in the Colleyville\/Southlake area since 1991.She graduated magna cum laude from Texas Wesleyan University in Ft. Worth with a Bachelor of Science Degree in Biology and a minor in Business.Dr. Hall received her Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine (D.O.) degree from The University of North Texas Health Science Center\/Texas College of Osteopathic Medicine in Ft. Worth. Following graduation, she completed a one year transitional internship at Osteopathic Medical Center of Texas, followed by an additional two years of family practice residency through the Texas College of Osteopathic Medicine. Following her residency, she became board  certified by the American Osteopathic Board of Family Medicine.She was honored to have had the opportunity to do some of her training at M.D. Anderson Cancer Center, Ft. Carson Army Base, UT Tyler Chest Hospital and Parkland Hospital.

name: Destination Health
bio: Dr. Daniel Melville is a Board Certified Family Medicine physician practicing at Destination Health in Southlake, TX.  Under his current practice concept and by limiting the quantity of patients whom are served, he takes pride in truly getting to know each and every patient and individualizing their treatment recommendations.   Dr. Melville earned the title of Distinguished Graduate from the United States Air Force Academy, by graduating in the top of his class academically, militarily, and physically.  He then received his Medical Degree from Louisiana State University Health Sciences Center in Shreveport, immediately followed by completing his training in Family Medicine, specifically with rural emphasis.  His unique training allows him to practice medicine in hospital and emergency medicine environments, in addition to outpatient clinical experiences.  His true passion in medicine, however, focuses on coordinating preventive and comprehensive care for his patients.   Dr. Melville has successfully practiced in academic and private sectors since 2007.  He has also completed advanced training in the Bale\/Doneen Heart Attack and Stroke Prevention Program.  Additionally, he has served as an Aviation Medical Examiner with the FAA and as a Civil Surgeon for the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services.

bio: Elizabeth Nelson, APRN is located at 356 South Main Street, Ainsworth, NE.  She owns her own family medical clinic, Devine Healthcare, LLC.  She has an interest in hormone replacement and sees a lot of women's health patients.  She has seen first-hand how pre-menopause, menopause and post-menopause affects patients from a wide age range.  It can truly make not only their life miserable, but the people who surround them.  She finds it exciting and intriguing that feeling so poorly can easily be fixed with some education and treatment!   \Libs\" is married and has two wiener dogs

name: Diabetes and Wellness Clinic, LLC
bio: Michelle has a Bachelor of Science from Mount Marty College, a Masters of Science as a Family Nurse Practitioner and a Doctorate of Nursing Practice.   She owns and operates a healthcare clinic specializing in Diabetes and Wellness.  She is currently Board Certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner and Advanced Diabetes Management.  She is also working on certification as a Healing Touch Practitioner.  Diabetes and Wellness Clinic LLC is the region's leading provider of comprehensive health care services. Dr. Michelle Brtek Zwiener, a Family Nurse Practitioner, has been caring for the Norfolk area for the past 10 years. Her specialties include management of prediabetes, diabetes, thyroid disorders, weight management, hormonal imbalance, fatigue, and anyone that is frustrated with their current treatment.  Our office specializes in education and co-managing healthcare with our patients.  We utilize an integrative approach to provide the best care for you and your family.   We pay great attention to the quality of our services. You can find detailed information about our services online or contact us for help.
